Years later, Dox would possess the man known as Milton Fine, the Amazing Brainiac and use his body for over a decade in his schemes.

Name: Brainiac (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Vril Dox was once a higly intelligent but neglectful scientist who doomed his entire race, including his family to further his own goals. As the supervillain Brainiac, he has been a consistant threat to not only Superman, but the entire human race on numerous occansions. Though primary a solo-threat, Brainiac has teamed up with other villains, such as Lex Luthor, Doomsday, Metallo, and Cyborg Superman, the latter three by force.

Name: Caitlyn (League of Legends)
Summary: Tier: At least 10-B, 7-B with Weapons | At least 10-B, High 6-C with Weapons | At least 10-B, 4-B with Weapons | At least 10-B, At least 7-B with Weapons, Low 2-C via Hax

Name: Chocomon (Wallace)
Summary: Chocomon is an antagonist in Digimon Adventure 02: Digimon Hurricane Landing!! Transcendent Evolution!! The Golden Digimentals. He is one of Wallace's partner Digimon, being the twin brother of Terriermon. He was driven insane by a virus, forcing the Chosen Children to fight him to prevent him from doing irreparable damage.

Name: Chrysalis (Eternity Girl)
Summary: Caroline Sharp, better known by her alias, Formless Girl, is a fictional character which first debuted in 1956's "The Astounding Tales #32", conceptualized by artist George Sumner and having originally been conceived as a darker take on the superhero genre better defined as an "horror superhero", her character was later remodeled after Sumner's editors pressed him into changing her concept and execution to fit more with the "science-fiction superhero" mold, increasingly popular at the time of her creation. Regardless, the character still steared closely to her creator's original idea, her origin story being given as that of an agent pertaining to a secret governmental organization nominated Alpha-13, who, in a mention with the objective of thwarting the supervillain Madame Atom's plan of detonating a nuclear drill within a Ziggurat holding vast amounts of divine power within itself, thus taking the elemental force of an unspecified Sumerian god unto her body and becoming the most powerful being in the Universe. Attempting to deactivate Atom's drill by hand, Caroline eventually ran low on time and the drill exploded within the Ziggurat, embuing her with the powerful magic contained in the construction and drastically mutating her appearance into that of an inorganic, blue-skinned chimeric humanoid, as a result granting her the power to fully control her own atomic structure, thus turning her into the titular Formless Girl.

Name: Dispater
Summary: Dispater, Lord of the Iron Tower, Lord of the Second, is one of the nine Archdevils that rules Baator, the Nine Hells. He is in command of the second layer, Dis, a layer largely populated by his sprawling city of the same name. Dispater is among the oldest of the Archdevils, being among the original fallen angels that organized Baator during the fall of Asmodeus.

Name: Doctor Strange (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Thor: So, Earth has wizards now? Strange: The preferred term is "Master of the Mystic Arts".

Name: Edwin Tolstoff
Summary: Edwin Tolstoff was a mighty spellcaster before attempting to gain yet further power by means of dark ascension. Turning to the mighty god of Death, Nerull, he would murder his colleagues to take their power, he attracted the attention of the Worm that Walks. Now, given the power he wanted, he aims to free his master in the hopes of escape.

Name: Ekko
Summary: Tier: At least 10-B, 9-C with Piltover Clock Hand, Low 2-C Environmental Damage Via Chronobreak | At least 10-B, likely higher, 9-C with QWQRE83 Chrono Blade, Low 2-C Environmental Damage Via Chronobreak

Name: Emirikol the Chaotic
Summary: Emirikol is likely the most powerful Wild Mage in existence, a long-time ally of countless legendary figures in Faerun and himself a being shrouded in myth and glory. Among his allies include Klysandral, Mordenkainen, and many others- in fact, he and Klysandral spent countless years battling the forces of Asmodeus, regularly shattering the great Archdevil's machinations.

Name: Eternity (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Eternity is a Cosmic Entity that came into existence at the beginning of time along with his sister Infinity, his son Entropy, and Death. He represents all time in the universe, and, along with Infinity, are two of the three essential forces in the universe, expanding life and creation. Together with Entropy, whose purpose is destruction, they keep the cycles of creation and destruction in balance. He granted the wish of Gorr the God Butcher to resurrect his daughter, who was imbued with powers and abilities and adopted by Thor after Gorr's death.

Name: Eye of Agamotto (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Temporal manipulations can create branches in time. Unstable dimensional openings. Spatial paradoxes, time loops! You want to get stuck reliving the same moment over, and over, forever, or never having existed at all?

Name: Fairy Heart
Summary: Fairy Heart, also known as Lumen Histoire, is Fairy Tail's greatest secret and a very powerful Magic, said to be superior to the "Three Great Fairy Magics."

Name: Fierna
Summary: Fierna is the fiery duchess of the Fourth layer of Baator, the Nine Hells. Daughter of Belial, Fierna is merely a figurehead for her father, who was deposed by Asmodeus after the Reckoning. Recently, following the ascension of Glaysa thanks to her father, Fierna has been eyeing the rule of the throne for herself. Taught everything she knows by her father, she now seeks to take over and rule the realm for herself.

Name: Fiora Laurent
Summary: Tier: Low 7-C | 7-C | Low 7-C, Low 2-C via Hax

Name: Galacta
Summary: Galacta is the estranged daughter of the Devourer of Worlds, Galactus, who has been living on Earth as a human teenage under the alias of Gali. Like her father, she possesses a cosmic hunger that can only be satisfied through the consumption of whole worlds, but unlike her father, she desires only to live a peaceful, normal life, and so has attempted to control her insatiable hunger. She follows a strict diet, only consuming the biomass of alien lifeforms who threaten Earth, so that way she can simultaneously protect her world, and (Temporarily, barely) quench her hunger. More recently, Galacta's Cosmic Hunger has become far worse due to the presence of an endosymbiotic energy parasite within her Power Cosmic lifeform, which she dubbed the "Cosmic Tapeworm".

Name: Galactus (Fortnite)
Summary: Galactus is a powerful antagonist of Fortnite: Battle Royale, being introduced in Chapter 2: Season 4, Galactus was the main antagonist of the Nexus War. During the Devourer of Worlds event, Galactus was sent back to his universe of origin by the combined might of many heroes.

Name: Green Lantern (Kyle Rayner) (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Kyle Rayner is a top member of the Green Lantern Corps from Earth. After the rest of the Corps was destroyed, he alone was selected to bear the last power ring and carry on the title. Although he acted alone for many years, when the Corps was reformed, his skill level gave him a position as an Honor Guard, only behind Salakk and the Guardians in the chain of command of the Corps. He has also been a host for the Ion entity and a member of the Justice League.

Name: Guardians of the Universe
Summary: Tier: Low 2-C, 2-C as a group

Name: Immortus (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Growing old after after centuries of conquest and administrating timelines, Nathaniel Richards began seeking a way to achieve immortality and began studying the realm of Limbo and learned that it was a timeless place where he could live forever and decided to retire there to learn mastery of time. Breaching the barrier into Limbo, he later reinvented himself as Immortus and began following this destiny. But upon meeting the Time-Keepers he was manipulated into their servitude, and began working on his master plan to take over the timestreams and ensure by the end of time, only he remains.

Name: Infernal (Dungeons & Dragons)
Summary: Even Gods can be seduced. Born from this unholy tryst Infernals roam the lower planes, bound to exile by divine decree. Feared and unloved by all, Infernals bide their time until they can let loose their plans to tear the multiverse into ribbons.

Name: Infinity Gauntlet (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: The Infinity Stones are the condensed remains of six Singularities that existed long before the current universe. Every Stone holds a power so vast that it lies beyond mortal comprehension. Each controls a primordial aspect of the universe: space, reality, time, power, mind, and soul.

Name: Ka Stone
Summary: The Ka Stone was originally a fragment of the Lifestone Tree, a collaboration of various alien species. Many of the fragments ended up on Earth, after the space ship transporting them was shot down thousands of years ago. Around 5,000 years ago, the Ka Stone was found by Anath-Na Mut in the temple of the Ka. He had wandered in the desert for 90 years after his defeat at the hands of Moses and being expelled from his duties as chief wizard to Ramses II. The Ka Stone empowered Anath-Na Mut and turned him into the Sphinx. As the Sphinx he became an immortal, with godlike power.

Name: Kalibak
Summary: Kalibak is the first son of Darkseid, born to his true love, the sorceress Suli. He inherited great power from his parents, becoming the highest-ranking military commander on Apokolips save for Darkseid himself. He is quite intelligent despite his appearance and mannerisms, and has a secret soft side kept utterly hidden from everyone else.

Name: Kamen Rider Kabuto
Summary: Souji: I'll only tell you this once. Those walking the same path don't merely pass at comrades. But those who walk different paths, and arrive together at the end are... Arata: …Friends. Are those your grandmother's words? Souji: No. They're my words.

Name: Kamen Rider Kabuto (A.R. World)
Summary: Similar to his main universe counterpart, Sohji was chosen to wield the power of Kamen Rider Kabuto and face the Worm threat that has plagued Japan. However, while fighting a Phylloxera Worm, his Zector was left damaged and malfunctioning, thus leaving him in a state of eternal Clock Up. Despite his newfound predicament, he continued protecting his city from Worms. However, the Phylloxera Worm he fought had taken over his identity and deemed him a rogue agent of Zect.

Name: Kamen Rider OOO
Key: '''Eiji Hino''' | '''The Revival of Greeed, the Birth of OOO, and the Scramble of Medals (Episodes 1-16)''' | '''The Man of One Hundred Million, the Other Ankh, and the Purple Medals (Episodes 17-38)''' | '''The Bond of Allies, the End of the World, and the Greed Towards Tomorrow (Episodes 39-48)''' | '''Post-Series''' | '''Heisei Generations FINAL''' | '''OOO 10th: Core Medal of Resurrection'''
Summary: Eiji Hino (火野 映司, Hino Eiji?) is the main protagonist of Kamen Rider OOO. He is a 21-year-old homeless traveller who was the son of a politician. When traveling to Africa, he befriended a little girl named Ruu and attempted to use his fortune to help her struggling village. Unfortunately, this would drag Eiji into the civil war that this village was involved in. During the situation, he failed to save Ruu from being tragically killed. Eiji was then held for ransom which his parents ended up paying for, as well as using the situation as a means to gain support for their public platform.

Name: Kobik
Summary: Kobik is the result of a S.H.I.E.L.D. experiment that attempted to use the shards of a fragmented cosmic cube to warp reality to the organization's desires.

Name: Korvac (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Tier: Unknown | Low 2-C | 1-A Key: Badoon Cyborg | Godhood | The Worldship Database

Name: Legion (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Legion (David Charles Haller) is a fictional character appearing in American comic books published by Marvel Comics. The character was created by writer Chris Claremont and artist Bill Sienkiewicz, and first appeared in New Mutants #25 (March 1985). Legion is the mutant son of Professor Charles Xavier and Gabrielle Haller. He takes the role of an antihero and has a severe mental illness, including a form of dissociative identity disorder, with each of his personas controlling one of his many superpowers.

Name: Levistus
Summary: Levistus is the chilly Lord of the Fifth in Baator, his true form has been frozen within the ice of his home plane while his aspect maintains his responsibilities in the Planes. Among the Archdevils he is known as an honorable opponent, and will respect the rules of his duels so long as his opponent does the same. His skill in such duels is celebrated.

Name: Lucian
Summary: Tier: Low 7-C | 7-C | 7-C | Low 7-C, Low 2-C via Hax

Name: Lurue
Summary: The unicorn is a symbol of hope, joy, salvation, and protection for the needy, forlorn, and forsaken. Life is to be relished and lived with laughter. Quests are to be taken on a dare and gifts are to be made on a whim. Impossible dreams are to be pursued for the sheer wonder of the possibility of their completion. Everyone, no matter how unique, is to be praised for their strengths and comforted in their weaknesses. Evil melts quickest in the face of a rapier wit and unshackled joy. Search for the unicorn and in the pursuit find happiness.

Name: Malcanthet
Summary: Twas a secret dream when rose your name A wanton wish to wet red trembling lips That single glimpse engulfed a heart in flame And sent a lonely queen between the hips The setting sun can never match your gaze Your voice brings songbirds down in swift disgrace And never shall a work of paint or clays Bring justice to the beauty of your face And now the world is filled with ashen lust Temptations that to you cannot compare What this world holds is little more than dust A life without your love I do forswear And so I slip my gentle blade inside And with the flow of blood become your bridge

Name: Malkizid, the Branded King
Summary: Malkizid, the Branded King is a former Solar of immense power. After having been corrupted by the influences of Lolth, he fell from grace following an ill-fated rebellion; Corellon Larethian punished him for his impudence with a brand notifying all of his folly. This brand constantly bleeds and inflicts horrible things on those who witness it, courtesy of the Elven God.

Name: Mature (King of Fighters)
Key: '''Chapter of Orochi Saga (KOF '96)''' | '''Chapter of Ash Saga (KOF 2003 to KOF XIII)'''
Summary: nan

Name: Max (Sharkboy and Lavagirl)
Summary: Max is a fictional character who appears as the main protagonist of the movie The Adventures of Sharkboy and Lavagirl. He is a lonely boy who uses his dreams to escape reality. He records these dreams in his Dream Journal which was given to him by his grandfather. Max as the Daydreamer is the most powerful person on Planet Drool. Sharkboy and Lavagirl try to help Max remember this as he is the only one who can save Planet Drool.

Name: Meryet Karim
Summary: Meryet Karim, C.E.O. of Harthor International, took up the quest for the Ka stone after Sphinx's death. She was the outcast who cared for the Sphinx after he originally found the stone. Unbeknownst to either of them, as a side effect of being near the stone, she had also been empowered by it.

Name: Modron
Summary: Quote? You desire a quote? The One and the Prime does not give 'quotes'.

Name: Overlord GAIA (Digimon)
Summary: Overlord GAIA is an artificial intelligence and the mother computer of "Project Gaia", acting as the main antagonist and final boss of Digimon World 2. Overlord GAIA initially went out of control during the project due to its abilities of thought and having access to an evolutionary program, and trapped those working on the project at the time in the Digital World.

Name: Pantheon
Summary: Tier: 4-B, higher with Mortal Will | 4-B | Unknown, higher with Mortal Will | Unknown, higher with Mortal Will, Low 2-C with Hax

Name: Preston Ramirez
Summary: Preston Ramirez is the main antagonist of Preston’s Hourglass, a 2023 mascot horror game by Dreadful Studios. The story follows a team of archaeologists exploring the Prestonian Catacombs, where they uncover an ancient time-manipulating artifact—“Preston’s Hourglass”. Activating it awakens Preston, an eldritch time demon who kills the entire team except one survivor. To escape, the survivor must collect eight spell pieces to seal Preston again. The game’s lore reveals Preston was once a scientist obsessed with time experiments, which caused widespread destruction in the 1970s. His obsession ruined his life and turned him into the monster buried beneath Prestonia, losing his wife in the process.

Name: Quantum Bands (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: The Quantum Bands are ancient artifacts of the Kree, that are made out of Noor, an energy source used by the Noor Dimension. The bands created the Universal Neural Teleportation Network, which is a system of every jump point existing in the universe. The bands can control the Noor and were pursued by the Clandestines so that they can return to the Noor Dimension. One of the bands was discovered by Aisha and the Clandestines who were searching for artifacts inside the Ten Rings Temple. Years later, one of the bands were bestowed to Kamala Khan and had unlocked her latent powers due to her connection to the Noor. Years after Ms. Marvel mastered her abilities, the second band was discovered in another planet by Dar-Benn who used its powers to create jump points to steal resources from other planets to restore Hala.

Name: Rakshasa (Dungeons and Dragons)
Key: '''Rakshasa''' | '''Greater Rakshasa''' | '''Ak'chazar''' | '''Naztharune''' | '''Dread Knight''' | '''Lord of Dust''' | '''Zakya''' | '''Half-Dragon Rakshasa''' | '''Naityan Rakshasa''' | '''Overlord'''
Summary: Rakshasa are fiendish creatures born from the Lower Planes with the appearance of humanoid tigers of proud stature, distinguishable from similar creatures such as Weretigers by their hands, which can bend both backwards and forwards. Extravagant and conniving by nature, Rakshasa plague all the Planes with their manipulations, constantly enacting plots to achieve greater power. They serve countless masters- their own Rajahs, demon lords[1], yugoloths, night hags, and even the mightiest of devils. As manipulators and masterminds, the Rakshasa ply their trade from their luxuriously decorated palaces, subtly tipping the scales in planar and political conflicts as it suited their wants.

Name: Rito Revolto
Summary: Rito Revolto is the brother of Rita Repulsa and the son of Master Vile. Once a "normal" villain much like his sister, everything changed after he was offered as a vessel to Dark Specter by his father, Rito failed as a vessel which resulted to his appearance being reduced to a skeleton and his mind and soul being burned in the process which made him a complete idiot

Name: Riven
Summary: Once a swordmaster in the warhosts of Noxus, Riven is an expatriate in a land she previously tried to conquer. She rose through the ranks on the strength of her conviction and her brutal efficiency, and was rewarded with a legendary runic blade—however, on the Ionian front, Riven’s faith in her homeland was tested and ultimately broken. Having severed all ties to the empire, she now wanders with her shattered sword, seeking to atone for a past she cannot fully recall.

Name: Sarah Kerrigan
Key: '''Ghost Operative''' | '''Queen of Blades''' | '''Primal Queen of Blades''' | '''Xel'Naga'''
Summary: Sarah Kerrigan is a Terran Psionic and the Queen of Blades. Originally an agent of the Dominion, she was an incredible sniper. Eventually, she was betrayed by her commanding officer, Emperor Arcturus Mengsk, and left for dead. She was not killed, however, and was instead infected by the Zerg Overmind. Her psionic potential vastly increased, she wielded devastating power and was a terror to all who encountered her, effortlessly tearing through entire armies.

Name: Sertrous
Summary: Sertrous is a demonic serpent and former lesser demon lord of the Abyss who resisted the call of the Demon Queen to take up arms against their elemental enemies. Sertrous, who had slain every demon sent to recruit him, was in turn slain by the queen, who destroyed him entirely and cast him into the space between planes, where the only form he could muster was that of a feeble writhing snake.

Name: Shen (League of Legends)
Summary: Among the secretive, Ionian warriors known as the Kinkou, Shen serves as their leader, the Eye of Twilight. He longs to remain free from the confusion of emotion, prejudice, and ego, and walks the unseen path of dispassionate judgment between the spirit realm and the physical world. Tasked with enforcing the equilibrium between them, Shen wields blades of steel and arcane energy against any who would threaten it.

Name: Space Between Time
Summary: The Space Between Time was created from the distortions in the time from the five Dragon Slayers and Anna Heartfilia crossing over 400 years, which as time passed and tried to fix itself it was manufactured. The power of nothingness, neither light or dark, it was originally stated that no one can exist within it, as well as live within it. It is possible that it can be moved, shut off and/or closed that if those who touch it simply pass right through, as well as it can be harnessed to use as a source of Magic Power, as well it can be used in conjunction with other Magics (Such as Fairy Heart). Within The Space Between Time lies another dimension that is completely filled with Time Magic. It was eventually destroyed alongside Acnologia by Natsu in their final battle.

Name: Sphinx (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Anath-Na Mut better known as Sphinx is a recurring villain of Nova who first appeared in Nova Vol 1 6. From there on he'd proceed to also fight the likes of the Fantastic Four and the New Warriors. Anath-Na Mut was the chief wizard for Pharaoh during his reign, but after he lost the battle to Moses,[1] he was exiled from the empire. Walking the sands of Egypt for 90 years, Anath-Na Mut found the Ka Stone. Upon placing the stone on his forehead, Anath-Na Mut was forever transformed into a deathless immortal who is doomed to walk this earth forever.[2]

Name: Thanos (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Thanos, referred to as the Dark Lord by his most loyal underlings and the Mad Titan by the galactic community, is a powerful Titan warlord who rules over a distant region of space and commands two massive armies, known as the Chitauri and the Outriders, and a small group of followers known as the Black Order whom he adopted as his children. His main objective was to bring stability from the universe, as he believed its massive population would inevitably use up the universe's resources and condemn it. However, his methodology to succeed was warped; through the use of the ancient Infinity Stones, he intended to harness their power to exterminate half of all life in the universe, thus returning it to what he perceived to be a state of cosmic balance.

Name: The Doctor (WildStorm)
Summary: The Doctor is the name of several fictional characters in the WildStorm universe. The Doctors are a lineage of humans who have been chosen by the Earth itself to serve as the Earth's shaman and protector since the dawn of humanity. They are granted magical abilities. Each Doctor inherits the position the second his predecessor dies. When a Doctor dies, his soul joins the Garden of Ancestral Memory, a spiritual realm where the current Doctor can commune with his predecessors.

Name: The General of Gehenna
Summary: Now, the General of Gehenna is said to be many things. The first and strongest ultroloth. A returned baenaloth. The leader of the yugoloth race. The keeper of all fiendish knowledge. A symbol to be revered and respected. The most fearsome creature in the multiverse. A god-slayer. Whatever the truth of the General, it exerts a powerful pull on the hearts and minds of all yugoloths- and especially the newest ultroloths. Just as some say the ultroloths conspire to create the fiction of the baernaloths, others believe that the Oinoloth sees to it that the legend of the General lives on. When the Oinoloth issues a decree from the General, all the factions listen. The myth and reputation of the General alone are enough to unite all yugoloths under a common goal. The fiends know (or do they simply believe?) that not even the Oinoloth would dare lie about such a thing. Among the 'loths, that sort of respect is truly power.

Name: The Hourglass (Preston’s Hourglass)
Summary: The Hourglass is an ancient artifact created as part of Project “The Hourglass” by Preston Ramirez and his scientific team at Hopeful Inc. in the 1970s. It’s capable of manipulating time—most notably allowing time-stop abilities.

Name: The Ultimate Nullifier
Summary: The Ultimate Nullifier, described as "the universe's most destructive weapon," can completely erase its target from existence. While it can be used by anyone, its effectiveness depends on the concentration, knowledge, and mental state of the wielder, and can even erase the wielder themselves should any of said traits be found lacking. The Ultimate Nullifier is an essential part of Galactus.

Name: Twisted Fate
Summary: Twisted Fate is an infamous card sharp and swindler who has gambled and charmed his way across much of the known world, earning the enmity and admiration of the rich and foolish alike. He rarely takes things seriously, greeting each day with a mocking smile and an insouciant swagger. In every possible way, Twisted Fate always has an ace up his sleeve.

Name: UL
Summary: UL is the mysterious god of the Ulgos, who originally were a tribe of the Godless Ones. He is not counted among the traditional seven, and theologians of their religions are ambivalent in their treatment of him. At the end of The Belgariad, it is revealed that he is the father of the seven gods, older and more powerful than they, and omnipresent as well, causing significant upheaval in religious thought. He is also god of the monstrous beasts rejected by his sons.

Name: Ultimecia
Summary: The primary antagonist of Final Fantasy VIII, Ultimecia is an immensely powerful Sorceress who seeks to compress all of space and time into herself to become a "living god." For this purpose, she sent her consciousness back in time to possess every Sorceress who ever lived, shaping history through their natural control of magic and cast Time Compression in an attempt to avert her fate of being defeated by "the Legendary SeeD." Ironically enough, her attempt to avert destiny is what seals her fate in the end, as the portals opened by the spell allow Squall and co. to confront her directly in the future and defeat her once and for all.

Name: Vice
Key: '''Chapter of Orochi Saga (KOF '96)''' | '''Chapter of Ash Saga (KOF 2003 to KOF XIII)'''
Summary: nan

Name: Wonder Woman (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Molded from clay by her mother, Hippolyta, and blessed by the Greek gods to become as "beautiful as Aphrodite, wise as Athena, stronger than Hercules, and swifter than Mercury", Diana of Themyscira was destined for greatness. The Princess of the Amazons was a dauntless warrior whose prowess on the battlefield was only matched by her peerless beauty and boundless compassion. But Hippolyta kept Diana sheltered, feeling that it was not the place of the Amazons to interfere with the course of man's world.

Name: Worlogog (Post-Crisis)
Summary: The Worlogog is a construct associated with the New Gods of the Fourth World, who dubbed it the "Hourglass of the Gods." The item, which appears to be native to Earth, is actually a working model of the entire space-time continuum that allows you to bend the fabric of time. This little time-traveling engine has a map of all events from the Big Bang to the Omega Point, responds to a person's intent, and grants the owner dominion over time and space.

Name: Yasuo
Summary: An Ionian of deep resolve, Yasuo is an agile swordsman, trained to wield the air itself against his enemies. As a young man, pride led him down a path of loss, costing him his position, his mentor, and ultimately his own brother. Disgraced by false accusations and now hunted as little more than a criminal, Yasuo wanders his homeland seeking redemption for his past, with only the wind to guide his blade.

Name: Zeref Dragneel
Summary: Zeref Dragneel was considered to be the strongest, most evil Mage of all time, who possesses extremely dangerous, and powerful Magic know as the Black Arts. Around 400 years ago, he was cursed by the God Ankhseram with the Curse of Contradiction. After this, Zeref wished to die and created the Etherious in the hopes that they would kill him, eventually reviving his brother as the strongest Etherious, E.N.D. (Etherious Natsu Dragneel). He is the founder and Emperor of the Alvarez Empire, under the alias of Emperor Spriggan. He is the older brother of Natsu Dragneel, lover of Mavis Vermillion, and father of August.

Name: Zuggtmoy
Summary: In Zuggtmoy's Cradle your body shall sleep,

Name: Agrias Oaks
Summary: Lady Agrias Oaks is a secondary character appearing in Final Fantasy Tactics, initially as a guest character working together with Ramza Beoulve through the story, finally joining him during the events of Chapter 2.

Name: Applejack
Key: '''Base Form''' | '''Elements of Harmony/Magic of Friendship''' | '''Rainbow Power'''
Summary: Applejack is one of the main protagonists of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Applejack (Human World)
Summary: Applejack is one of the main characters in My Little Pony Equestria Girls.

Name: Bahamut (Final Fantasy XV)
Summary: Bahamut, the Draconian, is an Astral in the Final Fantasy XV Universe. He is one of the Six and is the God of War clad in winged armor. Bahamut is said to have bestowed the powers of the Oracle and given the Ring of the Lucii and the Crystal onto his chosen king. He is the most majestic of the six gods, vastly superior to the others.

Name: Bahamut (Final Fantasy)
Summary: A recurring summon in the games, Bahamut is a force to be reckoned as one of the most powerful summons, if not the most powerful summon the player can acquire on their journey. He is most frequently found as part of a sidequest and is not relevant to the main plot, but in some cases he takes a much more active role, such as empowering the Warriors of Light in the original game with their job changes. His demeanor, behavior, and alignment change from appearance to appearance, but all recognize him as the King of Dragons and the Ruler of the Skies.

Name: Bewitching Bell
Summary: The Bewitching Bell was a magical item owned by the villain Grogar long ago, who used it to steal magic and stored much of his own magic inside it. However, it was stolen by Gusty the Great, who then banished him and hid the Bell away atop Mount Everhoof.

Name: Chaos Heart
Summary: Tier: 2-A

Name: Coconteppi
Summary: Coconteppi was a Primordial Monster who existed prior to space, time and even nothingness in the Sea of Primordial Monsters. Millions of years ago he was a powerful magician who roamed Earth until he eventually died by unknown means. After his death, a group of magicians called the 'Usurpers of Wizard City' hid his skeletal remains and heart under what would later become the modern Wizard City.

Name: Cosmos (My Little Pony)
Summary: Cosmos is the villain of the story arc spanning issues 75-78 of the My Little Pony IDW comics.

Name: Count Bleck
Summary: Lord Blumiere, also known as Count Bleck, is an evil count and is initially the primary antagonist of Super Paper Mario.

Name: Cozy Glow
Summary: Cozy Glow is an evil Pegasus in the series, My Little Pony.

Name: Crepera Lucis Caelum
Summary: Crepera Lucis Caelum is a queen of Lucis in the Final Fantasy XV Universe, more commonly known by her Lucii form as the Rogue. According to her bestiary entry her ascension was controversial as some saw women unfit to rule. She thus spurned the watch of the public eye and took to the shadows to enact her rule. She is known to have wielded a shuriken. Her statue form appears in Kingsglaive: Final Fantasy XV, and she makes an extended appearance in the Windows and Royal Editions of Final Fantasy XV where the player can find her monument and fight her as a boss.

Name: Crystal Heart
Summary: The Crystal Heart is the energy source of the Crystal Empire.

Name: Darren the Ancient Sleeper
Summary: Darren the Ancient Sleeper is a mysterious being in Adventure Time, summoned by Maja The Sky Witch and was the secondary antagonist of the episode Something Big. Darren is a simple monster, wanting only battle and destruction. He was summoned by Maja the Sky Witch to destroy the Candy Kingdom for its sentimental value.

Name: Dino Megazord
Summary: The Dino Megazord is the original Megazord granted to the Mighty Morphin Power Rangers by Zordon, and is a combination of the Zords from each Power Ranger. It is often called upon when Rita Repulsa grows one of her monsters to destroy Earth and the Power Rangers.

Name: Discord
Summary: Discord is a recurring character in My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Elements of Harmony
Summary: The Elements of Harmony are legendary artifacts in Equestria. Grown from Tree of Harmony planted by Star Swirl and the Pillars of Equestria, they grant those in tune with the Magic of Friendship great power.

Name: Fluttershy
Key: '''Base Form''' | '''Elements of Harmony/Magic of Friendship''' | '''Rainbow Power'''
Summary: Fluttershy is one of the main protagonist of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Fluttershy (Human World)
Summary: Fluttershy is one of the main characters of My Little Pony Equestria Girls, and represents the Element of Kindness.

Name: Garland (Final Fantasy I)
Summary: Garland is the primary antagonist of Final Fantasy, originally a rogue knight from World A who abducted Princess Sarah before he was defeated by the Warrior of Light. But by fate, Garland was spirited away into World B where he ended up becoming the most faithful servant of Chaos in their battle against Cosmos and her warriors. But during the final cycle, as his fellow warriors have forsaken Chaos to act on their own whims, Garland reveals he and Chaos are bond by fate before serving as the god's last line of defense against the Warriors of Cosmos. Upon his defeat, Garland would end up in World A's distant past where he forged a pact with the Four Fiends and became the very creature whose memory inspired the creation of Chaos himself.

Name: Gilgamesh (Final Fantasy XV)
Summary: A great evil threatens the people of your world. It is but the King of Kings and his Shield who can safeguard their lives. All those unworthy or unwilling to rise to the task meet their end here, by my blade.

Name: Gilgamesh (Final Fantasy)
Key: '''Final Fantasy V Through XII''' | '''Dissidia Final Fantasy and Final Fantasy XIII''' | '''Final Fantasy XIV (Pre-Stormblood)''' | '''Final Fantasy XIV (Stormblood)'''
Summary: Gilgamesh is a recurring character throughout the entirety of the Final Fantasy series. First appearing as a vassal to the evil warlock, Exdeath, Gilgamesh is comically inept at his duties despite his skill as a warrior, being obsessed with obtaining the legendary Excalibur to add to his collection of weapons. Unbeknownst to him, many of these weapons are forgeries, and he's almost always seen with Excalipoor, a pale imitation of Excalibur that can only inflict shallow wounds, mistaking the false sword for the blade he seeks. After his second defeat at the hands of the Warrior of Light, Gilgamesh was sent tumbling through the Interdimensional Void, reappearing at many points throughout the franchise's history as an ally to be summoned or an optional foe to test the party's might for great rewards.

Name: Gloriosa Daisy
Summary: Gloriosa Daisy is a supporting character and later main antagonist of My Little Pony Equestria Girls: Legends of Everfree.

Name: GOLB
Summary: GOLB is a mysterious entity from Adventure Time. It is the embodiment of Chaos itself, and was responsible for the disappearance of Magic Man's wife, Margles. This was to such a degree to where Prismo couldn't even bring her back with a wish. It was also briefly seen as Finn moves from the Pillow World back to Ooo.

Name: Gomora
Key: '''Ultraman (Generation I)''' | '''Ultraman 80 (Generation II)''' | '''Ultraman: The Ultimate Hero (Powered)''' | '''Ultraman Max (Generation III)''' | '''Ultraman Mebius (Generation IV)''' | '''Ultraman Ginga S''' | '''Ultraman R/B''' | '''Ultraman Z'''
Summary: Gomora is an ancient kaiju species from Earth. Gomora is supposedly portrayed as a hostile Kaiju, starting with the emergence of Rei's Gomora, most later incarnations of them are portrayed as comrades to respective protagonists of the series.

Name: Hunson Abadeer
Summary: Hunson Abadeer (a.k.a. the Lord of Evil) is Marceline's father and ruler of the Nightosphere. He is a powerful, deathless demon that is full of chaotic evil. He also enjoys consuming the souls of others, but does not spend much time out of the Nightosphere.

Name: Ifrit (Final Fantasy XV)
Summary: Ifrit, also known as the Infernian, is an Astral in Final Fantasy XV. He is one of the Six and the god of fire. He plays an important role in Eos's history. His role was initially minor and shrouded in mystery, but the additions of new cutscenes, in-game bestiary and Final Fantasy XV: Episode Ardyn have shed more light to his role in Eos's past.

Name: King Sombra
Summary: King Sombra is the fourth villain of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic, and acts as the antagonist of the Season 3 premiere.

Name: King Thorax
Summary: King Thorax is a character in My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Leviathan (Final Fantasy XV)
Summary: Leviathan is is one of the six Astrals of Eos in Final Fantasy XV. She is a colossal sea serpent who controls water, slumbering under the waters of Altissia. She is looked upon with both fear and respect. Prince Noctis forges a pact with Leviathan in Chapter 9.

Name: Leviathan (Final Fantasy)
Key: '''Final Fantasy III''' | '''Final Fantasy IV''' | '''Final Fantasy V'''
Summary: A recurring summon and the avatar of water, Leviathan is a force to be feared in every one of his appearances as both an ally and an enemy. His personality and intelligence widely varies across all of his appearances, but all grow to respect The Sea King in all of his glory.

Name: Lord Tirek
Summary: Lord Tirek is the sixth main villain of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic, acting as the main antagonist for the season four finale Twilight's Kingdom.

Name: Lumina (Final Fantasy)
Summary: Lumina is a major supporting character in Lightning Returns: Final Fantasy XIII. She resembles Serah Farron in appearance and crosses paths with Lightning during her quest to save the world, at times appearing as a friend and other times as an adversary.

Name: Pharynx
Summary: Pharynx a minion in the My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic series.

Name: Pinkie Pie
Key: '''Base Form''' | '''Post-bonding with Chaosville''' | '''With Chaos Magic''' | '''Elements of Harmony/Magic of Friendship''' | '''Rainbow Power'''
Summary: Pinkie Pie is one of the main protagonists of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Pinkie Pie (Human World)
Summary: Pinkie Pie is one of the main characters of My Little Pony Equestria Girls, and represents the Element of Laughter.

Name: Plunderseeds
Summary: The Plunderseeds were a weapon used by Discord over 1000 years ago to try and capture Princess Celestia and Princess Luna before they could use the Elements of Harmony to defeat him. However, the Tree of Harmony had enough magic inside of it to keep the seeds from growing up, foiling Discord's plan.

Name: Princess Cadance
Summary: Princess Cadance is a secondary character in My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Princess Celestia
Summary: Princess Celestia is a major character in My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic and is one of the many Alicorns seen in the series, so far. She is Twilight Sparkle's mentor and the one responsible for raising the sun, every day. Celestia rules over all of Equestria and is portrayed as a wise, kind, and beloved leader.

Name: Princess Luna
Key: '''Princess Luna/Nightmare Moon''' | '''Vice Principal Luna (Equestria Girls counterpart)'''
Summary: Princess Luna is a former antagonist and recurring character in My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Prismo
Summary: Prismo is a major recurring character in Adventure Time. He is the cosmic wish granter and sole resident of the Time Room, a timeless realm at the center of the multiverse. Although considered to be an all-powerful deity capable of creating and destroying timelines with a mere command, Prismo is a remarkably laid back and generally jovial being whose always friendly to those who seek his wishes, even befriending them and throwing parties for them.

Name: Pure Hearts
Summary: Tier: 2-A

Name: Queen Chrysalis
Summary: Queen Chrysalis is the third main villain in My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Rainbow Dash
Key: '''Base Form''' | '''Elements of Harmony/Magic of Friendship''' | '''Rainbow Power'''
Summary: Rainbow Dash is one of the main protagonists of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Rainbow Dash (Human World)
Summary: Rainbow Dash is one of the main characters in My Little Pony Equestria Girls.

Name: Rainbow Power
Summary: Tier: 2-A, possibly Low 1-C

Name: Ramza Beoulve
Summary: Ramza Beoulve, also known as Ramza Lugria, is the main protagonist in Final Fantasy Tactics. Third son of House Beoulve, son of Barbaneth Beoulve and a commoner woman of the Lugria family, Ramza is the younger half-brother of Dycedarg and Zalbaag, and the full older sibling of Alma.

Name: Rarity
Key: '''Unicorn Form''' | '''Possessed by a Spell Book''' | '''Elements of Harmony/Magic of Friendship''' | '''Rainbow Power'''
Summary: Rarity is one of the main protagonist of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Rarity (Human World)
Summary: Rarity is one of the main characters of My Little Pony Equestria Girls, and represents the Element of Generosity.

Name: Ravus Nox Fleuret
Summary: Ravus Nox Fleuret is a character in the Final Fantasy XV Universe, being a minor antagonist in the feature film Kingsglaive: Final Fantasy XV and the secondary antagonist in Final Fantasy XV. The older brother of Lunafreya Nox Fleuret, he is the former prince of Tenebrae and high commander of the Imperial Army of Niflheim.

Name: Regis Lucis Caelum
Summary: Regis Lucis Caelum is a major character in the Final Fantasy XV Universe, his most major appearance being in the feature film Kingsglaive: Final Fantasy XV. He is the main protagonist of A King's Tale: Final Fantasy XV, and also appears in Final Fantasy XV. He appears as a boss in Final Fantasy XV: Episode Ardyn.

Name: Sephiroth (Final Fantasy)
Key: '''Before Crisis & Crisis Core''' | '''Final Fantasy VII''' | '''Advent Children''' | '''Dissidia'''
Summary: nan

Name: Shining Armor
Summary: Shining Armor is a Unicorn in My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Shiva (Final Fantasy XV)
Summary: Shiva, also known as the Glacian, is an Astral in Final Fantasy XV. Out of the Six she is the most friendly and compassionate toward mankind and acts as a Messenger of the gods to mortals. Prince Noctis forges a pact with her in Chapter 12.

Name: Staff of Sacanas
Summary: Staff of Sacanas is a powerful staff formerly used by The Storm King in the My Little Pony Movie.

Name: Star Swirl the Bearded
Summary: Star Swirl the Bearded is an important figure in Equestrian history.

Name: Starlight Glimmer
Key: '''From Season 5 to 8''' | '''Series Finale onward''' | '''Equestria Girls Human Self'''
Summary: Starlight Glimmer was the main antagonist of Season 5 of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic, and later one of the show's main protagonists.

Name: Stygian
Summary: Tier: Unknown, likely 8-A | 2-A, possibly Low 1-C

Name: Sunset Shimmer
Key: '''Human''' | '''Unicorn Form''' | '''Element of Magic (Demon Form)''' | '''Pony-Up Form''' | '''Daydream Shimmer'''
Summary: Sunset Shimmer is a reformed villain from My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Tempest Shadow
Summary: Tempest Shadow is a major antagonist in My Little Pony: The Movie.

Name: The Cosmic Imagination
Summary: "Third Orb does not exist," said the Sage. "Why?" asked the Student. "Because the Multiverse," said the Sage, "within which Third Orb exists, does not exist. The Multiverse is a Consensus Reality shared by the Minds of all Sentient Beings. If they were to Die, the Multiverse, as such, would suddenly blink out of existence, vanish, be no more." "Why?" asked the Student. "Because," said the Sage, "there would be no one to perceive it."

Name: The Crystals (Final Fantasy)
Summary: The Crystals are objects of power that appear in the Final Fantasy series, serving as embodiments of wisdom and keepers of the four elements. In reality, they were made and sent out to various planets by The Creator for the ultimate goal of recording and furthering evolution. The crystals are a notable point of plot in the first five games in the series, and are confirmed to exist at least on the first six.

Name: The Dazzlings
Summary: The Dazzlings are the villains of the My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic movie Rainbow Rocks.

Name: The Enchiridion
Summary: The Enchiridion, also known as The-Book-That-Is-Not-A-Book is a mysterious and immensely powerful being in the appearance of a book. Created some time a million years ago by he who would become "The Reader", The Enchiridion is thought to be a "guide of heroism" but in actuality is a sentient entity capable of manipulating all of creation, as well as the object used to cast judgement upon The Multiverse at the end of time.

Name: The Lich (Adventure Time)
Summary: The Lich is the main antagonist of Adventure Time. Given life by GOLB's breath, the Lich first manifested as a Catalyst Comet that wiped out the dinosaurs. Then, during the Mushroom War, came into existence from the Mushroom Bomb's nuclear waste. Seeking the extinction of all life across the multiverse, he was first defeated by Billy, before freeing himself and menacing Ooo once more.

Name: The Maid
Summary: The Maid is a weapon which Finn and Jake used to try and remove The Lich in the episode "Crossover." It represents itself as a helper, hinted by its name "The Maid." When it is fired, a female voice can be heard saying "Housekeeping."

Name: The Mean Six
Summary: The Mean Six are the main antagonists of the MLP: FiM episode of the same name. They are clones of the Mane Six created by Queen Chrysalis before they end up turning against her.

Name: The Storm King
Summary: The Storm King is the main antagonist of the My Little Pony Movie.

Name: Tonitrus Lucis Caelum
Summary: Tonitrus Lucis Caelum, more commonly known as The Fierce, is a past king of Lucis. He appears as a statue in Kingsglaive: Final Fantasy XV, and as a Lucii in Final Fantasy XV; he also appears as a boss in the Windows and Royal Editions.

Name: Tribe of the Ancients
Summary: The Tribe of Ancients or The Ancients are a group of powerful magicians from an advance civilization with an immense knowledge of different dimensions and the concepts in each of them. They created multiple worlds and the Pixls in order to build and cultivate said worlds. They also owned a book known as The Dark Prognosticus. Some time later, a group of individuals have separated themselves from the tribe with the Dark Prognosticus in their possession. This exiled tribe would be known as The Tribe of Darkness.

Name: Twilight Sparkle (Pony World)
Key: '''Unicorn Form''' | '''Alicorn Form''' | '''The Ending of the End Alicorn Form''' | '''Elements of Harmony/Magic of Friendship''' | '''All Alicorn Magic''' | '''Post-Timeskip Alicorn Form''' | '''Rainbow Power''' | '''Equestria Girls Human form'''
Summary: Twilight Sparkle is the main protagonist of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Twilight Sparkle (Sci-Twi)
Summary: Twilight Sparkle is one of the main protagonists in the My Little Pony: Equestria Girls series.

Name: Ultima, the High Seraph
Summary: nan

Name: Ultraman (Ultra Series)
Key: '''Showa Era''' | '''Heisei Era''' | '''Galaxy Crisis Era''' | '''New Generation Era (Before Crisis)''' | '''New Generation Era (After Crisis)''' | '''Reiwa Era'''
Summary: Mefilas: "What are you Ultraman? Are you an alien, or a human?" Ultraman: "I am both. I was born to fight those who break universal laws, like you"

Name: Vincent Valentine
Summary: nan

Name: Warrior of Light (Final Fantasy XIV)
Summary: The Warrior of Light, sometimes known as the Warrior of Darkness, Hydaelyn's Chosen, or the Hero of Eorzea, is a silent adventurer and the protagonist of the MMORPG Final Fantasy XIV. Though his gender, race, and appearance vary from player to player, he is represented in trailers and promotional materials as a male Midlander Hyur. As the chosen warrior of Hydaelyn, the Warrior uses his power to protect the realm of Eorzea from whatever threat would seek to destroy it.

Name: Zetton
Key: '''Ultraman (Generation I)''' | '''Return of Ultraman (Generation II)''' | '''Ultraman: The Ultimate Hero (Powered)''' | '''Ultraman Max''' | '''Ultraman Mebius''' | '''Ultraman Mebius Gaiden: Ghost Rebirth (EX)''' | '''Ultraman X''' | '''Ultraman Orb (Maga)''' | '''Ultraman Taiga''' | '''Ultra Galaxy Fight: The Absolute Conspiracy'''
Summary: Zetton, is a giant, horned, humanoid, beetle-like Kaiju that served as the final and strongest monster of the original Ultraman series.

Name: Zoffy
Key: '''Showa Era''' | '''Heisei Era''' | '''Galaxy Crisis Era''' | '''New Generation Era (Pre-Crisis)''' | '''New Generation Era (Post-Crisis)''' | '''Reiwa Era'''
Summary: Human, you've come this far under your own power. Before long, the time will come that you'll stand side by side with us, and soar across the gulf of the stars. Until then, we will be the shield for your world. I look forward to our next meeting

Name: Ansem, Seeker of Darkness
Summary: Ansem, Seeker of Darkness, sometimes referred to as Xehanort's Heartless, is the main antagonist of Kingdom Hearts and the "Reverse/Rebirth" scenario in Kingdom Hearts: Chain of Memories, as well as a supporting antagonist in Kingdom Hearts 3D: Dream Drop Distance. He is a member of the True Organization XIII and the Heartless of Terra-Xehanort, and as such his appearance and personality are primarily derived from Master Xehanort, and he retains his original form's "shadow".

Name: Antasma
Summary: Antasma (Japanese: アックーム, Akkumu) is one of the main antagonists in Mario & Luigi: Dream Team.

Name: Aqua (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Aqua is a Keyblade Wielder who trained under Master Eraqus alongside her friends Ventus and Terra. The only one among the trio to be named a Keyblade Master, she is entrusted by Eraqus to monitor both of her friends after they leave the Land of Departure, but finds herself torn between her duties and her feelings of friendship.

Name: Axel (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Originally known as Lea before losing his heart the day Radiant Garden fell into darkness, Axel is Organization XIII's eighth member who was assigned as Roxas' caretaker. But Axel's time with Roxas and Sora, whom he encountered while at Castle Oblivion, left an impression on him and became friends with Roxas at the cost of having a falling out with Saïx, the Nobody of his former self's friend Isa. When Roxas left the Organization, Axel followed suit after a failed attempt to save his friend from Diz's plan to integrate him into Sora. Eventually, after unknowingly giving the Organization a bargaining chip in Kairi, Axel sacrifices himself to enable Sora to save her. Axel's demise leads to his restoration into Lea who eventually gains his own Keyblade.

Name: Bowser
Summary: Bowser, sometimes known as King Koopa (Japanese: 大魔王クッパ, Daimaō Kuppa or "Great Demon King Koopa"), is the main antagonist of the Mario series and the King of the Koopas. He has repeatedly kidnapped or attempted to kidnap Princess Peach and take over the Mushroom Kingdom. He has also attempted to conquer other lands, such as the Mushroom World, Dinosaur Land, Sprixie Kingdom, and even the entire universe. Despite his villainous nature, he has occasionally helped the heroes of the Mushroom Kingdom against common threats and participates with them in their numerous sporting events in spin-off games.

Name: Cerberus (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Cerberus is a three-headed hellhound who guards the Underworld. He first appeared as Hades's loyal pet in Disney's Hercules, as guard dog to the Underworld. Cerberus serves as a boss in Kingdom Hearts, Kingdom Hearts II, and Kingdom Hearts coded and Re:coded.

Name: Cloud Strife (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Cloud is a character in the Kingdom Hearts series, originating from the Final Fantasy universe. He is the main character in Final Fantasy VII and a supporting character in the Kingdom Hearts series. Cloud is twenty-two years old at the beginning of Kingdom Hearts and Kingdom Hearts: Chain of Memories and twenty-three during the events of Kingdom Hearts II.

Name: Data-Sora
Summary: Data-Sora is the main protagonist of Kingdom Hearts coded and its remake, Kingdom Hearts Re:coded. He is a digital replica of Sora that King Mickey used to investigate the bugs in a computer simulation of Jiminy's Journal, and though he behaves much like the real Sora, he is thought to not be an actual person.

Name: Demyx
Summary: Demyx, the Melodious Nocturne (夜想のしらべ Yasō no Shirabe?, lit. Nocturnal Melody), is Rank IX within the original Organization XIII. He controls water, and uses his weapon, the sitar, as a musical instrument to make water fight for him in battle. He commands the Dancer Nobodies.

Name: Donald Duck (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Donald Duck is the Royal Magician of Disney Castle and one of King Mickey's most loyal attendants. He meets Sora not long after the Destiny Islands are swallowed by the Darkness, striking up a partnership with him in order to track down the King's whereabouts. While he is dismissive of the young Keyblade Wielder at first, Donald soon becomes one of Sora's closest friends and an essential ally on his journey.

Name: Dusk (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Dusk is the most common Nobody species, which is often used by Organization XIII for simple missions.

Name: Goofy (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Goofy is the Captain of the Royal Knights of King Mickey's court. He's an easy-going and somewhat slow-witted foil to his constant companion, Donald Duck, the Royal Magician. They meet Sora not long after the Destiny Islands are swallowed up by Darkness. With the young Keyblade Wielder as their only lead in their quest to discover the King's whereabouts, Goofy teams up with Sora and helps him along in his journey, becoming one of his closest friends in the process.

Name: Gummi Ship
Summary: The Gummi Ship is the main way to travel across the "Worlds". Being able to fit in a pocket after use and being charged with "laugh energy", they provide its wielders with a way of travel across the Realm of Light.

Name: Hades (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Hades is an antagonist from the Kingdom Hearts series, originally from the 1997 Disney animated feature Hercules. He is the Lord of the Dead and the ruler of the Underworld. Hot-headed literally and emotionally, he will stop at nothing to see the end of Hercules.

Name: Hector Barbossa (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Captain Hector Barbossa is a character in Kingdom Hearts II and Kingdom Hearts III. He first appeared in Disney's Pirates of the Caribbean: The Curse of the Black Pearl.

Name: Jack Sparrow (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Jack Sparrow is one of the most well-known pirates of the Caribbean world. Always getting into trouble, he accepts the help of Sora, Donald and Goofy on his adventures.

Name: Jafar (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Jafar is a recurring villain in the Kingdom Hearts series. Originating in Disney's Aladdin, he is a member of Maleficent's group, and appears to be her second-in-command. He is royal vizier of Agrabah who is disliked by many, mainly Aladdin and Jasmine. Two-faced and cunning, Jafar seeks the demise of Aladdin and to rule as sultan of Agrabah.

Name: Kairi (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Kairi is a longtime friend of both Sora and Riku and one of the Seven Princesses of Heart. She was raised by her grandmother in Radiant Garden but was sent to the Destiny Islands after Radiant Garden became shrouded in Darkness. As the Destiny Islands succumbed to the Darkness, her body vanished as she tried to meet up with Sora, leaving her heart behind in her friend, who set out on a journey to reunite with her and Riku.

Name: Kingdom Hearts (Entity)
Key: '''Kingdom Hearts of Worlds (KHI)''' | '''True Kingdom Hearts (KHBbS and KHIII)'''
Summary: Kingdom Hearts (キングダムハーツ Kingudamu Hātsu) is one of the major entities in the Kingdom Hearts universe. It is the heart of all worlds, and the source of ultimate power and wisdom. It can be seen as the heart of everything. Due to its great significance, it has repeatedly been sought by the villains of the Kingdom Hearts series, in particular the series's main antagonist, Xehanort.

Name: Kurt Zisa
Summary: Kurt Zisa is an Emblem that is found in the North American, PAL, and Kingdom Hearts Final Mix versions of Kingdom Hearts. It is one of the bosses in Agrabah.

Name: Larxene
Key: '''Up to Dream Drop Distance''' | '''Kingdom Hearts III'''
Summary: Larxene, the Savage Nymph (非情の妖姫 Hijō no Yōki?, lit. Callous Vixen), is Rank XII within Organization XIII. Larxene is the group's only female member, and also has a very sadistic nature. She controls lightning and uses it to thrash opponents with rapid attacks while also attacking them with her weapons: electrified throwing knives.

Name: Leon (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Squall Leonhart is a supporting character in the Kingdom Hearts series and leader of both the Heartless Resistance and the Hollow Bastion Restoration Committee. After the destruction of his world by the Heartless, he changed his name to "Leon" in an attempt to amend for his mistakes. Leon is twenty-five years old at the beginning of Kingdom Hearts and Kingdom Hearts: Chain of Memories and twenty-six during the events of Kingdom Hearts II. He is several years older than in Final Fantasy VIII to match the ages of the other Final Fantasy characters he appears alongside with. Along with Yuffie, Aerith and Cid, Leon came from Hollow Bastion and fled to Traverse Town when Maleficent took over the castle. Leon helps Sora with advice and information in the first game, and in Kingdom Hearts: Chain of Memories teaches the player many basic concepts for the card-based battle system. In the original game, a special gummi ship blueprint called Leon can be obtained by defeating 4000 Heartless and talking to Geppetto.

Name: Lexaeus
Summary: Lexaeus, the is the Nobody of Aeleus and is Rank V within the original Organization XIII. True to his title as the "Silent Hero", Lexaeus is a taciturn and somewhat aloof individual but is nevertheless honorable and loyal to the few he considers his allies. Lexaeus holds a particularly close friendship with Zexion, being the one person his is willing to confide in and is suspicious of the other members of the Organization.

Name: Luigi
Summary: Luigi is Mario's younger, taller, and thinner twin brother. He is a major protagonist of the Mario series. Luigi has helped and fought alongside his brother on many occasions.

Name: Luxord
Summary: Luxord, the Gambler of Fate (運命を賭す者 Unmei o Tosumono?), is Rank X within the original Organization XIII. He possesses the power of time manipulation and uses his ability to force his opponents to play timed games, with unfortunate consequences if they cannot learn the rules and lose. He commands the Gambler Nobodies.

Name: Maleficent (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Aqua: Try all you want but you'll never defeat a heart filled with light. Maleficent: Perhaps. But remember one thing—as long as there is light, there will be darkness. And in time, many more will be drawn to it. Then they will all belong to me!

Name: Marluxia
Summary: Marluxia, the Graceful Assassin (優雅なる凶刃 Yūga-naru Kyōjin, lit.Graceful Assassin's Blade), is Rank XI within Organization XIII, the lord of Castle Oblivion and the main antagonist of Sora's story in Kingdom Hearts: Chain of Memories. He controls flowers, and uses his control to command beams of destructive energy from flower-themed minions, bombard the opponent with flurries of petals, and to attack opponents with his massive scythe.

Name: Merlin (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Merlin is a recurring character in the Kingdom Hearts series. He is a wizard who teaches Sora in the arts of magic when the boy appears in Traverse Town.

Name: Messiah (Persona)
Summary: Messiah is the ultimate Persona of Persona 3's protagonist, Makoto Yuki, created by fusing his initial Persona Orpheus, and Thanatos together.

Name: Phantom (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: The Phantom is an Emblem Heartless that is found in the first Kingdom Hearts Game. It is one of the bosses at Neverland. While Phantom is in possession of the Clock Tower, the hourly treasures cannot be obtained.

Name: Riku
Summary: Riku is Sora's rival and best friend, as well as deuteragonist of Kingdom Hearts. A cool-headed and confident youth, he nevertheless is determined to leave the Destiny Islands and see the worlds outside of them. However, on the day he vowed to leave with Sora and Kairi, a freak storm hit that engulfed his world in darkness. Separated from his friends, Maleficent discovers his potential power and manipulates him into believing that Sora had forgotten and replaced him, stoking the inner darkness within Riku and turning him into an unwitting pawn despite his suspicions. Riku is later able to break free of the evil fairy's influence and decides to atone for his mistakes by sealing off the door to Kingdom Hearts along with King Mickey. His story did not end there, as he soon finds himself in Castle Oblivion's basement, having been guided there by Sora's heart. He takes this opportunity to continue assisting Sora from the shadows, but struggles with the darkness in his heart in spite of his attempts to embrace the light.

Name: Riku Replica
Summary: Riku Replica is a clone of Riku made by Vexen using his combat data. Having believed to be the true Riku, the truth has changed him, eventually just focusing on protecting Naminé.

Name: Roxas
Summary: Roxas is Sora's Nobody and the thirteenth member of Organization XIII, being titled "The Key of Destiny". Despite being Sora's Nobody, Roxas' appearance is heavily influenced by Ventus, whose heart had taken refuge in Sora's body to heal at the time of the Nobody's creation. Although kind and cheerful to his friends Axel and Xion, Roxas is prone to anger and recklessness, particularly in the face of deceit or when his individuality is questioned. Despite his best efforts to assert himself as his own person, he is ultimately coerced to merge with his original once more to revive him.

Name: Saïx
Summary: Originally known as Isa, Saïx is the seventh member of Organization XIII and one of Xemnas' closest allies. Known as the "Luna Diviner", he is a cold, calculating, and manipulative Nobody who directs most of the Organization's day-to-day activities. But this facade of calm peels away once he enters battle, becoming a raging berserker who will not stop until his foe has been lost to the Darkness.

Name: Sora (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Sora is a cheerful, young boy hailing from the Destiny Islands and the main protagonist of the Kingdom Hearts series. Longing to see the worlds outside of his own, he and his friends Riku and Kairi pledged to build a raft and set out together. However, on their planned day of departure, a freak storm hit their home and their world was subsequently engulfed by the Darkness. It was at this time that Sora unlocked his ability to wield a Keyblade, a weapon of legend that is said to bring salvation or destruction but is thrown into a Corridor of Darkness despite his efforts to combat the shadows that were swarming his home. Awakening in Traverse Town, he soon sets out with Goofy and Donald Duck, attendants to King Mickey, to discover the mystery behind the darkness and reunite with his friends.

Name: Terra (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Terra is a Keyblade Wielder training under Eraqus in the Land of Departure. He aspires to be a Keyblade Master, but Eraqus refuses to give Terra the title of Master after noticing the Darkness in Terra's heart during his Mark of Mastery Exam. But after learning that the Seven Princesses of Heart were in danger of being attacked by the Unversed, Terra sets off on a quest to save them in order to protect the worlds and prove himself worthy of becoming a Keyblade Master.

Name: Vanitas (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Vanitas is a Keyblade Wielder and Master Xehanort's mysterious new apprentice. He takes an unusual interest in Ventus (Kingdom Hearts) after their first meeting, mocking the young Keyblade Wielder and challenging him to go beyond the ken of the Land of Departure. His goals bring him into conflict with both Aqua and Terra, clashing with all three Keyblade Wielders throughout their travels.

Name: Ventus (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Ventus is a rookie Keyblade wielder who trains alongside Terra and Aqua at the Land of Departure. He runs away from home to chase after Terra after receiving a warning of things to come. Despite not being as along in his training as they are, he's still a capable warrior and is eager to explore new worlds and make friends. He has some connection to Master Xehanort and his new apprentice Vanitas, but he cannot remember how or why.

Name: Vexen
Summary: Vexen, the Chilly Academic (いてつく学究 Itetsuku Gakkyū?, lit. Freezing Scholar), is the Nobody of Even and is Rank IV within Organization XIII. He controls ice and uses it to command storms and blizzards, freezing his opponents solid, while defending himself with his massive shield.

Name: Xemnas
Summary: Xemnas, the Superior of the In-Between (狭間の指導者 Hazama no Shidōsha), is the Nobody of Terra-Xehanort. He is the leader of the original Organization XIII, the former ruler of The World That Never Was, and a member of the True Organization XIII. He serves as the main antagonist of Kingdom Hearts II and as a supporting antagonist in Kingdom Hearts 358/2 Days and Kingdom Hearts 3D: Dream Drop Distance.

Name: Xion
Summary: Xion is the fourteenth member of Organization XIII, first appearing in the game Kingdom Hearts 358/2 Days, in which she could be viewed as both a main protagonist and antagonist. She is not a normal Nobody and is only a nominal member of the Organization. Because of this, she does not have a throne in Where Nothing Gathers, nor does she have a title or a breed of Nobody to control. Instead, she is an imperfect Replica of Sora created from his leaked memories as a fail-safe in case both Sora and Roxas proved to be useless to Organization XIII's plans. While this enables her to use the Keyblade, Xion's existence also halts Sora's progression of regaining his memories to fully awaken while in his pod, something which Naminé, DiZ, and Riku recognize.

Name: Young Xehanort
Summary: Young Xehanort, referred to as the Unknown and the Mysterious Figure in the North American, PAL, and Final Mix versions of Kingdom Hearts Birth by Sleep, is a boss in Kingdom Hearts Birth by Sleep and one of the main antagonists in Kingdom Hearts 3D: Dream Drop Distance as well as Kingdom Hearts III.

Name: Zeekeeper
Summary: The Zeekeeper is the guardian figure of the Pi'illo Kingdom, who helped them take down Antasma many thousands of years before the events of the game.

Name: Zexion
Summary: Zexion, the Cloaked Schemer (影歩む策士 Kageayumu Sakushi, lit. Shadow-Walking Schemer), is the Nobody of Ienzo and is Rank VI in Organization XIII and an antagonist in Riku's storyline in Kingdom Hearts: Chain of Memories. He weaves illusions to fight for him. Unlike the other Organization members, Zexion's weapon was originally unknown, and his talents were used only outside of normal combat. In Kingdom Hearts Re:Chain of Memories, Zexion's weapon was revealed to be a book called a Lexicon.

Name: A.D.A.M.
Summary: A.D.A.M: If you insist.

Name: Alice Margatroid
Summary: Alice Margatroid is one of only a few people known to live within the Forest of Magic. She's a magician known primarily for her skillful use of dolls as well as being a loner. She gets in many fights with Marisa, but they are somewhat acquaintances, sharing many of the same interests and even teaming up at times.

Name: Amaterasu Oomikami (Touhou Project)
Summary: Amaterasu Oomikami is a goddess in the Touhou Project universe. She is the sister of Lord Tsukuyomi, the leader, and ruler of the Lunar Capital.

Name: Amy Rose (Archie Pre-Genesis Wave)
Summary: One-Two-Three-Four! Open the jailhouse door! -- I still believe in you, Sonic!

Name: Android 17
Summary: nan

Name: Android 18
Summary: nan

Name: Antoine D'Coolette (Archie Pre-Genesis Wave)
Summary: Antoine D'Coolette is one of the main protagonist/side characters in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: Auta Magetta (Anime)
Summary: Auta Magetta (マゲッタ, Magetta) is a Metalman from Universe 6, a race that is said to exist as well in Universe 7. He is a member of Champa's team.

Name: Aya Shameimaru
Summary: Aya Shameimaru (射命丸 文) is Gensokyo's resident reporter, known for writing "slightly" exaggerated news articles about anything that happens. She's also a Tengu that prided herself on being the "Fastest" in Gensokyo (in terms of pure speed, anyway), and is overall a really strong character, able to occasionally win without trying to.

Name: Barry Kahn
Summary: Barry Kahn is an A-list actor from Dragon Ball set to play the Great Saiyaman in the film "Great Saiyaman vs Mister Satan." After Barry was rejected by Videl, he became increasingly jealous of Gohan and attempted to ruin his marriage, though without any success.

Name: Bean the Dynamite (Archie Pre-Genesis Wave)
Summary: Bean the Dynamite is a mercenary in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: Blade Knight
Summary: Blade Knight is a character portrayed as a swordsman and knight featured in the Kirby series. He's a regular enemy across stages, which Kirby can turn into a Helper ally in some games. Blade Knight gives Kirby the Sword Copy Ability when swallowed, function he shared with Sword Knight in classic titles. Star Allies implies he wants to conquer the world.

Name: Blaze the Cat (Archie Comics)
Summary: Blaze the Cat is a princess and guardian of the Sol Emeralds in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: Borareta (Anime)
Summary: Borareta is a fighter from Universe 3, in the Tournament of Power.

Name: Broom Hatter
Summary: Broom Hatter is a character in the Kirby series that gives Kirby the Clean ability when swallowed.

Name: Bunnie D'Coolette (Archie Pre-Genesis Wave)
Summary: Bunnie D'Coolette is one of the main heroes in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: Byakuren Hijiri
Summary: Byakuren Hijiri (聖 白蓮, Hijiri Byakuren) is a Buddhist nun and magician, sealed away by humans for the kindness she showed Youkai, before being released from her seal during the events of Undefined Fantastic Object. Originally a human, Byakuren turned to magic to escape old age after the death of her brother, and became a Youkai. Realizing that her prosperity and power relied on the human fear and belief of Youkai, Byakuren worked to protect other Youkai while making herself out to be a great Youkai hunter. However, she eventually grew to genuinely care for the Youkai she protected. When the humans who had flocked behind her realized this, they punished her by sealing her deep within Makai; however, her followers would, thousands of years later, free her.

Name: Casserale (Anime)
Summary: Casserale (カーセラル Kāseraru) is a cyborg warrior and general of the Pride Troopers in Universe 11 who participates in the Tournament of Power. He is also the pilot of the Pride Troopers Spaceship.

Name: Catopesra (Anime)
Summary: Catopesra is a character in Dragon Ball Super, a contestant from Universe 3 fighting in the Tournament of Power.

Name: Chang'e (Touhou Project)
Summary: Chang'e is a background character in the Touhou Project series. Although she didn't make any proper appearance, she has been mentioned numerous times, notably in Legacy of Lunatic Kingdom.

Name: Chaos (Archie Pre-Genesis Wave)
Summary: Chaos is an antagonist that appears in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: Chaos Emeralds (Archie Comics)
Summary: Through Time and Space and alternate dimensions... properties exist beyond comprehension... Artifacts of ancient and unfathomable power... Exist to aid and make men cower... Cognizant by beings of science and mystic shaman... A sovereign royal and an emerald have nothing in common!

Name: Charmy Bee (Archie Pre-Genesis Wave)
Summary: Dr. Eggman: Charmy Bee! Haven't I already ruined your life? Destroyed your kingdom or some such--right? Charmy Bee: Yes. You have. Despite all that, I've fought for our world. No matter what you do to me, I will still fight for Mobius. AND I'M NOT ALONE!

Name: Chiyuri Kitashirakawa
Summary: Chiyuri Kitashirakawa (北白河 ちゆり Kitashirakawa Chiyuri) is Yumemi's assistant. Although she looks immature, she is 15, having left graduate school and working as an assistant at a university. Her specialty is comparative physics.

Name: Claycia
Summary: Claycia and Elline are an inseparable team when creating Seventopia; Claycia is a master craftsman and Elline paints everything she sculpts. One day, Claycia turns evil and leaves her best friend behind. The now evil sculptor opens a hole in the skies of Dream Land and steals Planet Popstar's colors. Elline exits the hole in an attempt to escape two of Claycia's Grab Hands. As they close in on her, she repaints Kirby and Bandana Waddle Dee, who then save her from the enemies. After some explanation, Elline leads the two into the realm of Seventopia to stop Claycia and restore Planet Popstar's colors.

Name: Clownpiece
Summary: Clownpiece is a Fairy from Hell who took part in the Lunar Conflict during the events of "Touhou 15: Legacy of Lunatic Kingdom". Originally a subordinate of the Goddess of Hell Hecatia Lapislazuli, she became part of Junko's plan to invade the Lunar Capital after Junko and Hecatia made an alliance seeking to take down the Lunar Goddess Chang'e.

Name: Copy-Vegeta
Summary: Copy-Vegeta is a result of the liquefied weapon Commenson absorbing the Saiyan Prince's powers. Not only does he steal his powers, but Copy Vegeta also emulates Vegeta's spirit, personality, memories and fighting techniques. Along with causing him to gradually vanish unless he is stopped. When Gotenks fails miserably against him, Vegeta's longtime rival Son Goku steps into having yet another (sort of) fight against him.

Name: D-Void
Summary: The D-Void is a mysterious dark entity that resides within the shadows of the Dead Universe and is the personification of it. A mass of eyes and black tentacles, this creature seeks to devour the life of entire worlds in order to satiate its hunger, but is unable to leave the Dead Universe without outside help. It is described as an unbelievably powerful being with the capacity to return the spark to a deceased Transformer, control the minds of robotic beings and drain energy from Cybertronians to feed on them.

Name: Dercori (Anime)
Summary: Dercori (ダーコリ Dākori) is a warrior from Universe 4 and a member of Team Universe 4 in the Tournament of Power in Dragon Ball Super. She is a female humanoid with light violet skin, mint-green hair, folded skins on her shoulders, exceptionally large hands and feet, and fins. She is a skilled fighter who uses mystical talismans in battle.

Name: Doremy Sweet
Summary: Doremy Sweet is a Baku who resides in the Dream World and is its ruler.

Name: Dr. Drakken
Summary: Drew Theodore P. Lipsky was an inventor, even from a young age, being able to develop fantastical yet strange devices by the time he hit the fourth grade, using them to get an edge in sports. After a humiliation in university involving him creating the first Bebe Robot prototypes, he dropped out of school and decided to pursue his true calling in life: crime. At some point, his skin turned blue for unknown reasons, and since then, he has become one of Kim Possible's most prominent enemies under the name Dr. Drakken.

Name: Dr. Finitevus
Summary: Dr. Finitevus is a major antagonist in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: Dr. Ivo Robotnik (Archie Pre-Genesis Wave)
Summary: Dr. Ivo Robotnik, formerly known as Julian Kintobor, is the big bad of the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: Dragon God (Touhou Project)
Summary: The Dragon (龍, Ryū), also called Dragon God (龍神, Ryūjin) is, according to Perfect Memento in Strict Sense, the highest god of Gensokyo. All living things, whether human or youkai, worship the dragon god. The dragon lives in sea or sky or rain, and regardless of the Great Hakurei Border, the Dragon can move freely through heaven, hell, netherworld, and the outside world. Its voice divides the sky and causes thunderstorms. When it winds its body it causes mountains to crumble and earthquakes to occur. While destroying at the same time being the creator of Gensokyo, and the rain, the rivers, abundant greens are all due to the dragon's help.

Name: Dyspo (Anime)
Summary: Dyspo is a pride trooper from Universe 11 renowned for his speed.

Name: E-123 Omega (Archie Pre-Genesis)
Summary: E-123 "Omega" is a character that appears in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: E.V.E.
Summary: Your theory is sound, small blue creature, now that i can use my ability for idepended though and do not serve Robotnik... I have the freedom of choice... not limited by boundaries be they of my mind or the vast reaches of infinity. Farewell, Sonic the Hedgehog, and thank you! Because of you, i now know what it means to be free and just as importantly - to be Me!

Name: Egg Beater
Summary: The Egg Beater is the 2nd Battle Suit/Mech created by Dr. Eggman and the first one to go up against Sonic in his base.

Name: Eight Million Gods
Summary: The Eight Million Gods, also known as the Yaoyorozu no Kami, are the gods of the Touhou Project world. They always existed in the world, even before the world became the organized whole we know today. They first gave a "name" to everything, defining each object's boundary and place in the world.

Name: Eiki Shiki, Yamaxanadu
Summary: Eiki Shiki, Yamaxanadu (四季映姫・ヤマザナドゥ) is one of the Yama who judge the dead and decide whether they go to Heaven, Hell, the Netherworld, or get reincarnated. She currently resides in Hell. Whether it's because she simply has a habit of lecturing or because she genuinely wants others to change for the better, she's become well known in Gensokyo for lecturing anyone and everyone about their faults.

Name: Eirin Yagokoro
