Summary: Eirin Yagokoro (八意 永琳, Yagokoro Eirin) is a medical genius from the Moon, able to create even the Hourai Elixir with the help of Kaguya's power, the manipulation of eternity. She is living in exile in Gensokyo after choosing to stay with and devote herself to Kaguya Houraisan on Earth rather than take her back to the Moon. She was a very well-known figure on the Moon, having not only been instrumental in the founding of Lunar society with Lord Tsukuyomi, but also being its leading medical mind and the person in charge of the Moon's emissaries to the Earth.

Name: Elias Acorn
Summary: Elias Acorn is the prince/king of the Kingdom of Acorn in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: Elis
Summary: Elis is a mysterious demon found in Makai. Nothing is known about her, except the fact that she attacks Reimu.

Name: Ellen (Touhou Project)
Summary: Ellen (エレン Eren) is an eternally young witch who stars in the 3rd Touhou game, Phantasmagoria of Dim. Dream. She does not have a good memory, often forgetting, and because of this, she is always a child.

Name: Elly
Summary: Elly is the third stage boss of Lotus Land Story, and who also serves as the gatekeeper of Mugenkan, a mansion where Yuuka resides in the PC-98 era.

Name: Enerjak
Summary: Such a show. Violence. Drama. You haven't been this much fun in years! -- Oh, don't spoil this for the boy, dear. I'm something to be experienced

Name: Espio the Chameleon (Archie Pre-Genesis Wave)
Summary: Espio the Chameleon is a character that appears in the Archie Sonic Comics and its spin-offs.

Name: Evil Dragon (Touhou Project)
Summary: The Evil Dragon was a dragon that was sealed long ago into the local Inari Shrine. It recently tricked Marisa into unsealing it.

Name: Flandre Scarlet
Summary: Flandre Scarlet (フランドール・スカーレット) is the younger sister of Remilia Scarlet and a vampire who has lived at the Scarlet Devil Mansion for over 495 years.

Name: Frieza (DBS Manga)
Summary: Frieza (フリーザ, Furīza?) is the leader of the Planet Trade Organization and the son of King Cold, who once ruled over the majority of the Seventh Universe for decades. Thanks to his mutant and hybrid status, Frieza was born with an abnormally high power level and never needed to train a day in his life to access his phenomenal power. But Frieza grew fearful of the legendary Super Saiyan folktale, slaughtering nearly the entirety of the Saiyan race by destroying the Saiyans' Planet Vegeta. The Saiyan genocide served as the catalyst for nearly every event since "Dragon Ball", ultimately resulting in a showdown with Goku on Namek that ended with Frieza leading himself to his own downfall by triggering the Super Saiyan transformation he feared so much.

Name: Fujiwara no Mokou
Summary: Fujiwara no Mokou (藤原 妹紅) was formerly an ordinary human, but she became an immortal being after drinking the Hourai Elixir about 1300 years ago. Now she is never able to die, though she still feels the pain of injuries as normal. She's considered to be very powerful, given her long life, the power she earned through her life, and her immortal status since she can keep fighting until she can no longer stand the pain.

Name: Fusion Zamasu (Manga)
Summary: Fusion Zamasu (合体がったい ザマス, Gattai Zamasu?) is a fusion born of the union between Goku Black (Present Zamasu in Goku's body) and Future Zamasu through the Potara earrings.

Name: Gamma 1 (Anime)
Summary: Gamma 1 is the first of 2 androids created by Dr. Hedo after his team-up with Magenta to rebuild the Red Ribbon Army. After Piccolo Fought Gamma 2 and manipulated the situation to get Gohan back into fighting shape, Piccolo revealed himself a second time during the latter's assault. The two Gammas started to fight Gohan and Piccolos After the two androids battled Gohan and Piccolo for a long enough time, Piccolo's convincing and the robots sensing no evil intent finally caused them to join forces with the heroes instead of fighting them.

Name: Gamma 2 (Anime)
Summary: Gamma 2 is the second of 2 androids created by Dr. Hedo after his team-up with Magenta to rebuild the Red Ribbon Army. For his first mission, he was sent to fight "the evil King Piccolo" to test his power. After arrogantly thinking he won, Piccolo tailed him back to the new Red Ribbon Army base, where he learned of the organization's plans. After Piccolo manipulated the situation to get Gohan back into fighting shape, the Namekian revealed himself a second time during the latter's assault and the two fought once again.

Name: Gas (Dragon Ball)
Summary: Gas (ガス, Gasu?) is part of the Heeter family, being a prodigy in terms of fighting strength, he acted as their muscle. He serves as one of the true main antagonists of the Granolah the Survivor Saga.

Name: Gengetsu
Summary: Gengetsu (幻月) is the second Extra Stage boss of Lotus Land Story and an inhabitant of the mysterious dream world that was said to be her younger sister's, Mugetsu.

Name: Gensokyo
Key: '''Average Humans''' | '''Fairies''' | '''Average Youkai''' | '''Stronger Individuals''' | '''Dragon God & Eirin Yagakoro'''
Summary: Gensokyo is a land hidden somewhere in Japan. Formerly mere an isolated region of the country infested by Youkai, it has now since been separated from the "Outside World" and now exists as one of the last places where Youkai and fantasy can thrive.

Name: Geoffrey St. John
Summary: Geoffrey St. John is a side character in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: Gilgamesh (Final Fantasy)
Key: '''Final Fantasy V Through XII''' | '''Dissidia Final Fantasy and Final Fantasy XIII''' | '''Final Fantasy XIV (Pre-Stormblood)''' | '''Final Fantasy XIV (Stormblood)'''
Summary: Gilgamesh is a recurring character throughout the entirety of the Final Fantasy series. First appearing as a vassal to the evil warlock, Exdeath, Gilgamesh is comically inept at his duties despite his skill as a warrior, being obsessed with obtaining the legendary Excalibur to add to his collection of weapons. Unbeknownst to him, many of these weapons are forgeries, and he's almost always seen with Excalipoor, a pale imitation of Excalibur that can only inflict shallow wounds, mistaking the false sword for the blade he seeks. After his second defeat at the hands of the Warrior of Light, Gilgamesh was sent tumbling through the Interdimensional Void, reappearing at many points throughout the franchise's history as an ally to be summoned or an optional foe to test the party's might for great rewards.

Name: Goku Black (Manga)
Summary: Zamasu (ザマス?) was once the Supreme Kai apprentice under Gowasu of Universe 10, who developed a loathing for mortals as he witnessed their actions across the universe, leading him to embark on a crusade against mortals after stealing the body of Son Goku using the Super Dragon Balls, gaining the title of Goku Black (悟ご空くうブラック, Gokū Burakku?), or, as he is more commonly referred, simply Black.|

Name: Goliath Doll
Summary: The Goliath Doll is a giant doll used in Alice's last spellcard during the events of Cirno's story mode in Touhou Hisoutensoku. It seems it's the most powerful doll in Alice's possession.

Name: Gotenks
Key: '''Pre-Room of Spirit and Time Training''' | '''Post-Room of Spirit and Time Training''' | '''Super Saiyan 3''' | '''Super Hero Arc'''
Summary: nan

Name: Grand Priest (Manga)
Summary: Goku: He may not look like it but he seems pretty strong to me. Whis: Very perceptive. So far as I know the great Grand Priest is the strongest person in this world. Goku: R-REALLY?! Whis: Shhhh! Still, you must not ask to fight him or anything like that. Goku: B-but now I'm curious...

Name: Granolah
Summary: Granolah is a bounty hunter who is the last survivor of the Cerealian race, seeking revenge against Frieza for their destruction at the Saiyan Army's hands.

Name: Hasshaku-sama (Touhou Project)
Summary: Hasshaku-sama is an Urban Legend originating from the internet. She is a ghost haunting a small village and cursing individuals every 10 years or so to a certain death.

Name: Hata no Kokoro
Summary: Hata no Kokoro (秦 こころ) is a menreiki youkai. As she relies on her masks to show her emotions to others, her facial expressions are emotionless and can be likened to a poker face.

Name: Hatate Himekaidou
Summary: Hatate Himekaidou (姫海棠 はたて) is a tengu reporter who produces Kakashi Spirit News. Unlike her rival, Aya Shameimaru, she virtually never goes outside to gather news and photographs, instead using her special ability of Thoughtography.

Name: Heavy and Bomb (Archie Pre-Genesis)
Summary: Rotor: I want Eggman to fight for every inch he gains in my city. Besides, you were with the Chaotix. Where's that take-all-challangers attitude?

Name: Hecatia Lapislazuli
Summary: Hecatia Lapislazuli (ヘカーティア・ラピスラズリ) is a mysterious Goddess of Hell who governs the Hells of the moon, the Earth, and Otherworlds. She has a separate body in each of the three worlds and can act independently with each of them. Once, she was the main leader of the Ministry of Right and Wrong, but due to unknown reasons, deserted of the organization, living now as an outlaw, controlling the Hells from the shadows.

Name: Houyi (Touhou Project)
Summary: Houyi is a god from Chinese Mythology. In Touhou, he is responsible for shooting down multiple suns, including one in Hell. Due to this action killing Junko's son, he was later murdered by her.

Name: Iblis (Archie Comics)
Summary: Iblis is a character mentioned in the Sonic the Hedgehog Encyclopedia published by Archie Comics.

Name: Ichirin Kumoi
Summary: Ichirin Kumoi (雲居 一輪) and her guardian Unzan (雲山) are two youkai that follow and support Byakuren Hijiri. Ichirin was formerly a human, but eventually became a youkai due to being hated and rejected by humanity.

Name: Iron King
Summary: The Iron King (real name Jun Kun) is an antagonist in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: Iwanagahime
Summary: Iwanagahime was a goddess from Mt. Fuji. She used to live with her sister, Konohana-Sakuyahime, until the latter partially destroyed a mountain out of spite. This caused Iwanagahime to move to what will eventually become the Youkai Mountain.

Name: Ixis Naugus (Archie Pre-Genesis Wave)
Summary: Ixis Naugus is a major antagonist in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics. He is one of the last surviving members of the Order of Ixis, born from the fusion of three other wizards: Agunus, Nusgau, and Suguna, who fused into one being after they all entered the Sun to attain the element of fire.[1] During his time as the Kingdom of Acorn's Royal Wizard, he helped instigate events that led to the Great War, and then fled to the Zone of Silence as a safe haven where he was trapped for many years until he managed to escape after the First Robotnik War.

Name: Jet the Hawk (Archie Comics)
Summary: Jet the Hawk is a Mobian hawk and expert Extreme Gear rider who deserted from the Battle Bird Armada and became the leader of the Babylon Rogues. Jet believed it was his destiny to find Babylon Garden and take the glory that would come with it, and seeks to do this in order to get back at the Armada as well. He worked temporarily for Dr. Eggman in order to escape his wrath by promising to defeat Sonic the Hedgehog, only for him and his team to be beaten by the hedgehog, Miles "Tails" Prower, and Knuckles the Echidna in a race. After this loss, he would return to his previous quest, and end up running into enemies like Team Dark, Team Rose, Team Hooligan, and his former allies in the Battle Bird Armada. After discovering the garden at last, Jet set out on a new quest: to become the fastest being on Mobius.

Name: Jimizu (Anime)
Summary: Jimizu is a Yardrat from Universe 2 and a member of Team Universe 2 for the Tournament of Power. Jimizu is pretty arrogant because of his instant transmission, knowing he can do it quick enough that it is hard for him to be attacked. He, like his other teammates, hold the Kamikaze Fireballs in high esteem as seen when they rushed to their side after hearing Brianne call the attention of the other warriors, and he partook in the choir of proclaiming the song of love and victory. He also seemed enamored by the Kamikaze Fireballs after they transformed.

Name: Jiren (Manga)
Summary: Jiren is a member of the Pride Troopers who participated in the Tournament of Power under the banner of Team Universe 11 to obtain the wish of reviving his master Gicchin from the Super Dragon Balls.

Name: Joon Yorigami
Summary: Joon Yorigami is Shion's younger twin sister and a goddess of pestilence. While she inevitably leads those around her to financial ruin, she is better liked than her sister and is much more driven. Using her abilities and her skill in conning others, she gets them to use up all their money for her before abandoning them once they're completely drained of fortune and money.

Name: Josef (Final Fantasy II)
Summary: Josef is a playable character in Final Fantasy II and one of the primary protagonists of Soul of Rebirth. He was once a soldier of Palamecia, before he escaped and moved to the snowy town of Salamand. He becomes and ally to the party when the rescue to slaves from Semitt Falls. He also helps the party retrieve the Goddess Bell in Snow Cave, but loses his life to a boulder plotted by General Borghen. He then joins the afterlife where he meets Minwu and Scott; joining forces with them in the process.

Name: Julie-Su
Summary: Julie-Su is an ex-dark legionnaire and Chaotix member in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: Junko (Touhou Project)
Summary: Junko (純狐) is the sworn enemy of the Lunarians, dedicating herself to their destruction following the death of her son at the hands of Chang'e's husband. Ultimately, she used her own power to purify anything to purify herself, turning herself into the embodiment of her own hate, a Divine Spirit formed from her own emotions and willpower.

Name: Kaguya Houraisan
Summary: Kaguya Houraisan (蓬莱山 輝夜, Houraisan Kaguya) is the former princess of the Moon, banished to Earth for consuming the Hourai Elixir to become immortal. There, she dwelt among the humans and eventually grew to love her new home. Her beauty attracted many suitors, but she refused to marry any of them if they failed to accomplish one of her Five Impossible Requests. Eventually, when the Lunarians forgave her and attempted to retrieve her, she rejected Lunarian society in favor of Earth and escaped with Eirin Yagokoro to the hidden mansion of Eientei.

Name: Kana Anaberal
Summary: Kana Anaberal (カナ・アナベラル Kana anaberaru) is a poltergeist created by a mentally unstable girl, and haunts a huge mansion. Because its owner no longer fears her from growing used to it, she thinks of moving, wondering what all the fuss is about. She is a playable character in Phantasmagoria of Dim. Dream.

Name: Kanako Yasaka
Summary: Kanako Yasaka (八坂 神奈子) is the current goddess of the Moriya Shrine, following her victory over Suwako during the Great Suwa War, thousands of years in the past. Due to her dependence on faith, which was scarce in the Outside World, she moved her shrine to Gensokyo so she could collect it more easily.

Name: Kasen Ibaraki
Summary: Kasen Ibaraki (茨木 華扇, Ibaraki Kasen) is a mysterious self-proclaimed hermit living in the mountains. She can often be seen dispensing advice and knowledge to Reimu Hakurei, Marisa Kirisame, and Sanae Kochiya.

Name: Keiki Haniyasushin
Summary: Keiki Haniyasushin (埴安神 袿姫 Haniyasushin Keiki) is a god summoned by human spirits and acts as the main antagonist of Wily Beast and Weakest Creature.

Name: Keine Kamishirasawa
Summary: Keine Kamishirasawa (上白沢 慧音, Kamishirasawa Keine) is a were-hakutaku who acts as the guardian of the Human Village.

Name: Kettol (Anime)
Summary: Kettol (ケットル Kettoru) is a member of the Pride Troopers who participates in the Tournament of Power.

Name: Kikuri
Summary: Kikuri is a mysterious enemy that faces Reimu Hakurei.

Name: Kirby
Summary: First you draw a circle, Then you dot the eyes. Add a great big smile And presto, it's Kirby!

Name: Knuckles the Echidna (Archie Pre-Genesis Wave)
Summary: Knuckles is one of the primary protagonists who stands as the last guardian of Angel Island and leader of the Chaotix in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: Koichiarator (Anime)
Summary: Koichiarator is a triple fusion of the Universe 3 robots Koitsukai, Panchia, and Bollarator.

Name: Koishi Komeiji
Summary: Koishi Komeiji (古明地 こいし) is Satori Komeiji's younger sister. To escape the fear and hatred which other beings feel towards the satori species, she attempted to destroy her mind-reading ability by closing her Third Eye. However, this had the side effect of sealing away her own conscious mind, causing her to lose all thoughts and motives; she could no longer be hated, but neither could she be loved, or even remembered by people who saw her.

Name: Koitsukai (Anime)
Summary: Koitsukai is a warrior from Universe 3 and a member of Team Universe 3.

Name: Komachi Onozuka
Summary: Komachi Onozuka (小野塚 小町) is a lazy shinigami who ferries souls across the Sanzu River and works for Eiki Shiki, Yamaxanadu. While she is a slacker and a slow worker, she tends to copy her boss' habit of lecturing others and has little else to talk about besides suicide and other death-related horrors.

Name: Konngara
Summary: Konngara is one of the Final Bosses of Highly Responsive to Prayers. It is found in the Hell route and is likely the one behind the shrine's destruction.

Name: Konohana-Sakuyahime
Summary: Konohana-Sakuyahime is the Goddess of Volcanoes in Gensokyo. She resides on Mt. Fuji. Years ago, a group of humans came to her mountain to drop a jar into the volcano. Unfortunately, the jar contained the Hourai Elixir, which would trigger the volcano's eruption hard enough that not even Sakuyahime could stop it. As such, she convinced the humans to not drop it in the volcano. As a precaution, she also murdered most of them in their sleep. The two survivors had to carry away the Elixir, although one of them killed the other and took the Elixir for themselves. Said person will go on to become Fujiwara no Mokou.

Name: Kosuzu Motoori
Summary: Kosuzu Motoori (本居 小鈴, Motoori Kosuzu) is the main character of the print work Forbidden Scrollery. She lives in the Human Village and serves as a worker of the Suzunaan book renter.

Name: Kotohime
Summary: Kotohime (小兎姫) is a character who appears in Phantasmagoria of Dim. Dream. While she should be a princess, she has an odd personality that doesn't allow her to meet people often. She finds an interest in collecting things that normal people aren't interested in.

Name: Kraken (Final Fantasy I)
Summary: Kraken is the fiend of water. He is the squid like beast that appears in the Sunken Shrine. The Warriors of Light must defeat him to awaken the Water Crystal.

Name: Krillin (DBS Anime)
Summary: Krillin or Kuririn (クリリン, Kuririn?) is a former monk of the Orin Temple who ran away to train under Master Roshi, eventually doing so alongside Son Goku, who would grow to become his best friend.

Name: Kurumi (Touhou Project)
Summary: Kurumi is a vampire and gatekeeper found at the entrance to the Lake of Blood, a body of water at the center of a mountain. She appears as the second stage boss of Lotus Land Story.

Name: Kutaka Niwatari
Summary: Kutaka Niwatari (庭渡 久侘歌 Niwatari Kutaka) is a god of chickens and a guard of Hell. She lives in a spring atop the Youkai Mountain but goes to Higan for her job of overseeing the gateway to otherworlds such as Hell under the yama's oversight. Kutaka first appeared as the stage 3 midboss and boss in Wily Beast and Weakest Creature, attempting to dissuade the protagonist from entering Hell. She speaks in a polite, somewhat refined manner, and despite already being authorized to let the protagonist through, she takes extra care to test the protagonist's strength out of concern for their well-being.

Name: Lara-Su
Summary: Lara-Su was Knuckles’s and Julie-Su's daughter from the alternate future timeline known as Light Mobius. She was initially at odds with her father, who refused to allow her to become a Guardian. Eventually, he relented however, only for that future to be warped almost beyond recognition by an alteration of history from King Sonic. Lara-Su and a few others recalled the rightful timeline, and together fought the despotic King Shadow. Lara-Su herself ended the fight by imprisoning him with Chaos Control. Serving as a Guardian for five years, she also became a member of the Future Freedom Fighters when Shadow returned.

Name: Lich (Final Fantasy I)
Summary: Lich is the fiend of Earth and the first of the four fiends fought by the Warriors of Light. He rests at the bottom of Earthgift Shrine and appears to be a skeleton of the undead.

Name: Lord Tsukuyomi
Summary: Lord Tsukuyomi is the leader and ruler of the Lunar Capital. Very little is known about him.

Name: Louise (Touhou Project)
Summary: Louise is one of many demons from Makai, serving as the Stage 2 boss of Mystic Square, and later as a mid-boss of Stage 4.

Name: Lunar Capital
Key: '''Basic Infantry | Higher Technology and High Ranking Members | Gods'''
Summary: The Lunar Capital (月の都, Tsuki no Miyako) is an extremely powerful and advanced civilization on the Moon of the Touhou Project universe. They used to be humans living on Earth. However, their leader, Lord Tsukuyomi, wanted him and his kind to escape the impurity of Earth. They did so by colonizing the moon, an otherwise untouched and pure land, where they could live a completely pure life.

Name: Mai (Touhou Project)
Summary: Mai is, along with Yuki, a witch who resides in Makai and with Yuki, serves as one of two bosses in Mystic Square's fourth stage.

Name: Maji Kayo (Anime)
Summary: Maji Kayo is a fighter from Universe 3 for the Tournament of Power.

Name: Majin Buu
Summary: nan

Name: Majin Buu (DBS Manga)
Summary: Majin Buu is an extremely ancient creature, who has been controlled by the evil wizard Bibidi with the purpose of ruling the universe.

Name: Mamizou Futatsuiwa
Summary: Mamizou Futatsuiwa (二ッ岩 マミゾウ) is a Bake-danuki summoned by Nue Houjuu to act as the Myouren Temple's trump card against Toyosatomimi no Miko.

Name: Mammoth Mogul
Summary: IN: Then its true! Your power, your knowledge, it must mean...! MM: Yes, Naugus. I was once known as Ixis Mogul.

Name: Marilith (Final Fantasy I)
Summary: Marilith is the Fiend of Fire. She appears in Mount Gulg as a woman with the lower body of a snake and has six arms, each wielding a sword.

Name: Marisa Kirisame
Summary: Marisa Kirisame is an "ordinary" human magician specializing in flashy heat and light-based magic, and the secondary protagonist of the Touhou Project. She is a notorious and proud thief and has built herself up as a great magician through nothing but hard work and dedication to her craft.

Name: Meira
Summary: Meira is a swordswoman from Gensokyo. She came to the Hakurei Shrine to steal the Hakurei's power, but was defeated.

Name: Mephiles the Dark (Archie Comics)
Summary: Mephiles the Dark is a character mentioned in the Sonic the Hedgehog Encyclopedia published by Archie Comics.

Name: Meta Knight
Summary: Nova: "READY. -> I WILL GRANT YOU ONE WISH... ->" Meta Knight: "My one wish is to become stronger... So I wish to fight... the greatest warrior in the galaxy!

Name: Metal Sonic v3.0 (Archie Comics)
Summary: Metal Sonic (v3.0) is an antagonist in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: Mighty the Armadillo (Archie Pre-Genesis Wave)
Summary: Mighty the Armadillo is a Mobian eastern armadillo who took up residence in the mountains of Angel Island, though he was born planet-side in the Kingdom of Mercia. He has known Sonic the Hedgehog since his childhood, but they wouldn't meet again for roughly six years after their first adventure. After spending much of his youth wandering, he was brought to the Floating Island by Knuckles the Echidna and Vector the Crocodile. Thus, he became one of the original members of the Chaotix.

Name: Mima
Summary: Mima (魅魔) is a vengeful spirit that haunts the area around the Hakurei Shrine in the PC-98 canon. Though she is called an evil spirit, she is not the same variety as the ones that appear in Subterranean Animism and Wild and Horned Hermit. She is, in reality, extremely strong, and she is very confident in her combat and magical abilities. Originally, she is sealed in the hokora attached to the shrine, but she manages to repeatedly break free of the seal.

Name: Mini-Hakkero
Summary: The Mini-Hakkero is a magical furnace currently possessed by Marisa Kirisame. The mini-hakkero was given to her by Rinnosuke Morichika in Curiosities of Lotus Asia. It's not an actual weapon though.

Name: Ministry of Right and Wrong
Summary: The Ministry of Right and Wrong is the organization that manages the entire system regarding Souls and the afterlife in the Touhou Project series. Created in response to humanity's growing numbers, it is mainly composed of the many judges who deal with the deceased and of the leaders of Heaven, the Netherworld and the many hells.

Name: Mizue no Uranoshimako
Summary: Mizue no Uranoshimako was a human fisherman from Earth, who accidentally found himself on the Moon. Believing it to be the Dragon Palace, he stayed there for three years before being sent to his world, but three hundred years into the future. When he arrived, everyone he knew had disappeared, and no one believed his stories about the Dragon Palace. In despair, he opened up the box that was gifted to him, which made him age all of his 300 skipped years. Despite his old age, rumors about the old man's visit to the Dragon Palace spread around the land, eventually reaching the Emperor's ear. However, Uranoshimako had already died by the time the Emperor got to him. A shrine was built in his name, and he eventually became a god.

Name: Monkey Khan
Summary: Monkey Khan, originally named Ken Khan, is a character that appears in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: Mononobe no Futo
Summary: Mononobe no Futo (物部 布都) is a Shikaisen, a Taoist Hermit and a loyal servant of Toyosatomimi no Miko.

Name: Moro
Summary: Moro is a powerful wizard who threatened Universe 7 about ten million years ago. His power proved to be so great that the Grand Supreme Kai needed to sacrifice his own godly power in order to seal him away. Now that his power has been returned after millions of years of imprisonment, Moro once again poses a threat to the Universe.

Name: Mugetsu
Summary: Mugetsu (夢月) is the first Extra Stage boss of Lotus Land Story and possibly the creator of a mysterious dream world in which Reimu Hakurei and Marisa Kirisame stumbled upon. She is the younger sister of Gengetsu and appears to be dressed as a maid of some sort, but according to the music comments of her theme "Illusion of a Maid ~ Icemilk Magic" in Lotus Land Story, she is probably not a maid. Not much is known about her or her sister as they serve no relevance to the plot.

Name: Nicole the Holo-Lynx (Archie Pre-Genesis Wave)
Summary: Nicole, also NICOLE, is the assistant of Princess Sally and the one who governs New Mobotropolis in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: Nue Houjuu
Summary: Nue Houjuu (封獣 ぬえ) is said to be one of the most mysterious and feared youkai in many years, yet has been defeated by humans many times. There are many different legends according to her appearance because she hides her "true form". At some point, she was sealed underground, but after the events of Subterranean Animism, she resurfaced back in Gensokyo.

Name: Nyarlathotep (VShojo Mythos)
Summary: Nyarlathotep is the emissary sent by Azathoth to light the beacon of chaos and bring an end to existence. Before heading to the farthest reaches of the expanse, she created a companion named Goro from the cosmic dust surrounding her. Goro was the one to give her the nickname, "Nyan." Once Nyan stumbled upon Earth, she began harvesting the sanity of humans to fuel the beacon. Nature itself rose to stop Nyan from reawakening her creators, stealing her powers and freezing her beneath the East Siberian Sea.

Name: Occult Balls
Summary: The Occult Balls are a collection of objects found in a variety of Mystery Spots all over the world. Much like the Mystery Spots they emerged from, these Occult Balls' main purpose is to increase the spiritual strength of something. Unlike these spots, however, these objects mainly increases the strength of beliefs around them, causing those to be manifested in the real world. Thus, they are the main cause of the Urban Legends incident of Gensokyo. However, one of them was different and stronger than the rest. It was the Lunar Capital Ball, created by Sagume Kishin. This ball was part of a plan by the Lunarians to move the Capital in Gensokyo by spreading the rumor of NASA hiding what they saw on the Moon, thus making the Capital manifest itself in Gensokyo.

Name: Okina Matara
Summary: Okina Matara (摩多羅 隠岐奈, Matara Okina) is a secret god who lurks behind all things, hiding in plain sight behind a number of public faces and disguises, such as an Earth Mother Goddess, a god of Noh, a god of the stars, a god of silkworm breeding, a god of impediments, and a god of burakumin. No one knows her true identity, but she was one of the sages who helped create Gensokyo in the past. Now, living in the Outside World, she protects Gensokyo and maintains its balance.

Name: Optimus Prime (IDW)
Summary: Question One: In whose interest do you exercise your power?

Name: Orange (Touhou Project)
Summary: Orange is the first boss enemy encountered in Touhou 4, Lotus Land Story. Though she may be a boss opponent, she is defeated easily by the protagonist as they move on to the Lake of Blood ahead.

Name: Patchouli Knowledge
Summary: Patchouli Knowledge is a very smart, anemic and asthmatic magician from the Scarlet Devil Mansion. As opposed to the rest of the inhabitants, she is neither an employee or relative of Remilia Scarlet, instead being a close friend whose role is to cause and solve problems. She spends most of her time in the mansion's library reading and writing magic books. It seems that she's capable of very powerful magic of all kinds, using many elements in a single spell, but due to her anemia, asthma and general poor health she's often unable to recite her spells.

Name: Phantoms (Touhou Project)
Summary: Phantoms are a kind of spirit in the Touhou Project series. They are the embodiment of the spirits of things, be it plants, humans or otherwise. They are not to be confused with ghosts.

Name: Power Rings (Archie Comics)
Summary: Power Rings, also called Magic Rings, are objects that appear in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: Rabanra
Summary: Rabanra (ラバンラ Rabanra) is a warrior from Dragon Ball's Universe 2, a member of Team Universe 2, and an attendant to the Kamikaze Fireballs.

Name: Ran Yakumo
Summary: Ran Yakumo (八雲 藍, Yakumo Ran) is an unknown shikigami created by Yukari Yakumo that has possessed the body of a nine-tailed kitsune as long as she has been seen. None of the kitsune's original consciousness has ever been stated to be present. She obtained the powers and abilities of this unnamed kitsune by possessing her. Kitsune grow one extra tail per 100 years that they live. The possessed kitsune's nine tails showcases her great power and experience and her approaching divinity. It is not shown how she was created, or how she possessed the kitsune, but she is a very powerful youkai, even capable of owning a shikigami of her own.

Name: Reimu Hakurei
Summary: Reimu Hakurei is the Shrine Maiden of the Hakurei Shrine and the main protagonist of the Touhou series alongside her friend, Marisa Kirisame. She is exceptionally talented and gifted, but her laziness makes her hate training.

Name: Reisen Udongein Inaba
Summary: Reisen Udongein Inaba is a moon rabbit who deserted the Lunar Capital during the "Lunar War" that began in 1969, after the Apollo 11 "invasion". Arriving in Gensokyo, she stumbled upon the infamous fugitives Kaguya Houraisan and Eirin Yagokoro, and in exchange for asylum in Eientei, she swore loyalty to them.

Name: Remilia Scarlet
Summary: Remilia Scarlet is the head of the Scarlet Devil Mansion, the mistress of Sakuya and Meiling, a close friend of Patchouli's, and the older sister of Flandre Scarlet. While she often seems childish and non-threatening, she is incredibly strong and is known across Gensokyo as the "Scarlet Devil".

Name: Rick (Kirby)
Summary: Rick is a friendly and energetic hamster that is a close friend with Kirby. He is one of the original three Animal Friends appearing Kirby's Dream Land 2, making major appearances in classic games of the series.

Name: Rika (Touhou Project)
Key: '''Rika by herself''' | '''Flower Tank/Shrine Tank''' | '''Evil Eye Sigma'''
Summary: Rika is a human engineer and first boss of Story in Eastern Wonderland. She is responsible for the creation of all the enemies in her stage, though she is unrelated to the incident.

Name: Rikako Asakura
Summary: Rikako Asakura is a scientist from Gensokyo. Being one of the few persons using science instead of magic, she firmly believes that the mysterious ruins were made using science.

Name: Rinnosuke Morichika
Summary: Rinnosuke Morichika (森近 霖之助, Morichika Rinnosuke), nicknamed Kourin (香霖), is a half-human half-youkai hybrid and using his ability to know the name and purpose of an object, he runs Kourindou, an antique shop specializing in items from the Outside World. He's one of the few male characters depicted in the Touhou Project and is the protagonist of Curiosities of Lotus Asia.

Name: Rodimus (IDW)
Summary: We've seen off a phase sixer, cured an army of sparkeaters, survived a mutiny, travelled in time, gatecrashed a universe, saved half our race, we've liberated planets, defeated the D.J.D., found Luna-1 and the Necrobot, rescued TWO metrotitans, been erased from existence and stole a moon, and a few hours ago we died and broke heaven.

Name: Rouge the Bat (Archie Pre-Genesis Wave)
Summary: Rouge the Bat is a character that appears in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: Roukanken and Hakurouken
Summary: Tier: 2-C

Name: Sagume Kishin
Summary: Sagume Kishin (稀神サグメ Kishin Sagume) is a reclusive, high-ranking official on the Moon. Due to her power to reverse any situation by merely speaking of it, she is similar to an Amanojaku, but instead of acting contrarily, the world acts contrarily in response to her words. While she can be tentatively classified as a Divine Spirit, but her true nature is not that of a God.

Name: Sakuya Izayoi
Summary: Sakuya Izayoi is the chief maid of the Scarlet Devil Mansion. Although she is the leader of the fairy maids there, she usually has to do all of the work herself, as the fairy maids are completely useless. She also helps resolve incidents (usually those concerning the mansion), alongside Reimu Hakurei and Marisa Kirisame. Her origins are unknown; she is said to have been given her name by Remilia Scarlet, and Hieda no Akyuu theorizes that she was originally a vampire hunter.

Name: Sally Acorn (Archie Pre-Genesis Wave)
Summary: S: Fine then. I'm guilty. Hamlin: Well! In that case, I move that we... S: But understand this... I will not go through this again. I will not act, I will not give any order, until I have direct approval of the council. Even if we're in the middle of a fight. You can discount any help from the Chaotix, they are free agents, beyond my control. I will refuse to give them any orders. Or— You can trust me. I’ve been defending us all my life. I wouldn’t do anything to endanger my people.

Name: Sanae Kochiya
Summary: Sanae Kochiya is a human descendant of Suwako Moriya who was born in the Outside World. While she is a minor goddess due to her divine heritage, she works as the shrine maiden and wind priestess of the Moriya Shrine and moved into Gensokyo along with Suwako Moriya and Kanako Yasaka. As a result, she is one of the few people living in Gensokyo with a developed knowledge of the Outside World.

Name: Sara (Touhou Project)
Summary: Sara is the Stage 1 boss of Mystic Square and the gatekeeper of Makai, the realm created by Shinki.

Name: Sariel (Touhou Project)
Summary: Sariel is one of the final bosses of the original Touhou game, Highly Responsive to Prayers. She seems to be responsible for destroying Reimu's shrine and is eventually defeated by the Shrine Maiden.

Name: Seiga Kaku
Summary: Seiga Kaku (霍青娥) is the wicked hermit responsible for resurrecting Yoshika Miyako and converting Toyosatomimi no Miko to Taoism.

Name: Seven-Three
Summary: Seven-Three (セブンスリー Sebunsurī), whose proper designation is OG73-I, is a member of the Galactic Bandit Brigade.

Name: Shadow the Hedgehog (Archie Pre-Genesis Wave)
Summary: Shadow the Hedgehog is a protagonist in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: Shadow the Hedgehog (Light Mobius)
Summary: King Shadow the Hedgehog is a character that appears in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: Shard the Metal Sonic
Summary: Shard the Metal Sonic was the first ever version of Metal Sonic,[2] created by Mobius Prime's original Eggman to have his own Sonic the Hedgehog. He met his demise attempting to race Sonic on Stardust Speedway, his legs beginning to melt as he tried to keep up with his organic counterpart after he performed his Super Peel Out.

Name: Shinki
Summary: Shinki (神綺) is the goddess and creator of Makai, an alternate realm in the Touhou universe. However, she decided to start a vacation business to Gensokyo, sending demons there. Four people, Reimu, Marisa, Yuuka and Mima, went into her own Realm to beat her up and force her to abandon this project. To this day, she hasn't stopped yet.

Name: Shinmyoumaru Sukuna
Summary: Shinmyoumaru Sukuna (少名 針妙丸 Sukuna Shinmyoumaru) is an inchling living in the Shining Needle Castle. Her ancestor Issun-Boushi exterminated an oni, and obtained the oni's treasure, the "Miracle Mallet".

Name: Shion Yorigami
Summary: Shion Yorigami is Joon's elder twin sister and a goddess of poverty. As she brings misfortune and ruin everywhere she goes, she is universally despised, and she is incredibly unlucky herself. Due to the loathing she is subject to, Shion is generally depressed and lacks any motivation to do anything, preferring to let other people handle things for her while she wallows.

Name: Shou Toramaru
Summary: Shou Toramaru (寅丸 星, Toramaru Shou) is a disciple of the god Bishamonten (毘沙門天). Along with Minamitsu Murasa and the other youkai aboard the Palanquin Ship, she seeks to revive Byakuren Hijiri after she had been sealed away in Makai by humans.

Name: Silver Crystal (Sailor Moon)
Summary: The Silver Crystal (幻の銀水晶, Maboroshi no Ginzuishou; often translated as "the Illusionary Silver Crystal"), was a crystalline object of great and immeasurable power.it is the center of the plot of the Manga Sailor Moon, because of its power, All the Antagonist of the manga have tried to Get it in vain, It was used by Queen Serenity and Usagi. there are variant of the Silver Crystal like the Millennium Crystal which is a palace formed by the Silver Crystal when Usagi becomes queen in the future.

Name: SinGyoku
Summary: SinGyoku is a mysterious entity that appears at the Hakurei Shrine.

Name: Son Gohan (DBS Anime)
Key: '''Resurrection of F''' | '''Universe 6 Tournament''' | '''Tournament of Power''' | '''Super Hero Arc'''
Summary: Son Gohan (孫そん悟ご飯はん?) is the eldest son of Son Goku and Chi-Chi, and one of the primary heroes of the second half of Dragon Ball. Although originally introduced as a mild-mannered and easily scared child, Gohan harbors an immense, limitless potential that surpasses that of his father. However, unlike his father, Gohan dislikes fighting and harming others, and his true power only shows through during moments of intense rage. Following Goku's death, he was trained by Piccolo in anticipation of the upcoming Saiyan invasion, and grew much stronger and closer to his new mentor, ultimately redeeming him and setting him down the path of heroism due to their bond.

Name: Son Gohan (DBS Manga)
Summary: Son Gohan (孫そん悟ご飯はん?) is the eldest son of Son Goku and Chi-Chi, and one of the primary heroes of the second half of Dragon Ball. Although originally introduced as a mild-mannered and easily scared child, Gohan harbors an immense, limitless potential that surpasses that of his father. However, unlike his father, Gohan dislikes fighting and harming others, and his true power only shows through during moments of intense rage. Following Goku's death, he was trained by Piccolo in anticipation of the upcoming Saiyan invasion, and grew much stronger and closer to his new mentor, ultimately redeeming him and setting him down the path of heroism due to their bond.

Name: Son Goten (Manga)
Key: '''Majin Buu Arc''' | ''' DBS Super Hero Onwards '''
Summary: Son Goten (孫そん悟ご天てん, Son Goten?) is a protagonist in the Dragon Ball manga and the animes Dragon Ball Z, Dragon Ball GT and Dragon Ball Super. He is the younger son of the main protagonist of the Dragon Ball series Goku and his wife Chi-Chi, making him a Saiyan and Human hybrid. Goten is Gohan's younger brother and Trunks' best friend.

Name: Sous Roas (Anime)
Summary: Sous Roas (スー・ロース, Sū Rōsu) is a warrior from Universe 2 and a member of the Kamikaze Fireballs. In her Magical Girl form, she becomes Magical Girl Roasie (ロージィ, Rōjī).

Name: Storm the Albatross (Archie Comics)
Summary: Storm the Albatross is a hulking, grey albatross and the enforcer of the Babylon Rogues. Strong-armed and simple-minded, he serves as Jet the Hawk's right hand man and is usually at odds with his intellectually superior teammate, Wave the Swallow. Relying more on his brute strength, Storm is not the most skilled at riding Extreme Gear, but is still an adequate flyer while being able to match other physically fit opponents like Knuckles the Echidna.

Name: Suika Ibuki
Summary: Suika Ibuki (伊吹 萃香, Ibuki Suika) is a typical oni who loves drinking and fighting. Before appearing in Gensokyo, she lived in the Underworld, and even before that, she lived on Youkai Mountain as one of the four "Devas of the Mountain", along with Yuugi Hoshiguma and two other unknown oni. Due to her immense strength, she is still remembered as someone to be respected.

Name: Suiki
Summary: Suiki is one of the Kishin Chiefs of Hell. It has been sent in Gensokyo to defeat Seiga Kaku, a hermit who lived past her intended lifespan.

Name: Sumireko Usami
Key: '''Base''' | '''Dream World''' | '''With the Occult Balls' true power'''
Summary: Sumireko Usami is the president of the Occult Club from the Outside world. She first reached Gensokyo through her dreams, but she planned to destroy the barrier separating the outside world from Gensokyo so she could access it fully.

Name: Suwako Moriya
Summary: Suwako Moriya (洩矢 諏訪子, Moriya Suwako) is the original goddess of the Moriya Shrine, prior to Kanako's take over. Officially the shrine belongs to Kanako, but Suwako handles the divine services. She is a native god born from and formed of faith, and Sanae Kochiya is her distant descendant and shrine maiden.

Name: Sword of Hisou
Summary: The Sword of Hisou is a relic that can only be wielded by Celestials and Tenshi's primary weapon.

Name: Tails (Archie Pre-Genesis Wave)
Summary: Miles Tails Prower is one of the main protagonists in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: Tenryu (Touhou Project)
Summary: Tenryu, also known as the Celestial Dragon, is one of the Dragons in the world of Touhou Project. It is a living constellation in Heaven that is bound to eventually devour the Unmoving Star, also known as the North Star.

Name: Tenshi Hinanawi
Summary: Born Chiko Hinanawi, she ascended alongside her parents when they became Celestials, and chose to rename herself Tenshi. However, as she did not earn ascension herself, she is considerably less enlightened than her peers and quickly grew bored and frustrated with Bhavaagra. This is what prompted her to cause chaos in Gensokyo, having watched several of the incidents its inhabitants have caused and deciding that they must be lots of fun.

Name: Terminus Blade
Summary: The Terminus Blade is a legendary weapon that can bring Omega Terminus under heel, but also connect and even move worlds. It was created by Solus Prime for herself and her brethren to cross dimensions in their campaign against Unicron. As fate would have it, however, technological advancement rendered the Blade obsolete, and so it was carelessly cast aside, with none of the Thirteen considering what would happen if ordinary Cybertronians were to get ahold of it.

Name: The Brotherhood of Guardians
Summary: To ensure history not repeat itself, they appointed a Guardian to stand and watch over the surviving Chaos Emerald. Edmund was the first to bear that mantle. A scared trust, passed generation unto generation, through all his children, to my father and finally, to me!

Name: The Creator (VShojo Mythos)
Summary: As their title implies, The Creator is the higher power responsible for the existence of everything in the VShojo multiverse. Once everything had been created, they fell asleep almost immediately afterwards, locked behind a gate which was guarded by the higher angels. No one laid eyes on the Creator for eons, until one lower angel dared challenge the status quo.

Name: The Crystals (Final Fantasy)
Summary: The Crystals are objects of power that appear in the Final Fantasy series, serving as embodiments of wisdom and keepers of the four elements. In reality, they were made and sent out to various planets by The Creator for the ultimate goal of recording and furthering evolution. The crystals are a notable point of plot in the first five games in the series, and are confirmed to exist at least on the first six.

Name: Tiamat (Final Fantasy I)
Summary: Tiamat is the Fiend of Wind final and most powerful member of the Four Fiends that the Warriors of Light face. She forged a contract with Garland to create an everlasting time loop that would revive the Fiends time and again until the Warriors of Light ventured into the past to end them once and for all.

Name: Toyosatomimi no Miko
Summary: Toyosatomimi no Miko is the true identity of Prince Shoutoku, an advocate of Buddhism from the 6th century. Renowned for her genius and skill, Miko gradually became dissatisfied with her life and turned against her fate as a human to eventually die. She was approached by Seiga Kaku, a Taoist hermit who taught her the ways of Taoism. Miko was delighted to find a religion that could help her realize true immortality, though she knew that it wasn't fit for ruling a country. So, she pretended to support Buddhism while advancing her own study of Taoism.

Name: Trunks (Manga)
Key: '''Majin Buu Arc''' | ''' DBS Super Hero Onwards '''
Summary: Trunks (トランクス) is a protagonist in the Dragon Ball manga, and the anime series Dragon Ball Z, and Dragon Ball Super. He is the Human and Saiyan hybrid son of Bulma and Vegeta.

Name: Tupper (Anime)
Summary: Tupper is a Pride Trooper from Universe 11 who fought in the Tournament of Power.

Name: Ultimate Annihilator
Summary: The Ultimate Annihilator was the ultimate weapon of the late, Prime Dr. Ivo Robotnik in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: Utsuho Reiuji
Summary: Utsuho Reiuji is one of Satori Komeiji's pets and the regulator of the flames of the former Hell of Blazing Fires. A Hell Raven, born from the darkness of Hell, Utsuho isn't the brightest, which made her a good subject for Kanako Yasaka's plan to gain the ultimate power of nuclear fusion. In her dreams, Utsuho was told to consume the remains of the sun god Yatagarasu, so she could fulfill the wishes of those above and below the surface of the world. However, she misinterpreted the message and decided that she would use her newfound, immense power to conquer all of Gensokyo and incinerate any who opposed her.

Name: Vector the Crocodile (Archie Pre-Genesis Wave)
Summary: Vector the Crocodile is a Mobian crocodile and one of Knuckles the Echidna's oldest friends and the de-facto leader of the Chaotix. Having lived with the Guardian on Angel Island and made his acquaintance after what Knuckles thought was the death of his father Locke, Vector was the first mobian to join Knuckles as an ally in combat.

Name: Vegeta (DBS Manga)
Key: '''Battle of Gods Arc''' | '''Resurrection 'F' Arc''' | '''Universe 6 - Future Trunks Arc''' | '''Post-Training Future Trunks Saga''' | '''Universe Survival - Broly Arc''' | '''Galactic Patrol Prisoner Arc''' | '''Granolah the Survivor Arc'''
Summary: Vegeta (ベジータ, Bejīta?) is the disgraced prince of the Saiyan race, one of the few survivors of his species after Frieza destroyed Planet Vegeta. Left with no choice but to follow his orders, Vegeta travelled across the galaxy and eradicated planets for sale before he was brought to Earth by Raditz's report of the Dragon Balls, a magical set of balls that could grant him immortality. Upon arriving on Earth, he ultimately comes to encounter and fights Son Goku, the man who would go on to become his greatest rival.

Name: Vegito
Summary: nan

Name: Vegito (DBS Manga)
Summary: Vegito (ベジット, Bejitto?) is the Potara Fusion of Son Goku and Vegeta, originally formed to defeat Majin Buu after he had absorbed Gohan, and later reappearing to fight Fusion Zamasu. While all fusions have immense power, Vegito's power is abnormal even by Potara standards, as Vegeta and Goku's intense rivalry has brought out an exceptional power.

Name: Viara (Anime)
Summary: Viara is a warrior from Universe 3 who fought in the Tournament of Power.

Name: Warrior of Light (Final Fantasy XIV)
Summary: The Warrior of Light, sometimes known as the Warrior of Darkness, Hydaelyn's Chosen, or the Hero of Eorzea, is a silent adventurer and the protagonist of the MMORPG Final Fantasy XIV. Though his gender, race, and appearance vary from player to player, he is represented in trailers and promotional materials as a male Midlander Hyur. As the chosen warrior of Hydaelyn, the Warrior uses his power to protect the realm of Eorzea from whatever threat would seek to destroy it.

Name: Watatsuki no Toyohime
Summary: Watatsuki no Toyohime is a Lunarian princess. Along with her younger sister, Yorihime, she is in charge of the Lunarian Defense Corps.

Name: Watatsuki no Yorihime
Summary: Watatsuki no Yorihime is a Lunarian princess. Along with her sister, Toyohime, she is the head of the Lunarian Defense Corps; she appears to be primarily responsible for training the moon rabbits.

Name: Wave the Swallow (Archie Comics)
Summary: Wave the Swallow is a purple Mobian swallow, and the resident technical genius for the Babylon Rogues. As a former member of the Battle Bird Armada, Wave worked with Dr. Fukurokov until she crossed him and went Rogue after escaping jail. She is quite knowledgable in mechanics and technological expertise, and is responsible for maintaining the Rogues' zeppelin and its supplies. Wave is a skilled rider of Extreme Gear and considers all of the Rogue's Gear her own; taking great pride in the work she puts into it while demeaning the skills of others like Tails with his own airboards, which makes her a bit of a trash-talker. She obsesses greatly over the effort put into keeping their Extreme Gear in the best condition possible that she gives them priority over anything else once they take enough damage. After a failed battle to steal a Sol Emerald, Wave found a clue to Babylon Garden that enabled the Rogues to discover the means to unlock it.

Name: Yatagarasu
Summary: Yatagarasu was the avatar of Amaterasu and the Personification of the Sun. It used to be a giant crow living in the sun. However, seemingly after Houyi shot down the sun, it was found deceased. Following this, Kanako planned to make a certain underworld raven a living nuclear reactor by making her absorb the deceased Sun God into her being.

Name: Yin-Yang Orb
Summary: The Yin-Yang Orb is Reimu's main weapon and one of the main artifact of the Hakurei Shrine. Its exact nature hasn't been explained in detail, but it is recognized as an artifact from the Hakurei God that was created to fulfill the Shrine's function of exterminating youkai.

Name: Youkai Mountain
Summary: The Youkai Mountain is an important landmark in Gensokyo and home to several youkai, as per its name. The mountain covers several smaller locations such as the Giant Toad's Pond, the Moriya Shrine, the Genbu Ravine and the Untrodden Valley.

Name: Youmu Konpaku
Summary: Youmu Konpaku (魂魄 妖夢, Konpaku Youmu) is Yuyuko Saigyouji's gardener and attendant. A half-human, half-phantom, she was trained in the art of swordplay by the previous gardener, Youki Konpaku, and took over his position once he disappeared.

Name: Yukari Yakumo
Summary: Yukari Yakumo is a legendary youkai with the power to manipulate boundaries, and one of the youkai sages who created Gensokyo. Often called the "gap youkai," she is a remarkably youkai-like youkai who spends most of her time sleeping and relaxing. However, she is quite brilliant and is aware of most things happening within Gensokyo.

Name: Yuki (Touhou Project)
Summary: Yuki is, along with Mai, a witch who resides in Makai and with Mai, serves as one of two bosses in Mystic Square's fourth stage.

Name: Yumeko
Summary: Yumeko is a resident of Makai, and one of Shinki's greatest creations. Initially polite towards her master, she regards the main heroines with disdain. Despite her display of power and being ranked as one of the most powerful beings, she is quickly defeated.

Name: Yumemi Okazaki
Summary: Yumemi Okazaki (岡崎 夢美, Okazaki Yumemi) is a college professor who has come to Gensokyo in her ship, the Probability Space Hypervessel, in search of magic, to bring it back to the scientific community.

Name: YuugenMagan
Summary: YuugenMagan is a boss from the first installment of the Touhou Project series: Highly Responsive to Prayers. Nothing is known about this enemy, except the fact that it's found in Makai.

Name: Yuugi Hoshiguma
Summary: Yuugi Hoshiguma is an oni of the Underworld and one of the former Big Four of the Mountain, alongside Suika Ibuki. Content to spend her life partying and drinking, she lives alongside the many other oni that were forced below ground.

Name: Yuuka Kazami
Summary: Yuuka Kazami (風見 幽香, Kazami Yuuka) is a mysterious, long-lived youkai most often found in the Garden of the Sun. With a threat level described as "very high" and a human friendship level described as "worst", she is a fearsome and immensely strong youkai despite her polite mannerisms.

Name: Yuuma Toutetsu
Summary: Yuuma Toutetsu (饕餮 尤魔 Toutetsu Yuuma) is the leader of the Gouyoku Alliance under which the eagle spirits serve. She was originally mentioned by Saki Kurokoma in the extra stage of Wily Beast and Weakest Creature, before appearing as the primary antagonist of Gouyoku Ibun.

Name: Yuyuko Saigyouji
Summary: Yuyuko Saigyouji is the ghost princess of Hakugyokurou, the shrine of the Netherworld. In life, before she became a ghost, she was the head of the Saigyouji clan. Possessing the powerful ability to manipulate departed souls, after this power developed into the ability to kill anything, Yuyuko was overwhelmed by the power of her ability and, terrified, she committed suicide. She was buried under the Saigyou Ayakashi, sealing away its blossoms, and she returned as a ghost, incapable of vanishing or reincarnating as long as the seal still stands.

Name: Zone Cops
Summary: We're Ready for this, every Single Zone Cop is prepared to give it all they've got.

Name: 160-Ton Thermonuclear Bomb
Summary: The 160-Ton Thermonuclear Bomb is a Doomsday weapon created by Captain Underpants's arch nemesis, Tippy Tinkletrousers. After suffering a humiliating defeat from the hero, Tippy planned to get his final revenge by detonating the bomb. Which would destroy Captain Underpants, and the entire world along with him.

Name: A.D.A.M.
Summary: A.D.A.M: If you insist.

Name: Agrias Oaks
Summary: Lady Agrias Oaks is a secondary character appearing in Final Fantasy Tactics, initially as a guest character working together with Ramza Beoulve through the story, finally joining him during the events of Chapter 2.

Name: Aigis
Summary: Aigis is a 7th Generation Anti-Shadow Suppression Weapon constructed by the Kirijo Group as part of their experiments. Created to wield a Persona and do battle against Shadows, she is one of the last of her kind. She fights alongside the members of SEES during the events of Persona 3, becoming especially attached to its field leader.

Name: Akihiko Sanada
Summary: Akihiko Sanada is a playable character in Persona 3. Growing up in an orphanage alongside his best friend Shinjiro and younger sister Mikki. Mikki one day died in an orphanage fire and by that grief and powerlessness, Akihiko vowed to become stronger eventually encountering Mitsuru Kirijo and joining S.E.E.S.

Name: Alice Margatroid
Summary: Alice Margatroid is one of only a few people known to live within the Forest of Magic. She's a magician known primarily for her skillful use of dolls as well as being a loner. She gets in many fights with Marisa, but they are somewhat acquaintances, sharing many of the same interests and even teaming up at times.

Name: Amaterasu Oomikami (Touhou Project)
Summary: Amaterasu Oomikami is a goddess in the Touhou Project universe. She is the sister of Lord Tsukuyomi, the leader, and ruler of the Lunar Capital.

Name: Amy Rose (Archie Pre-Genesis Wave)
Summary: One-Two-Three-Four! Open the jailhouse door! -- I still believe in you, Sonic!

Name: Android 17
Summary: nan

Name: Android 18
Summary: nan

Name: Ann Takamaki
Key: '''Beginning of the Game''' | '''Early Game''' | '''Mid Game''' | '''Late Game''' | '''End Game'''
Summary: Ann Takamaki is one of the founding members of the Phantom Thieves of Hearts. The classmate of Ren Amamiya and Ryuji Sakamoto, she is one of the first playable characters in Persona 5. Ann was shunned because of her looks and didn't have many friends before meeting the protagonist. Along with the other Phantom Thieves of Hearts, Ann hopes to reform society by stealing the hearts of the corrupt.

Name: Ansem, Seeker of Darkness
Summary: Ansem, Seeker of Darkness, sometimes referred to as Xehanort's Heartless, is the main antagonist of Kingdom Hearts and the "Reverse/Rebirth" scenario in Kingdom Hearts: Chain of Memories, as well as a supporting antagonist in Kingdom Hearts 3D: Dream Drop Distance. He is a member of the True Organization XIII and the Heartless of Terra-Xehanort, and as such his appearance and personality are primarily derived from Master Xehanort, and he retains his original form's "shadow".

Name: Antasma
Summary: Antasma (Japanese: アックーム, Akkumu) is one of the main antagonists in Mario & Luigi: Dream Team.

Name: Antoine D'Coolette (Archie Pre-Genesis Wave)
Summary: Antoine D'Coolette is one of the main protagonist/side characters in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: Anubis Cruger
Summary: Anubis "Doggie" Cruger is the leading commander of Earth Branch's Space Patrol Delta, a dog-like alien race called Sirian, and the S.P.D Shadow Ranger. Before residing on Earth, he lives on a planet named Sirius, which was was attacked by Emperor Grumm and his forces. Despite fighting against the army and even cutting off one of Grumm's horns, the battle was lost with the Sirian race being killed and Sirius being destroyed. While he tends to act stubborn and serious, he is actually courageous, considerate, and indulgent. He was eventually promoted to Supreme Commander of Space Patrol Delta.

Name: Applejack
Key: '''Base Form''' | '''Elements of Harmony/Magic of Friendship''' | '''Rainbow Power'''
Summary: Applejack is one of the main protagonists of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Applejack (Human World)
Summary: Applejack is one of the main characters in My Little Pony Equestria Girls.

Name: Aqua (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Aqua is a Keyblade Wielder who trained under Master Eraqus alongside her friends Ventus and Terra. The only one among the trio to be named a Keyblade Master, she is entrusted by Eraqus to monitor both of her friends after they leave the Land of Departure, but finds herself torn between her duties and her feelings of friendship.

Name: Aunn Komano
Summary: Aunn Komano is a Komainu living near the Hakurei Shrine. Without its owner's knowledge, she guards the Shrine against intruders.

Name: Auta Magetta (Anime)
Summary: Auta Magetta (マゲッタ, Magetta) is a Metalman from Universe 6, a race that is said to exist as well in Universe 7. He is a member of Champa's team.

Name: Axel (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Originally known as Lea before losing his heart the day Radiant Garden fell into darkness, Axel is Organization XIII's eighth member who was assigned as Roxas' caretaker. But Axel's time with Roxas and Sora, whom he encountered while at Castle Oblivion, left an impression on him and became friends with Roxas at the cost of having a falling out with Saïx, the Nobody of his former self's friend Isa. When Roxas left the Organization, Axel followed suit after a failed attempt to save his friend from Diz's plan to integrate him into Sora. Eventually, after unknowingly giving the Organization a bargaining chip in Kairi, Axel sacrifices himself to enable Sora to save her. Axel's demise leads to his restoration into Lea who eventually gains his own Keyblade.

Name: Aya Shameimaru
Summary: Aya Shameimaru (射命丸 文) is Gensokyo's resident reporter, known for writing "slightly" exaggerated news articles about anything that happens. She's also a Tengu that prided herself on being the "Fastest" in Gensokyo (in terms of pure speed, anyway), and is overall a really strong character, able to occasionally win without trying to.

Name: Bahamut (Final Fantasy XV)
Summary: Bahamut, the Draconian, is an Astral in the Final Fantasy XV Universe. He is one of the Six and is the God of War clad in winged armor. Bahamut is said to have bestowed the powers of the Oracle and given the Ring of the Lucii and the Crystal onto his chosen king. He is the most majestic of the six gods, vastly superior to the others.

Name: Bahamut (Final Fantasy)
Summary: A recurring summon in the games, Bahamut is a force to be reckoned as one of the most powerful summons, if not the most powerful summon the player can acquire on their journey. He is most frequently found as part of a sidequest and is not relevant to the main plot, but in some cases he takes a much more active role, such as empowering the Warriors of Light in the original game with their job changes. His demeanor, behavior, and alignment change from appearance to appearance, but all recognize him as the King of Dragons and the Ruler of the Skies.

Name: Barry Kahn
Summary: Barry Kahn is an A-list actor from Dragon Ball set to play the Great Saiyaman in the film "Great Saiyaman vs Mister Satan." After Barry was rejected by Videl, he became increasingly jealous of Gohan and attempted to ruin his marriage, though without any success.

Name: Bean the Dynamite (Archie Pre-Genesis Wave)
Summary: Bean the Dynamite is a mercenary in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: Benben Tsukumo
Summary: Benben Tsukumo is one of the Tsukumogami sister. She was transformed into a Youkai from a simple tool due to the Miracle Mallet's magical powers.

Name: Bewitching Bell
Summary: The Bewitching Bell was a magical item owned by the villain Grogar long ago, who used it to steal magic and stored much of his own magic inside it. However, it was stolen by Gusty the Great, who then banished him and hid the Bell away atop Mount Everhoof.

Name: Blade Knight
Summary: Blade Knight is a character portrayed as a swordsman and knight featured in the Kirby series. He's a regular enemy across stages, which Kirby can turn into a Helper ally in some games. Blade Knight gives Kirby the Sword Copy Ability when swallowed, function he shared with Sword Knight in classic titles. Star Allies implies he wants to conquer the world.

Name: Blaze the Cat (Archie Comics)
Summary: Blaze the Cat is a princess and guardian of the Sol Emeralds in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: Blue Senturion
Summary: After the United Alliance of Evil took over the universe, the Blue Senturion was built and sent into the past to inform the Rangers about the future. Eventually he becomes part of the present time and aids the Rangers on their mission to protect the world and save Zordon

Name: Borareta (Anime)
Summary: Borareta is a fighter from Universe 3, in the Tournament of Power.

Name: Bowser
Summary: Bowser, sometimes known as King Koopa (Japanese: 大魔王クッパ, Daimaō Kuppa or "Great Demon King Koopa"), is the main antagonist of the Mario series and the King of the Koopas. He has repeatedly kidnapped or attempted to kidnap Princess Peach and take over the Mushroom Kingdom. He has also attempted to conquer other lands, such as the Mushroom World, Dinosaur Land, Sprixie Kingdom, and even the entire universe. Despite his villainous nature, he has occasionally helped the heroes of the Mushroom Kingdom against common threats and participates with them in their numerous sporting events in spin-off games.

Name: Broom Hatter
Summary: Broom Hatter is a character in the Kirby series that gives Kirby the Clean ability when swallowed.

Name: Bunnie D'Coolette (Archie Pre-Genesis Wave)
Summary: Bunnie D'Coolette is one of the main heroes in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: Byakuren Hijiri
Summary: Byakuren Hijiri (聖 白蓮, Hijiri Byakuren) is a Buddhist nun and magician, sealed away by humans for the kindness she showed Youkai, before being released from her seal during the events of Undefined Fantastic Object. Originally a human, Byakuren turned to magic to escape old age after the death of her brother, and became a Youkai. Realizing that her prosperity and power relied on the human fear and belief of Youkai, Byakuren worked to protect other Youkai while making herself out to be a great Youkai hunter. However, she eventually grew to genuinely care for the Youkai she protected. When the humans who had flocked behind her realized this, they punished her by sealing her deep within Makai; however, her followers would, thousands of years later, free her.

Name: Captain Falcon (Smash Bros)
Summary: Captain Falcon is a character that first appeared in the F-Zero series and eventually became famous thanks to his appearance in the very first Super Smash Bros game.

Name: Casey Rhodes
Key: '''Casey Rhodes''' | '''Dai-Shi awakening Arc (1-10)''' | '''Overlords Arc (11-21)''' | '''Phantom Beast Arc (22-32)'''
Summary: Casey Rhodes is the Jungle Fury Red Ranger. He was a fairly new member to the Pai Zhua Academy and hence known as a cub and possessed the spirit of the tiger. He has the power to stand up for what he believes in and for others. He doesn't like other people to get picked on. When Casey stood up one day for a fellow cub who was being verbally abused by Jarrod, Master Mao (the leader of the Pai Zhua Academy) dismissed Jarrod. Master Mao saw the potential that Casey had in him and chose him instead of Jarrod, to guard Dai Shi's imprisonment box.

Name: Casserale (Anime)
Summary: Casserale (カーセラル Kāseraru) is a cyborg warrior and general of the Pride Troopers in Universe 11 who participates in the Tournament of Power. He is also the pilot of the Pride Troopers Spaceship.

Name: Catopesra (Anime)
Summary: Catopesra is a character in Dragon Ball Super, a contestant from Universe 3 fighting in the Tournament of Power.

Name: Cerberus (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Cerberus is a three-headed hellhound who guards the Underworld. He first appeared as Hades's loyal pet in Disney's Hercules, as guard dog to the Underworld. Cerberus serves as a boss in Kingdom Hearts, Kingdom Hearts II, and Kingdom Hearts coded and Re:coded.

Name: Chang'e (Touhou Project)
Summary: Chang'e is a background character in the Touhou Project series. Although she didn't make any proper appearance, she has been mentioned numerous times, notably in Legacy of Lunatic Kingdom.

Name: Chaos (Archie Pre-Genesis Wave)
Summary: Chaos is an antagonist that appears in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: Chaos Emeralds (Archie Comics)
Summary: Through Time and Space and alternate dimensions... properties exist beyond comprehension... Artifacts of ancient and unfathomable power... Exist to aid and make men cower... Cognizant by beings of science and mystic shaman... A sovereign royal and an emerald have nothing in common!

Name: Chaos Heart
Summary: Tier: 2-A

Name: Charmy Bee (Archie Pre-Genesis Wave)
Summary: Dr. Eggman: Charmy Bee! Haven't I already ruined your life? Destroyed your kingdom or some such--right? Charmy Bee: Yes. You have. Despite all that, I've fought for our world. No matter what you do to me, I will still fight for Mobius. AND I'M NOT ALONE!

Name: Chiyuri Kitashirakawa
Summary: Chiyuri Kitashirakawa (北白河 ちゆり Kitashirakawa Chiyuri) is Yumemi's assistant. Although she looks immature, she is 15, having left graduate school and working as an assistant at a university. Her specialty is comparative physics.

Name: Chizuru Kagura
Key: '''Chapter of Orochi Saga (KOF '96 to KOF '97)''' | '''Chapter of Ash Saga (KOF 2003 to KOF XIII)'''
Summary: nan

Name: Claycia
Summary: Claycia and Elline are an inseparable team when creating Seventopia; Claycia is a master craftsman and Elline paints everything she sculpts. One day, Claycia turns evil and leaves her best friend behind. The now evil sculptor opens a hole in the skies of Dream Land and steals Planet Popstar's colors. Elline exits the hole in an attempt to escape two of Claycia's Grab Hands. As they close in on her, she repaints Kirby and Bandana Waddle Dee, who then save her from the enemies. After some explanation, Elline leads the two into the realm of Seventopia to stop Claycia and restore Planet Popstar's colors.

Name: Cloud Strife (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Cloud is a character in the Kingdom Hearts series, originating from the Final Fantasy universe. He is the main character in Final Fantasy VII and a supporting character in the Kingdom Hearts series. Cloud is twenty-two years old at the beginning of Kingdom Hearts and Kingdom Hearts: Chain of Memories and twenty-three during the events of Kingdom Hearts II.

Name: Clownpiece
Summary: Clownpiece is a Fairy from Hell who took part in the Lunar Conflict during the events of "Touhou 15: Legacy of Lunatic Kingdom". Originally a subordinate of the Goddess of Hell Hecatia Lapislazuli, she became part of Junko's plan to invade the Lunar Capital after Junko and Hecatia made an alliance seeking to take down the Lunar Goddess Chang'e.

Name: Coconteppi
Summary: Coconteppi was a Primordial Monster who existed prior to space, time and even nothingness in the Sea of Primordial Monsters. Millions of years ago he was a powerful magician who roamed Earth until he eventually died by unknown means. After his death, a group of magicians called the 'Usurpers of Wizard City' hid his skeletal remains and heart under what would later become the modern Wizard City.

Name: Cole Evans
Summary: Cole Evans is the Red Ranger Wild Force and the main character of Power Rangers Wild Force, leading his team of rangers against Master Org and other Orgs.

Name: Conner McKnight
Key: '''Civilian Form''' | '''Red Ranger''' | '''Super Dino Mode''' | '''Triassic Ranger, w/ Battlizers'''
Summary: Conner McKnight is the Dino Thunder Red Ranger and leader of the group. He is given the special power of super speed by his Red Dino Gem and fights alongside the other DT rangers in order to defeat Mesagog. Conner's enjoys soccer, playing at Reefside High School and on a namesake club, and he aspires to be a famous soccer star. At first, he appears to fit the stereotype of being a high school jock as he comes off as hot-headed, arrogant and being a bit of a flirt with woman but he is actually a very well-meaning and honest person who always does the right thing in the end.

Name: Copy-Vegeta
Summary: Copy-Vegeta is a result of the liquefied weapon Commenson absorbing the Saiyan Prince's powers. Not only does he steal his powers, but Copy Vegeta also emulates Vegeta's spirit, personality, memories and fighting techniques. Along with causing him to gradually vanish unless he is stopped. When Gotenks fails miserably against him, Vegeta's longtime rival Son Goku steps into having yet another (sort of) fight against him.

Name: Cosmos (My Little Pony)
Summary: Cosmos is the villain of the story arc spanning issues 75-78 of the My Little Pony IDW comics.

Name: Count Bleck
Summary: Lord Blumiere, also known as Count Bleck, is an evil count and is initially the primary antagonist of Super Paper Mario.

Name: Cozy Glow
Summary: Cozy Glow is an evil Pegasus in the series, My Little Pony.

Name: Crepera Lucis Caelum
Summary: Crepera Lucis Caelum is a queen of Lucis in the Final Fantasy XV Universe, more commonly known by her Lucii form as the Rogue. According to her bestiary entry her ascension was controversial as some saw women unfit to rule. She thus spurned the watch of the public eye and took to the shadows to enact her rule. She is known to have wielded a shuriken. Her statue form appears in Kingsglaive: Final Fantasy XV, and she makes an extended appearance in the Windows and Royal Editions of Final Fantasy XV where the player can find her monument and fight her as a boss.

Name: Crystal Heart
Summary: The Crystal Heart is the energy source of the Crystal Empire.

Name: D-Void
Summary: The D-Void is a mysterious dark entity that resides within the shadows of the Dead Universe and is the personification of it. A mass of eyes and black tentacles, this creature seeks to devour the life of entire worlds in order to satiate its hunger, but is unable to leave the Dead Universe without outside help. It is described as an unbelievably powerful being with the capacity to return the spark to a deceased Transformer, control the minds of robotic beings and drain energy from Cybertronians to feed on them.

Name: Darren the Ancient Sleeper
Summary: Darren the Ancient Sleeper is a mysterious being in Adventure Time, summoned by Maja The Sky Witch and was the secondary antagonist of the episode Something Big. Darren is a simple monster, wanting only battle and destruction. He was summoned by Maja the Sky Witch to destroy the Candy Kingdom for its sentimental value.

Name: Darwin Watterson
Summary: Darwin Raglan Caspian Ahab Poseidon Nicodemius Watterson Ⅲ is the deuteragonist of The Amazing World of Gumball, and is Gumball and Anais' adoptive sibling.

Name: Data-Sora
Summary: Data-Sora is the main protagonist of Kingdom Hearts coded and its remake, Kingdom Hearts Re:coded. He is a digital replica of Sora that King Mickey used to investigate the bugs in a computer simulation of Jiminy's Journal, and though he behaves much like the real Sora, he is thought to not be an actual person.

Name: Demyx
Summary: Demyx, the Melodious Nocturne (夜想のしらべ Yasō no Shirabe?, lit. Nocturnal Melody), is Rank IX within the original Organization XIII. He controls water, and uses his weapon, the sitar, as a musical instrument to make water fight for him in battle. He commands the Dancer Nobodies.

Name: Dercori (Anime)
Summary: Dercori (ダーコリ Dākori) is a warrior from Universe 4 and a member of Team Universe 4 in the Tournament of Power in Dragon Ball Super. She is a female humanoid with light violet skin, mint-green hair, folded skins on her shoulders, exceptionally large hands and feet, and fins. She is a skilled fighter who uses mystical talismans in battle.

Name: Dino Megazord
Summary: The Dino Megazord is the original Megazord granted to the Mighty Morphin Power Rangers by Zordon, and is a combination of the Zords from each Power Ranger. It is often called upon when Rita Repulsa grows one of her monsters to destroy Earth and the Power Rangers.

Name: Discord
Summary: Discord is a recurring character in My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Donald Duck (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Donald Duck is the Royal Magician of Disney Castle and one of King Mickey's most loyal attendants. He meets Sora not long after the Destiny Islands are swallowed by the Darkness, striking up a partnership with him in order to track down the King's whereabouts. While he is dismissive of the young Keyblade Wielder at first, Donald soon becomes one of Sora's closest friends and an essential ally on his journey.

Name: Donkey Kong (Super Smash Bros.)
Summary: Donkey Kong (ドンキーコング, Donkey Kong), oftentimes shortened to DK, is the eponymous protagonist of the Donkey Kong series. First premiering in the video game of the same name alongside Mario, he has since starred in a plethora of his own adventures while persisting in his rivalry against the plumber. As a member of the "perfect-attendance crew", Donkey Kong has been featured as a playable character in every installment of the Super Smash Bros. series.

Name: Doremy Sweet
Summary: Doremy Sweet is a Baku who resides in the Dream World and is its ruler.

Name: Dr. Drakken
Summary: Drew Theodore P. Lipsky was an inventor, even from a young age, being able to develop fantastical yet strange devices by the time he hit the fourth grade, using them to get an edge in sports. After a humiliation in university involving him creating the first Bebe Robot prototypes, he dropped out of school and decided to pursue his true calling in life: crime. At some point, his skin turned blue for unknown reasons, and since then, he has become one of Kim Possible's most prominent enemies under the name Dr. Drakken.

Name: Dr. Finitevus
Summary: Dr. Finitevus is a major antagonist in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: Dr. Ivo Robotnik (Archie Pre-Genesis Wave)
Summary: Dr. Ivo Robotnik, formerly known as Julian Kintobor, is the big bad of the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: Dragon God (Touhou Project)
Summary: The Dragon (龍, Ryū), also called Dragon God (龍神, Ryūjin) is, according to Perfect Memento in Strict Sense, the highest god of Gensokyo. All living things, whether human or youkai, worship the dragon god. The dragon lives in sea or sky or rain, and regardless of the Great Hakurei Border, the Dragon can move freely through heaven, hell, netherworld, and the outside world. Its voice divides the sky and causes thunderstorms. When it winds its body it causes mountains to crumble and earthquakes to occur. While destroying at the same time being the creator of Gensokyo, and the rain, the rivers, abundant greens are all due to the dragon's help.

Name: Duck Hunt Dog (Super Smash Bros)
