Summary: Duck Hunt Dog, also known as Duck Hunt Duo, which comprises of the classic dog, a duck, and the hunter, is a playable character in the Super Smash Bros. series. Originating in Super Smash Bros. for 3DS and Wii U, the dog throws various projectiles, the duck carries it around and assists the dog by extending its melee range, and the hunter fires at their opponents from far away.

Name: Dusk (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Dusk is the most common Nobody species, which is often used by Organization XIII for simple missions.

Name: Dyspo (Anime)
Summary: Dyspo is a pride trooper from Universe 11 renowned for his speed.

Name: E-123 Omega (Archie Pre-Genesis)
Summary: E-123 "Omega" is a character that appears in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: E.V.E.
Summary: Your theory is sound, small blue creature, now that i can use my ability for idepended though and do not serve Robotnik... I have the freedom of choice... not limited by boundaries be they of my mind or the vast reaches of infinity. Farewell, Sonic the Hedgehog, and thank you! Because of you, i now know what it means to be free and just as importantly - to be Me!

Name: Egg Beater
Summary: The Egg Beater is the 2nd Battle Suit/Mech created by Dr. Eggman and the first one to go up against Sonic in his base.

Name: Eight Million Gods
Summary: The Eight Million Gods, also known as the Yaoyorozu no Kami, are the gods of the Touhou Project world. They always existed in the world, even before the world became the organized whole we know today. They first gave a "name" to everything, defining each object's boundary and place in the world.

Name: Eika Ebisu
Summary: Eika Ebisu is the spirit of a stillborn child, and a god of fortune, inhabiting the riverbank of the Sanzu River. Here, she acts as the leader of other stillborn children, where she often organize stone stacking contests.

Name: Eiki Shiki, Yamaxanadu
Summary: Eiki Shiki, Yamaxanadu (四季映姫・ヤマザナドゥ) is one of the Yama who judge the dead and decide whether they go to Heaven, Hell, the Netherworld, or get reincarnated. She currently resides in Hell. Whether it's because she simply has a habit of lecturing or because she genuinely wants others to change for the better, she's become well known in Gensokyo for lecturing anyone and everyone about their faults.

Name: Eirin Yagokoro
Summary: Eirin Yagokoro (八意 永琳, Yagokoro Eirin) is a medical genius from the Moon, able to create even the Hourai Elixir with the help of Kaguya's power, the manipulation of eternity. She is living in exile in Gensokyo after choosing to stay with and devote herself to Kaguya Houraisan on Earth rather than take her back to the Moon. She was a very well-known figure on the Moon, having not only been instrumental in the founding of Lunar society with Lord Tsukuyomi, but also being its leading medical mind and the person in charge of the Moon's emissaries to the Earth.

Name: Elements of Harmony
Summary: The Elements of Harmony are legendary artifacts in Equestria. Grown from Tree of Harmony planted by Star Swirl and the Pillars of Equestria, they grant those in tune with the Magic of Friendship great power.

Name: Elias Acorn
Summary: Elias Acorn is the prince/king of the Kingdom of Acorn in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: Elis
Summary: Elis is a mysterious demon found in Makai. Nothing is known about her, except the fact that she attacks Reimu.

Name: Ellen (Touhou Project)
Summary: Ellen (エレン Eren) is an eternally young witch who stars in the 3rd Touhou game, Phantasmagoria of Dim. Dream. She does not have a good memory, often forgetting, and because of this, she is always a child.

Name: Elly
Summary: Elly is the third stage boss of Lotus Land Story, and who also serves as the gatekeeper of Mugenkan, a mansion where Yuuka resides in the PC-98 era.

Name: Enerjak
Summary: Such a show. Violence. Drama. You haven't been this much fun in years! -- Oh, don't spoil this for the boy, dear. I'm something to be experienced

Name: Espio the Chameleon (Archie Pre-Genesis Wave)
Summary: Espio the Chameleon is a character that appears in the Archie Sonic Comics and its spin-offs.

Name: Evil Dragon (Touhou Project)
Summary: The Evil Dragon was a dragon that was sealed long ago into the local Inari Shrine. It recently tricked Marisa into unsealing it.

Name: Flandre Scarlet
Summary: Flandre Scarlet (フランドール・スカーレット) is the younger sister of Remilia Scarlet and a vampire who has lived at the Scarlet Devil Mansion for over 495 years.

Name: Fluttershy
Key: '''Base Form''' | '''Elements of Harmony/Magic of Friendship''' | '''Rainbow Power'''
Summary: Fluttershy is one of the main protagonist of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Fluttershy (Human World)
Summary: Fluttershy is one of the main characters of My Little Pony Equestria Girls, and represents the Element of Kindness.

Name: Frieza (DBS Manga)
Summary: Frieza (フリーザ, Furīza?) is the leader of the Planet Trade Organization and the son of King Cold, who once ruled over the majority of the Seventh Universe for decades. Thanks to his mutant and hybrid status, Frieza was born with an abnormally high power level and never needed to train a day in his life to access his phenomenal power. But Frieza grew fearful of the legendary Super Saiyan folktale, slaughtering nearly the entirety of the Saiyan race by destroying the Saiyans' Planet Vegeta. The Saiyan genocide served as the catalyst for nearly every event since "Dragon Ball", ultimately resulting in a showdown with Goku on Namek that ended with Frieza leading himself to his own downfall by triggering the Super Saiyan transformation he feared so much.

Name: Fujiwara no Mokou
Summary: Fujiwara no Mokou (藤原 妹紅) was formerly an ordinary human, but she became an immortal being after drinking the Hourai Elixir about 1300 years ago. Now she is never able to die, though she still feels the pain of injuries as normal. She's considered to be very powerful, given her long life, the power she earned through her life, and her immortal status since she can keep fighting until she can no longer stand the pain.

Name: Fusion Zamasu (Manga)
Summary: Fusion Zamasu (合体がったい ザマス, Gattai Zamasu?) is a fusion born of the union between Goku Black (Present Zamasu in Goku's body) and Future Zamasu through the Potara earrings.

Name: Futaba Sakura
Summary: Futaba Sakura is a member of the Phantom Thieves of Hearts. She serves as the navigator for the team after they save her by helping her to overcome her intense guilt and depression stemming from the death of her mother. She is a genius hacker who uses her skills to support the Phantom Thieves both inside and outside of the Metaverse.

Name: Gamma 1 (Anime)
Summary: Gamma 1 is the first of 2 androids created by Dr. Hedo after his team-up with Magenta to rebuild the Red Ribbon Army. After Piccolo Fought Gamma 2 and manipulated the situation to get Gohan back into fighting shape, Piccolo revealed himself a second time during the latter's assault. The two Gammas started to fight Gohan and Piccolos After the two androids battled Gohan and Piccolo for a long enough time, Piccolo's convincing and the robots sensing no evil intent finally caused them to join forces with the heroes instead of fighting them.

Name: Gamma 2 (Anime)
Summary: Gamma 2 is the second of 2 androids created by Dr. Hedo after his team-up with Magenta to rebuild the Red Ribbon Army. For his first mission, he was sent to fight "the evil King Piccolo" to test his power. After arrogantly thinking he won, Piccolo tailed him back to the new Red Ribbon Army base, where he learned of the organization's plans. After Piccolo manipulated the situation to get Gohan back into fighting shape, the Namekian revealed himself a second time during the latter's assault and the two fought once again.

Name: Garland (Final Fantasy I)
Summary: Garland is the primary antagonist of Final Fantasy, originally a rogue knight from World A who abducted Princess Sarah before he was defeated by the Warrior of Light. But by fate, Garland was spirited away into World B where he ended up becoming the most faithful servant of Chaos in their battle against Cosmos and her warriors. But during the final cycle, as his fellow warriors have forsaken Chaos to act on their own whims, Garland reveals he and Chaos are bond by fate before serving as the god's last line of defense against the Warriors of Cosmos. Upon his defeat, Garland would end up in World A's distant past where he forged a pact with the Four Fiends and became the very creature whose memory inspired the creation of Chaos himself.

Name: Gas (Dragon Ball)
Summary: Gas (ガス, Gasu?) is part of the Heeter family, being a prodigy in terms of fighting strength, he acted as their muscle. He serves as one of the true main antagonists of the Granolah the Survivor Saga.

Name: Gengetsu
Summary: Gengetsu (幻月) is the second Extra Stage boss of Lotus Land Story and an inhabitant of the mysterious dream world that was said to be her younger sister's, Mugetsu.

Name: Gensokyo
Key: '''Average Humans''' | '''Fairies''' | '''Average Youkai''' | '''Stronger Individuals''' | '''Dragon God & Eirin Yagakoro'''
Summary: Gensokyo is a land hidden somewhere in Japan. Formerly mere an isolated region of the country infested by Youkai, it has now since been separated from the "Outside World" and now exists as one of the last places where Youkai and fantasy can thrive.

Name: Geoffrey St. John
Summary: Geoffrey St. John is a side character in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: Gilgamesh (Final Fantasy XV)
Summary: A great evil threatens the people of your world. It is but the King of Kings and his Shield who can safeguard their lives. All those unworthy or unwilling to rise to the task meet their end here, by my blade.

Name: Gilgamesh (Final Fantasy)
Key: '''Final Fantasy V Through XII''' | '''Dissidia Final Fantasy and Final Fantasy XIII''' | '''Final Fantasy XIV (Pre-Stormblood)''' | '''Final Fantasy XIV (Stormblood)'''
Summary: Gilgamesh is a recurring character throughout the entirety of the Final Fantasy series. First appearing as a vassal to the evil warlock, Exdeath, Gilgamesh is comically inept at his duties despite his skill as a warrior, being obsessed with obtaining the legendary Excalibur to add to his collection of weapons. Unbeknownst to him, many of these weapons are forgeries, and he's almost always seen with Excalipoor, a pale imitation of Excalibur that can only inflict shallow wounds, mistaking the false sword for the blade he seeks. After his second defeat at the hands of the Warrior of Light, Gilgamesh was sent tumbling through the Interdimensional Void, reappearing at many points throughout the franchise's history as an ally to be summoned or an optional foe to test the party's might for great rewards.

Name: Gloriosa Daisy
Summary: Gloriosa Daisy is a supporting character and later main antagonist of My Little Pony Equestria Girls: Legends of Everfree.

Name: Goku Black (Manga)
Summary: Zamasu (ザマス?) was once the Supreme Kai apprentice under Gowasu of Universe 10, who developed a loathing for mortals as he witnessed their actions across the universe, leading him to embark on a crusade against mortals after stealing the body of Son Goku using the Super Dragon Balls, gaining the title of Goku Black (悟ご空くうブラック, Gokū Burakku?), or, as he is more commonly referred, simply Black.|

Name: GOLB
Summary: GOLB is a mysterious entity from Adventure Time. It is the embodiment of Chaos itself, and was responsible for the disappearance of Magic Man's wife, Margles. This was to such a degree to where Prismo couldn't even bring her back with a wish. It was also briefly seen as Finn moves from the Pillow World back to Ooo.

Name: Goliath Doll
Summary: The Goliath Doll is a giant doll used in Alice's last spellcard during the events of Cirno's story mode in Touhou Hisoutensoku. It seems it's the most powerful doll in Alice's possession.

Name: Gomora
Key: '''Ultraman (Generation I)''' | '''Ultraman 80 (Generation II)''' | '''Ultraman: The Ultimate Hero (Powered)''' | '''Ultraman Max (Generation III)''' | '''Ultraman Mebius (Generation IV)''' | '''Ultraman Ginga S''' | '''Ultraman R/B''' | '''Ultraman Z'''
Summary: Gomora is an ancient kaiju species from Earth. Gomora is supposedly portrayed as a hostile Kaiju, starting with the emergence of Rei's Gomora, most later incarnations of them are portrayed as comrades to respective protagonists of the series.

Name: Goofy (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Goofy is the Captain of the Royal Knights of King Mickey's court. He's an easy-going and somewhat slow-witted foil to his constant companion, Donald Duck, the Royal Magician. They meet Sora not long after the Destiny Islands are swallowed up by Darkness. With the young Keyblade Wielder as their only lead in their quest to discover the King's whereabouts, Goofy teams up with Sora and helps him along in his journey, becoming one of his closest friends in the process.

Name: Gotenks
Key: '''Pre-Room of Spirit and Time Training''' | '''Post-Room of Spirit and Time Training''' | '''Super Saiyan 3''' | '''Super Hero Arc'''
Summary: nan

Name: Grand Priest (Manga)
Summary: Goku: He may not look like it but he seems pretty strong to me. Whis: Very perceptive. So far as I know the great Grand Priest is the strongest person in this world. Goku: R-REALLY?! Whis: Shhhh! Still, you must not ask to fight him or anything like that. Goku: B-but now I'm curious...

Name: Granolah
Summary: Granolah is a bounty hunter who is the last survivor of the Cerealian race, seeking revenge against Frieza for their destruction at the Saiyan Army's hands.

Name: Greninja (Super Smash Bros)
Summary: Greninja is a Water/Dark type Pokemon and the final evolution of Froakie. They are hailed as being as dangerous as any other known ninja. This specific Greninja witnessed the intense battles the Smash Bros fighters undertook, and entered it himself as a surprise entrance. He has stayed with his newfound fighting partners ever since.

Name: Gumball Watterson
Summary: My brain is amazing; when I find something boring, it actually prevents me from hearing it.

Name: Gummi Ship
Summary: The Gummi Ship is the main way to travel across the "Worlds". Being able to fit in a pocket after use and being charged with "laugh energy", they provide its wielders with a way of travel across the Realm of Light.

Name: Hades (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Hades is an antagonist from the Kingdom Hearts series, originally from the 1997 Disney animated feature Hercules. He is the Lord of the Dead and the ruler of the Underworld. Hot-headed literally and emotionally, he will stop at nothing to see the end of Hercules.

Name: Haru Okumura
Summary: Haru Okumura is a playable character from Persona 5.

Name: Hasshaku-sama (Touhou Project)
Summary: Hasshaku-sama is an Urban Legend originating from the internet. She is a ghost haunting a small village and cursing individuals every 10 years or so to a certain death.

Name: Hata no Kokoro
Summary: Hata no Kokoro (秦 こころ) is a menreiki youkai. As she relies on her masks to show her emotions to others, her facial expressions are emotionless and can be likened to a poker face.

Name: Hatate Himekaidou
Summary: Hatate Himekaidou (姫海棠 はたて) is a tengu reporter who produces Kakashi Spirit News. Unlike her rival, Aya Shameimaru, she virtually never goes outside to gather news and photographs, instead using her special ability of Thoughtography.

Name: Heavy and Bomb (Archie Pre-Genesis)
Summary: Rotor: I want Eggman to fight for every inch he gains in my city. Besides, you were with the Chaotix. Where's that take-all-challangers attitude?

Name: Hecatia Lapislazuli
Summary: Hecatia Lapislazuli (ヘカーティア・ラピスラズリ) is a mysterious Goddess of Hell who governs the Hells of the moon, the Earth, and Otherworlds. She has a separate body in each of the three worlds and can act independently with each of them. Once, she was the main leader of the Ministry of Right and Wrong, but due to unknown reasons, deserted of the organization, living now as an outlaw, controlling the Hells from the shadows.

Name: Hector Barbossa (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Captain Hector Barbossa is a character in Kingdom Hearts II and Kingdom Hearts III. He first appeared in Disney's Pirates of the Caribbean: The Curse of the Black Pearl.

Name: Hina Kagiyama
Summary: Hina Kagiyama (鍵山 雛, Kagiyama Hina) is a misfortune goddess that resides in the Great Youkai Forest, at the base of Youkai Mountain. It is her job to amass misfortune and scare off any humans that get too close.

Name: Houyi (Touhou Project)
Summary: Houyi is a god from Chinese Mythology. In Touhou, he is responsible for shooting down multiple suns, including one in Hell. Due to this action killing Junko's son, he was later murdered by her.

Name: Hunson Abadeer
Summary: Hunson Abadeer (a.k.a. the Lord of Evil) is Marceline's father and ruler of the Nightosphere. He is a powerful, deathless demon that is full of chaotic evil. He also enjoys consuming the souls of others, but does not spend much time out of the Nightosphere.

Name: Iblis (Archie Comics)
Summary: Iblis is a character mentioned in the Sonic the Hedgehog Encyclopedia published by Archie Comics.

Name: Ice Climbers (Smash Bros.)
Summary: The Ice Climbers are fighters from the iconic NES game Ice Climbers. First originating in Super Smash Bros. Melee, the Climbers, comprised of Popo and Nana, fight as a team together and use various ice-based moves based off their games. They appeared in it's sequel, Super Smash Bros. Brawl, but did not appear in Super Smash Bros. 4. They returned in 2018 in Super Smash Bros. Ultimate

Name: Ichirin Kumoi
Summary: Ichirin Kumoi (雲居 一輪) and her guardian Unzan (雲山) are two youkai that follow and support Byakuren Hijiri. Ichirin was formerly a human, but eventually became a youkai due to being hated and rejected by humanity.

Name: Ichiryusai Madarame
Summary: Ichiryusai Madarame is the second major boss of Persona 5, and the Ruler of the Museum of Vanity.

Name: Ifrit (Final Fantasy XV)
Summary: Ifrit, also known as the Infernian, is an Astral in Final Fantasy XV. He is one of the Six and the god of fire. He plays an important role in Eos's history. His role was initially minor and shrouded in mystery, but the additions of new cutscenes, in-game bestiary and Final Fantasy XV: Episode Ardyn have shed more light to his role in Eos's past.

Name: Incineroar (Super Smash Bros)
Summary: Incineroar is a fiery hotshot newcomer to the Super Smash Bros roster, being the only new Pokemon in its latest game. But he can more than back it up with his strength in the ring, his battle prowess earning him a spot as one of the toughest combatants to ever come out of the Pokemon series, his abilities allowing him to already fight blow for blow with the veterans. Like any cat however, he has a softer side, making friends with many of the younger, smaller Pokemon outside the ring.

Name: Iron King
Summary: The Iron King (real name Jun Kun) is an antagonist in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: Isabelle (Smash Bros.)
Summary: Isabelle (しずえ, Shizue) is a playable character in Super Smash Bros. Ultimate. She is the 68th fighter overall. While she shares many moves with Villager, Isabelle is not an Echo Fighter and is instead a semi-clone.

Name: Iwanagahime
Summary: Iwanagahime was a goddess from Mt. Fuji. She used to live with her sister, Konohana-Sakuyahime, until the latter partially destroyed a mountain out of spite. This caused Iwanagahime to move to what will eventually become the Youkai Mountain.

Name: Ixis Naugus (Archie Pre-Genesis Wave)
Summary: Ixis Naugus is a major antagonist in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics. He is one of the last surviving members of the Order of Ixis, born from the fusion of three other wizards: Agunus, Nusgau, and Suguna, who fused into one being after they all entered the Sun to attain the element of fire.[1] During his time as the Kingdom of Acorn's Royal Wizard, he helped instigate events that led to the Great War, and then fled to the Zone of Silence as a safe haven where he was trapped for many years until he managed to escape after the First Robotnik War.

Name: Jack Sparrow (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Jack Sparrow is one of the most well-known pirates of the Caribbean world. Always getting into trouble, he accepts the help of Sora, Donald and Goofy on his adventures.

Name: Jafar (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Jafar is a recurring villain in the Kingdom Hearts series. Originating in Disney's Aladdin, he is a member of Maleficent's group, and appears to be her second-in-command. He is royal vizier of Agrabah who is disliked by many, mainly Aladdin and Jasmine. Two-faced and cunning, Jafar seeks the demise of Aladdin and to rule as sultan of Agrabah.

Name: Jason Lee Scott
Summary: Jason Lee Scott is the original Red Ranger of the Power Rangers series, and in a sense was the first true main character. He led the team during the struggles against Rita and even a bit into the Zedd times, but eventually left to attend a Peace Conference. He has later come back as the Gold Ranger in Zeo and as a Red Ranger in the special Forever Red.

Name: Jet the Hawk (Archie Comics)
Summary: Jet the Hawk is a Mobian hawk and expert Extreme Gear rider who deserted from the Battle Bird Armada and became the leader of the Babylon Rogues. Jet believed it was his destiny to find Babylon Garden and take the glory that would come with it, and seeks to do this in order to get back at the Armada as well. He worked temporarily for Dr. Eggman in order to escape his wrath by promising to defeat Sonic the Hedgehog, only for him and his team to be beaten by the hedgehog, Miles "Tails" Prower, and Knuckles the Echidna in a race. After this loss, he would return to his previous quest, and end up running into enemies like Team Dark, Team Rose, Team Hooligan, and his former allies in the Battle Bird Armada. After discovering the garden at last, Jet set out on a new quest: to become the fastest being on Mobius.

Name: Jigglypuff (Super Smash Bros.)
Summary: Jigglypuff (プリン, Purin), is a creature from the Pokémon series. It debuted in the series' first generation, and is considered part of the "perfect-attendance crew" throughout the entire Super Smash Bros. series.

Name: Jimizu (Anime)
Summary: Jimizu is a Yardrat from Universe 2 and a member of Team Universe 2 for the Tournament of Power. Jimizu is pretty arrogant because of his instant transmission, knowing he can do it quick enough that it is hard for him to be attacked. He, like his other teammates, hold the Kamikaze Fireballs in high esteem as seen when they rushed to their side after hearing Brianne call the attention of the other warriors, and he partook in the choir of proclaiming the song of love and victory. He also seemed enamored by the Kamikaze Fireballs after they transformed.

Name: Jiren (Manga)
Summary: Jiren is a member of the Pride Troopers who participated in the Tournament of Power under the banner of Team Universe 11 to obtain the wish of reviving his master Gicchin from the Super Dragon Balls.

Name: Joon Yorigami
Summary: Joon Yorigami is Shion's younger twin sister and a goddess of pestilence. While she inevitably leads those around her to financial ruin, she is better liked than her sister and is much more driven. Using her abilities and her skill in conning others, she gets them to use up all their money for her before abandoning them once they're completely drained of fortune and money.

Name: Josef (Final Fantasy II)
Summary: Josef is a playable character in Final Fantasy II and one of the primary protagonists of Soul of Rebirth. He was once a soldier of Palamecia, before he escaped and moved to the snowy town of Salamand. He becomes and ally to the party when the rescue to slaves from Semitt Falls. He also helps the party retrieve the Goddess Bell in Snow Cave, but loses his life to a boulder plotted by General Borghen. He then joins the afterlife where he meets Minwu and Scott; joining forces with them in the process.

Name: Julie-Su
Summary: Julie-Su is an ex-dark legionnaire and Chaotix member in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: Junko (Touhou Project)
Summary: Junko (純狐) is the sworn enemy of the Lunarians, dedicating herself to their destruction following the death of her son at the hands of Chang'e's husband. Ultimately, she used her own power to purify anything to purify herself, turning herself into the embodiment of her own hate, a Divine Spirit formed from her own emotions and willpower.

Name: Junpei Iori
Summary: Junpei Iori is a playable character in Persona 3/FES. He is best friends with the protagonist, meeting them at the start of the game and becoming a member of SEES due to being able to percieve the Dark Hour, and as such, able to summon a Persona, a fact discovered by one of the members of SEES itself.

Name: Junya Kaneshiro
Summary: I went through shit until I crawled my way out of the dregs! Now it's my turn to profit on everyone else! It doesn't matter whether you're clean or dirty! Only the clever come out on top! The strong and the smart devour the weak. That is the natural order of things. You damn brats who think you know the world through the shit you read online will make the perfect prey

Name: Justin Stewart
Summary: Justin Stewart is the blue ranger of the Turbo team. Justin a child prodigy who lost his mother at a young age. After Rocky damaged his leg, Justin went to see him in the hospital where he found the secret identities of the Power Rangers. After the Rangers received the Turbo Powers, they were missing a Blue Ranger. The Blue Turbo Power went to Justin as Rocky was in a bad shape, making him the new Blue Power Ranger. Justin would fight against Divatox and her armies for the entire season without being replaced as the first Turbo Rangers did. After the Command Center explodes, Justin doesn't join the Rangers on their way to follow Divatox to space and decides to stay on Earth but ready to help if they ever need him again.

Name: Kaguya Houraisan
Summary: Kaguya Houraisan (蓬莱山 輝夜, Houraisan Kaguya) is the former princess of the Moon, banished to Earth for consuming the Hourai Elixir to become immortal. There, she dwelt among the humans and eventually grew to love her new home. Her beauty attracted many suitors, but she refused to marry any of them if they failed to accomplish one of her Five Impossible Requests. Eventually, when the Lunarians forgave her and attempted to retrieve her, she rejected Lunarian society in favor of Earth and escaped with Eirin Yagokoro to the hidden mansion of Eientei.

Name: Kairi (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Kairi is a longtime friend of both Sora and Riku and one of the Seven Princesses of Heart. She was raised by her grandmother in Radiant Garden but was sent to the Destiny Islands after Radiant Garden became shrouded in Darkness. As the Destiny Islands succumbed to the Darkness, her body vanished as she tried to meet up with Sora, leaving her heart behind in her friend, who set out on a journey to reunite with her and Riku.

Name: Kana Anaberal
Summary: Kana Anaberal (カナ・アナベラル Kana anaberaru) is a poltergeist created by a mentally unstable girl, and haunts a huge mansion. Because its owner no longer fears her from growing used to it, she thinks of moving, wondering what all the fuss is about. She is a playable character in Phantasmagoria of Dim. Dream.

Name: Kanako Yasaka
Summary: Kanako Yasaka (八坂 神奈子) is the current goddess of the Moriya Shrine, following her victory over Suwako during the Great Suwa War, thousands of years in the past. Due to her dependence on faith, which was scarce in the Outside World, she moved her shrine to Gensokyo so she could collect it more easily.

Name: Kasen Ibaraki
Summary: Kasen Ibaraki (茨木 華扇, Ibaraki Kasen) is a mysterious self-proclaimed hermit living in the mountains. She can often be seen dispensing advice and knowledge to Reimu Hakurei, Marisa Kirisame, and Sanae Kochiya.

Name: Keiki Haniyasushin
Summary: Keiki Haniyasushin (埴安神 袿姫 Haniyasushin Keiki) is a god summoned by human spirits and acts as the main antagonist of Wily Beast and Weakest Creature.

Name: Keine Kamishirasawa
Summary: Keine Kamishirasawa (上白沢 慧音, Kamishirasawa Keine) is a were-hakutaku who acts as the guardian of the Human Village.

Name: Ken (Super Smash Bros.)
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:KenIsReadyForYaSoBringItOn.ogg

Name: Ken Amada
Summary: Ken Amada is a Playable Character in Persona 3. Growing up only with his mother, one night his mother died in an accident where Shinjiro Aragaki's Persona went out of control, killing her. Swearing revenge and unable to get anyone to believe him due to the nature of the Dark Hour, Ken joins SEES 2 years later to kill Shinjiro. During a Full Moon Operation, Shinjiro gave his life to save Ken from a bullet from Takaya Sakaki; causing Ken to feel remorse over his plot to take his life. By Persona 4 Arena Ultimax, Ken had further matured into a responsible young man, choosing to live for both his Mother and Shinjiro's sake, becoming an auxiliary member for Mitsuru's Shadow Operatives.

Name: Kettol (Anime)
Summary: Kettol (ケットル Kettoru) is a member of the Pride Troopers who participates in the Tournament of Power.

Name: Kikuri
Summary: Kikuri is a mysterious enemy that faces Reimu Hakurei.

Name: Kim Kaphwan (The King of Fighters)
Key: '''Prologue Chapter (KOF '94) ''' | '''Chapter of Orochi Saga (KOF '95 to KOF '97)''' | '''Chapter of NESTS Saga (KOF '99 to KOF 2001)''' | '''Chapter of Ash Saga (KOF 2003 to KOF XIII)'''
Summary: nan

Name: King K. Rool (Smash Bros.)
Summary: King K. Rool is the 67th fighter to be added to Super Smash Bros. Ultimate. In Adventure mode, he, along with everyone else besides Kirby, was incapacitated. When Galeem was defeated, he was captured by Dharkon.

Name: King Sombra
Summary: King Sombra is the fourth villain of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic, and acts as the antagonist of the Season 3 premiere.

Name: King Thorax
Summary: King Thorax is a character in My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Kingdom Hearts (Entity)
Key: '''Kingdom Hearts of Worlds (KHI)''' | '''True Kingdom Hearts (KHBbS and KHIII)'''
Summary: Kingdom Hearts (キングダムハーツ Kingudamu Hātsu) is one of the major entities in the Kingdom Hearts universe. It is the heart of all worlds, and the source of ultimate power and wisdom. It can be seen as the heart of everything. Due to its great significance, it has repeatedly been sought by the villains of the Kingdom Hearts series, in particular the series's main antagonist, Xehanort.

Name: Kirby
Summary: First you draw a circle, Then you dot the eyes. Add a great big smile And presto, it's Kirby!

Name: Kirby (Smash Bros.)
Summary: Tier: High 6-A, higher with Final Smash | Low 2-C, higher with Final Smash

Name: Knuckles the Echidna (Archie Pre-Genesis Wave)
Summary: Knuckles is one of the primary protagonists who stands as the last guardian of Angel Island and leader of the Chaotix in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: Kogasa Tatara
Summary: Kogasa Tatara (多々良 小傘 Tatara Kogasa) is a subspecies of the Tsukumogami, a Karakasa obake. Originally coming from the Outside World, she ended up in Gensokyo where she became a Youkai that feeds on fear. Although with time passing, humans became less scared and she was left desperately trying to scare humans.

Name: Koichiarator (Anime)
Summary: Koichiarator is a triple fusion of the Universe 3 robots Koitsukai, Panchia, and Bollarator.

Name: Koishi Komeiji
Summary: Koishi Komeiji (古明地 こいし) is Satori Komeiji's younger sister. To escape the fear and hatred which other beings feel towards the satori species, she attempted to destroy her mind-reading ability by closing her Third Eye. However, this had the side effect of sealing away her own conscious mind, causing her to lose all thoughts and motives; she could no longer be hated, but neither could she be loved, or even remembered by people who saw her.

Name: Koitsukai (Anime)
Summary: Koitsukai is a warrior from Universe 3 and a member of Team Universe 3.

Name: Komachi Onozuka
Summary: Komachi Onozuka (小野塚 小町) is a lazy shinigami who ferries souls across the Sanzu River and works for Eiki Shiki, Yamaxanadu. While she is a slacker and a slow worker, she tends to copy her boss' habit of lecturing others and has little else to talk about besides suicide and other death-related horrors.

Name: Konngara
Summary: Konngara is one of the Final Bosses of Highly Responsive to Prayers. It is found in the Hell route and is likely the one behind the shrine's destruction.

Name: Konohana-Sakuyahime
Summary: Konohana-Sakuyahime is the Goddess of Volcanoes in Gensokyo. She resides on Mt. Fuji. Years ago, a group of humans came to her mountain to drop a jar into the volcano. Unfortunately, the jar contained the Hourai Elixir, which would trigger the volcano's eruption hard enough that not even Sakuyahime could stop it. As such, she convinced the humans to not drop it in the volcano. As a precaution, she also murdered most of them in their sleep. The two survivors had to carry away the Elixir, although one of them killed the other and took the Elixir for themselves. Said person will go on to become Fujiwara no Mokou.

Name: Koromaru
Summary: Koromaru is a playable character in Persona 3/FES. Koromaru is an albino Shiba Inu. When he joined SEES, he was given a special Evoker for dogs, a metallic collar around his neck. He has a red armband on his left arm, a miniature white t-shirt and very small angel-esque wings on his back.

Name: Kosuzu Motoori
Summary: Kosuzu Motoori (本居 小鈴, Motoori Kosuzu) is the main character of the print work Forbidden Scrollery. She lives in the Human Village and serves as a worker of the Suzunaan book renter.

Name: Kotohime
Summary: Kotohime (小兎姫) is a character who appears in Phantasmagoria of Dim. Dream. While she should be a princess, she has an odd personality that doesn't allow her to meet people often. She finds an interest in collecting things that normal people aren't interested in.

Name: Kraken (Final Fantasy I)
Summary: Kraken is the fiend of water. He is the squid like beast that appears in the Sunken Shrine. The Warriors of Light must defeat him to awaken the Water Crystal.

Name: Krillin (DBS Anime)
Summary: Krillin or Kuririn (クリリン, Kuririn?) is a former monk of the Orin Temple who ran away to train under Master Roshi, eventually doing so alongside Son Goku, who would grow to become his best friend.

Name: Kunikazu Okumura
Summary: Kunikazu Okumura is the fourth major boss of Persona 5, and the Ruler of the Space Station of Greed.

Name: Kurt Zisa
Summary: Kurt Zisa is an Emblem that is found in the North American, PAL, and Kingdom Hearts Final Mix versions of Kingdom Hearts. It is one of the bosses in Agrabah.

Name: Kurumi (Touhou Project)
Summary: Kurumi is a vampire and gatekeeper found at the entrance to the Lake of Blood, a body of water at the center of a mountain. She appears as the second stage boss of Lotus Land Story.

Name: Kutaka Niwatari
Summary: Kutaka Niwatari (庭渡 久侘歌 Niwatari Kutaka) is a god of chickens and a guard of Hell. She lives in a spring atop the Youkai Mountain but goes to Higan for her job of overseeing the gateway to otherworlds such as Hell under the yama's oversight. Kutaka first appeared as the stage 3 midboss and boss in Wily Beast and Weakest Creature, attempting to dissuade the protagonist from entering Hell. She speaks in a polite, somewhat refined manner, and despite already being authorized to let the protagonist through, she takes extra care to test the protagonist's strength out of concern for their well-being.

Name: Kyo Kusanagi
Key: '''Prologue Chapter (KOF '94)''' | '''Chapter of Orochi Saga (KOF '95 to KOF '97)''' | '''Chapter of NESTS Saga (KOF '99 to KOF 2001)''' | '''KOF Sky Stage''' | '''Chapter of Ash Saga (KOF 2003 to KOF XIII)'''
Summary: nan

Name: Lara-Su
Summary: Lara-Su was Knuckles’s and Julie-Su's daughter from the alternate future timeline known as Light Mobius. She was initially at odds with her father, who refused to allow her to become a Guardian. Eventually, he relented however, only for that future to be warped almost beyond recognition by an alteration of history from King Sonic. Lara-Su and a few others recalled the rightful timeline, and together fought the despotic King Shadow. Lara-Su herself ended the fight by imprisoning him with Chaos Control. Serving as a Guardian for five years, she also became a member of the Future Freedom Fighters when Shadow returned.

Name: Larxene
Key: '''Up to Dream Drop Distance''' | '''Kingdom Hearts III'''
Summary: Larxene, the Savage Nymph (非情の妖姫 Hijō no Yōki?, lit. Callous Vixen), is Rank XII within Organization XIII. Larxene is the group's only female member, and also has a very sadistic nature. She controls lightning and uses it to thrash opponents with rapid attacks while also attacking them with her weapons: electrified throwing knives.

Name: Leanbow
Summary: Leanbow is Udonna's husband, Bowen's father (AKA Nick Russel), and the mentor of Daggeron and Calindor. He was known for his honor and valor which Calindor resented. As a Mystic, he can assume "Ancient Mystic Mode", resembling a red/purple fiery demon wielding a sword and shield. Twenty years prior to the series, Leanbow led the other Mystics in the Great Battle against the Supreme Master of the Underworld, and his Forces of Darkness led by Morticon in order to prevent them entering the human realm. The forces of good magic eventually forced the Forces of Darkness through the Gate of the Underworld, with Leanbow personally taking on Morticon at one point. In order to keep the Forces of Darkness from escaping the Underworld, he held back the Darkness hordes from the Gate while Niella the Gatekeeper sealed both it and Leanbow into the Underworld.

Name: Leon (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Squall Leonhart is a supporting character in the Kingdom Hearts series and leader of both the Heartless Resistance and the Hollow Bastion Restoration Committee. After the destruction of his world by the Heartless, he changed his name to "Leon" in an attempt to amend for his mistakes. Leon is twenty-five years old at the beginning of Kingdom Hearts and Kingdom Hearts: Chain of Memories and twenty-six during the events of Kingdom Hearts II. He is several years older than in Final Fantasy VIII to match the ages of the other Final Fantasy characters he appears alongside with. Along with Yuffie, Aerith and Cid, Leon came from Hollow Bastion and fled to Traverse Town when Maleficent took over the castle. Leon helps Sora with advice and information in the first game, and in Kingdom Hearts: Chain of Memories teaches the player many basic concepts for the card-based battle system. In the original game, a special gummi ship blueprint called Leon can be obtained by defeating 4000 Heartless and talking to Geppetto.

Name: Leviathan (Final Fantasy XV)
Summary: Leviathan is is one of the six Astrals of Eos in Final Fantasy XV. She is a colossal sea serpent who controls water, slumbering under the waters of Altissia. She is looked upon with both fear and respect. Prince Noctis forges a pact with Leviathan in Chapter 9.

Name: Leviathan (Final Fantasy)
Key: '''Final Fantasy III''' | '''Final Fantasy IV''' | '''Final Fantasy V'''
Summary: A recurring summon and the avatar of water, Leviathan is a force to be feared in every one of his appearances as both an ally and an enemy. His personality and intelligence widely varies across all of his appearances, but all grow to respect The Sea King in all of his glory.

Name: Lexaeus
Summary: Lexaeus, the is the Nobody of Aeleus and is Rank V within the original Organization XIII. True to his title as the "Silent Hero", Lexaeus is a taciturn and somewhat aloof individual but is nevertheless honorable and loyal to the few he considers his allies. Lexaeus holds a particularly close friendship with Zexion, being the one person his is willing to confide in and is suspicious of the other members of the Organization.

Name: Lich (Final Fantasy I)
Summary: Lich is the fiend of Earth and the first of the four fiends fought by the Warriors of Light. He rests at the bottom of Earthgift Shrine and appears to be a skeleton of the undead.

Name: Lord Tirek
Summary: Lord Tirek is the sixth main villain of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic, acting as the main antagonist for the season four finale Twilight's Kingdom.

Name: Lord Tsukuyomi
Summary: Lord Tsukuyomi is the leader and ruler of the Lunar Capital. Very little is known about him.

Name: Louise (Touhou Project)
Summary: Louise is one of many demons from Makai, serving as the Stage 2 boss of Mystic Square, and later as a mid-boss of Stage 4.

Name: Lucina (Super Smash Bros.)
Summary: Lucina (ルキナ, Lucina) is one of the primary protagonists of Fire Emblem: Awakening, being the daughter of Chrom who traveled into the past in order to save her future from disaster. She was first introduced in Super Smash Bros. for Nintendo 3DS/Wii U, and has since appeared in Super Smash Bros. Ultimate as well.

Name: Luigi
Summary: Luigi is Mario's younger, taller, and thinner twin brother. He is a major protagonist of the Mario series. Luigi has helped and fought alongside his brother on many occasions.

Name: Lumina (Final Fantasy)
Summary: Lumina is a major supporting character in Lightning Returns: Final Fantasy XIII. She resembles Serah Farron in appearance and crosses paths with Lightning during her quest to save the world, at times appearing as a friend and other times as an adversary.

Name: Lunar Capital
Key: '''Basic Infantry | Higher Technology and High Ranking Members | Gods'''
Summary: The Lunar Capital (月の都, Tsuki no Miyako) is an extremely powerful and advanced civilization on the Moon of the Touhou Project universe. They used to be humans living on Earth. However, their leader, Lord Tsukuyomi, wanted him and his kind to escape the impurity of Earth. They did so by colonizing the moon, an otherwise untouched and pure land, where they could live a completely pure life.

Name: Luxord
Summary: Luxord, the Gambler of Fate (運命を賭す者 Unmei o Tosumono?), is Rank X within the original Organization XIII. He possesses the power of time manipulation and uses his ability to force his opponents to play timed games, with unfortunate consequences if they cannot learn the rules and lose. He commands the Gambler Nobodies.

Name: Mai (Touhou Project)
Summary: Mai is, along with Yuki, a witch who resides in Makai and with Yuki, serves as one of two bosses in Mystic Square's fourth stage.

Name: Maji Kayo (Anime)
Summary: Maji Kayo is a fighter from Universe 3 for the Tournament of Power.

Name: Majin Buu
Summary: nan

Name: Majin Buu (DBS Manga)
Summary: Majin Buu is an extremely ancient creature, who has been controlled by the evil wizard Bibidi with the purpose of ruling the universe.

Name: Makoto Niijima
Summary: There are too many incidents in this country that are never brought to light. That host was one. Villains who prey on the hearts of the weak with cowardly, legally questionable methods... My father risked his life trying to catch a group of those people. I will never forgive them. But I won't be able to eradicate them all on my own... Instead, I want to head an organization that will destroy the lawless and help rescue victims. (The Player chooses) Your father would be proud. I hope so... That is the justice I aim for. I also believe it will be a continuation of my father's legacy

Name: Makoto Yuki
Summary: Makoto Yuki is the protagonist of Persona 3/FES/Portable. He is a transfer student enrolling in Gekkoukan High School in Iwatodai City. He is an orphan whose parents died on the Moonlight Bridge in their car during a fatal incident a decade before the events of the game. He has dark blue hair unkempt at the front, blue eyes, and a light build, being shorter than average. His bangs cover his right eye. He is often shown with his hands in his pockets. He is very stoic, reserved, and calm, gathered by the fact that he remains unmoved even when guns are pointed at him. He appears very introverted, distant, and aloof since he only observes the conversations of his party members and only speaks when someone is directed at him for his opinion on the matter.

Name: Maleficent (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Aqua: Try all you want but you'll never defeat a heart filled with light. Maleficent: Perhaps. But remember one thing—as long as there is light, there will be darkness. And in time, many more will be drawn to it. Then they will all belong to me!

Name: Mamizou Futatsuiwa
Summary: Mamizou Futatsuiwa (二ッ岩 マミゾウ) is a Bake-danuki summoned by Nue Houjuu to act as the Myouren Temple's trump card against Toyosatomimi no Miko.

Name: Mammoth Mogul
Summary: IN: Then its true! Your power, your knowledge, it must mean...! MM: Yes, Naugus. I was once known as Ixis Mogul.

Name: Marilith (Final Fantasy I)
Summary: Marilith is the Fiend of Fire. She appears in Mount Gulg as a woman with the lower body of a snake and has six arms, each wielding a sword.

Name: Mario (Super Smash Bros.)
Summary: Mario (マリオ, Mario) is the eponymous protagonist of the Mario series. Unanimously viewed as the mascot of Nintendo, Mario is said to be the most well-known and most popular video game character in the world, having appeared in over 200 video games. As a member of the "perfect-attendance crew", Mario has been featured as a playable character in every installment of the Super Smash Bros. series.

Name: Marisa Kirisame
Summary: Marisa Kirisame is an "ordinary" human magician specializing in flashy heat and light-based magic, and the secondary protagonist of the Touhou Project. She is a notorious and proud thief and has built herself up as a great magician through nothing but hard work and dedication to her craft.

Name: Marluxia
Summary: Marluxia, the Graceful Assassin (優雅なる凶刃 Yūga-naru Kyōjin, lit.Graceful Assassin's Blade), is Rank XI within Organization XIII, the lord of Castle Oblivion and the main antagonist of Sora's story in Kingdom Hearts: Chain of Memories. He controls flowers, and uses his control to command beams of destructive energy from flower-themed minions, bombard the opponent with flurries of petals, and to attack opponents with his massive scythe.

Name: Marth (Super Smash Bros.)
Summary: Marth (マルス, Marth; formerly translated as Mars prior to Super Smash Bros. Melee) is the main protagonist of the first game in the long-running Fire Emblem franchise, Fire Emblem: Shadow Dragon and the Blade of Light, and has been an extremely important presence throughout the entire series. He has made an appearance in every entry of Super Smash Bros. franchise ever since his premiere appearance in Super Smash Bros. Melee)

Name: Martin Mertens
Summary: Martin Mertens, also formerly known as Mr. M, is Finn's biological father. Billy calls him "Dad the Human", similar to Finn's title "Finn the Human". He was first revealed in the episode "Billy's Bucket List".

Name: Megabug
Summary: Megabug is a dragon-like creature of pure energy. It happens to be aberration of time and space from the dimensional vortex that altered the fabric of Mario's world, created from the Rabbids' Time Washing Machine after a blast of the SuperMerge visor. Initially, appearing as a blue dimensional rift, it slowly grows larger and changes colors from the energy it absorbs from the all the Rabbids-fused enemies Mario and his allies defeated, which happened to be created by Spawny under Bowser Jr.'s command. It eventually gains form and absorbs Spawny and later Bowser to form MegaDragonBowser. After Mario, his friends, and their Rabbid counterparts teamed up and defeated it, the monstrosity disappeared and the rift along with it, making the world safe once more.

Name: Meira
Summary: Meira is a swordswoman from Gensokyo. She came to the Hakurei Shrine to steal the Hakurei's power, but was defeated.

Name: Mephiles the Dark (Archie Comics)
Summary: Mephiles the Dark is a character mentioned in the Sonic the Hedgehog Encyclopedia published by Archie Comics.

Name: Merlin (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Merlin is a recurring character in the Kingdom Hearts series. He is a wizard who teaches Sora in the arts of magic when the boy appears in Traverse Town.

Name: Messiah (Persona)
Summary: Messiah is the ultimate Persona of Persona 3's protagonist, Makoto Yuki, created by fusing his initial Persona Orpheus, and Thanatos together.

Name: Meta Knight
Summary: Nova: "READY. -> I WILL GRANT YOU ONE WISH... ->" Meta Knight: "My one wish is to become stronger... So I wish to fight... the greatest warrior in the galaxy!

Name: Metal Sonic v3.0 (Archie Comics)
Summary: Metal Sonic (v3.0) is an antagonist in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: Mewtwo (Super Smash Bros)
Summary: Mewtwo is one of the oldest Pokémon representatives in Super Smash Bros, debuting in Super Smash Bros: Melee. He was absent for the next game, Brawl, replaced by a functionally identical character, as well as the next game before he was finally added back into the series in the form of free DLC by popular demand, and remains in the series to this day.

Name: Mighty the Armadillo (Archie Pre-Genesis Wave)
Summary: Mighty the Armadillo is a Mobian eastern armadillo who took up residence in the mountains of Angel Island, though he was born planet-side in the Kingdom of Mercia. He has known Sonic the Hedgehog since his childhood, but they wouldn't meet again for roughly six years after their first adventure. After spending much of his youth wandering, he was brought to the Floating Island by Knuckles the Echidna and Vector the Crocodile. Thus, he became one of the original members of the Chaotix.

Name: Mii Fighter
Summary: The Mii Fighters are warriors based on the customizable Mii avatars.

Name: Mima
Summary: Mima (魅魔) is a vengeful spirit that haunts the area around the Hakurei Shrine in the PC-98 canon. Though she is called an evil spirit, she is not the same variety as the ones that appear in Subterranean Animism and Wild and Horned Hermit. She is, in reality, extremely strong, and she is very confident in her combat and magical abilities. Originally, she is sealed in the hokora attached to the shrine, but she manages to repeatedly break free of the seal.

Name: Mini-Hakkero
Summary: The Mini-Hakkero is a magical furnace currently possessed by Marisa Kirisame. The mini-hakkero was given to her by Rinnosuke Morichika in Curiosities of Lotus Asia. It's not an actual weapon though.

Name: Ministry of Right and Wrong
Summary: The Ministry of Right and Wrong is the organization that manages the entire system regarding Souls and the afterlife in the Touhou Project series. Created in response to humanity's growing numbers, it is mainly composed of the many judges who deal with the deceased and of the leaders of Heaven, the Netherworld and the many hells.

Name: Minoriko Aki
Summary: Minoriko Aki is one of the two goddesses of autumn. Her job is to make harvest fruitful by helping farmers with their plantations.

Name: Mitsuru Kirijo
Summary: Mitsuru Kirijo is the only child of the current head of the Kirijo Group, Takeharu Kirijo. She is also the Gekkoukan High School’s valedictorian and student council president as well as the leader of the Specialized Extracurricular Execution Squad (S.E.E.S.), an organization composed of Persona users to battle Shadows during the Dark Hour.

Name: Mizue no Uranoshimako
Summary: Mizue no Uranoshimako was a human fisherman from Earth, who accidentally found himself on the Moon. Believing it to be the Dragon Palace, he stayed there for three years before being sent to his world, but three hundred years into the future. When he arrived, everyone he knew had disappeared, and no one believed his stories about the Dragon Palace. In despair, he opened up the box that was gifted to him, which made him age all of his 300 skipped years. Despite his old age, rumors about the old man's visit to the Dragon Palace spread around the land, eventually reaching the Emperor's ear. However, Uranoshimako had already died by the time the Emperor got to him. A shrine was built in his name, and he eventually became a god.

Name: Monkey Khan
Summary: Monkey Khan, originally named Ken Khan, is a character that appears in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: Mononobe no Futo
Summary: Mononobe no Futo (物部 布都) is a Shikaisen, a Taoist Hermit and a loyal servant of Toyosatomimi no Miko.

Name: Morgana (Persona)
Key: '''Beginning of the game''' | '''Early Game''' | '''Mid Game''' | '''Late Game''' | '''End Game'''
Summary: Morgana is a playable character in Persona 5.

Name: Moro
Summary: Moro is a powerful wizard who threatened Universe 7 about ten million years ago. His power proved to be so great that the Grand Supreme Kai needed to sacrifice his own godly power in order to seal him away. Now that his power has been returned after millions of years of imprisonment, Moro once again poses a threat to the Universe.

Name: Mr. Game & Watch
Summary: Mr. Game & Watch is an inhabitant of a completely flat world called Flat Zone. He does various chores there, varying from cooking to fighting a giant octopus and even saving a princess. However, the 2D composition of his body made him a prime target for Tabuu's evil plan. He was captured by Tabuu and convinced to produce the Subspace Army for him. He also was the one controlling the Halberd. He was later stopped by Peach and co. and brought back on their side by giving him an umbrella.

Name: Mugetsu
Summary: Mugetsu (夢月) is the first Extra Stage boss of Lotus Land Story and possibly the creator of a mysterious dream world in which Reimu Hakurei and Marisa Kirisame stumbled upon. She is the younger sister of Gengetsu and appears to be dressed as a maid of some sort, but according to the music comments of her theme "Illusion of a Maid ~ Icemilk Magic" in Lotus Land Story, she is probably not a maid. Not much is known about her or her sister as they serve no relevance to the plot.

Name: Ness (Super Smash Bros.)
Summary: Ness is a character that first appeared in EarthBound (or Mother 2 in Japan) and eventually became famous thanks to his appearance in the very first Super Smash Bros game (mostly in the U.S).

Name: Nicole the Holo-Lynx (Archie Pre-Genesis Wave)
Summary: Nicole, also NICOLE, is the assistant of Princess Sally and the one who governs New Mobotropolis in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: Nicole Watterson
Summary: Nicole Watterson is one of the main characters in The Amazing World of Gumball. Nicole is the mother of the Watterson family. She is the only truly responsible member of the family. She is very dedicated to her family, and would do anything in her power to keep them comfortable and safe.

Name: Nue Houjuu
Summary: Nue Houjuu (封獣 ぬえ) is said to be one of the most mysterious and feared youkai in many years, yet has been defeated by humans many times. There are many different legends according to her appearance because she hides her "true form". At some point, she was sealed underground, but after the events of Subterranean Animism, she resurfaced back in Gensokyo.

Name: Nyarlathotep (VShojo Mythos)
Summary: Nyarlathotep is the emissary sent by Azathoth to light the beacon of chaos and bring an end to existence. Before heading to the farthest reaches of the expanse, she created a companion named Goro from the cosmic dust surrounding her. Goro was the one to give her the nickname, "Nyan." Once Nyan stumbled upon Earth, she began harvesting the sanity of humans to fuel the beacon. Nature itself rose to stop Nyan from reawakening her creators, stealing her powers and freezing her beneath the East Siberian Sea.

Name: Occult Balls
Summary: The Occult Balls are a collection of objects found in a variety of Mystery Spots all over the world. Much like the Mystery Spots they emerged from, these Occult Balls' main purpose is to increase the spiritual strength of something. Unlike these spots, however, these objects mainly increases the strength of beliefs around them, causing those to be manifested in the real world. Thus, they are the main cause of the Urban Legends incident of Gensokyo. However, one of them was different and stronger than the rest. It was the Lunar Capital Ball, created by Sagume Kishin. This ball was part of a plan by the Lunarians to move the Capital in Gensokyo by spreading the rumor of NASA hiding what they saw on the Moon, thus making the Capital manifest itself in Gensokyo.

Name: Okina Matara
Summary: Okina Matara (摩多羅 隠岐奈, Matara Okina) is a secret god who lurks behind all things, hiding in plain sight behind a number of public faces and disguises, such as an Earth Mother Goddess, a god of Noh, a god of the stars, a god of silkworm breeding, a god of impediments, and a god of burakumin. No one knows her true identity, but she was one of the sages who helped create Gensokyo in the past. Now, living in the Outside World, she protects Gensokyo and maintains its balance.

Name: Optimus Prime (IDW)
Summary: Question One: In whose interest do you exercise your power?

Name: Orange (Touhou Project)
Summary: Orange is the first boss enemy encountered in Touhou 4, Lotus Land Story. Though she may be a boss opponent, she is defeated easily by the protagonist as they move on to the Lake of Blood ahead.

Name: Patchouli Knowledge
Summary: Patchouli Knowledge is a very smart, anemic and asthmatic magician from the Scarlet Devil Mansion. As opposed to the rest of the inhabitants, she is neither an employee or relative of Remilia Scarlet, instead being a close friend whose role is to cause and solve problems. She spends most of her time in the mansion's library reading and writing magic books. It seems that she's capable of very powerful magic of all kinds, using many elements in a single spell, but due to her anemia, asthma and general poor health she's often unable to recite her spells.

Name: Phantom (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: The Phantom is an Emblem Heartless that is found in the first Kingdom Hearts Game. It is one of the bosses at Neverland. While Phantom is in possession of the Clock Tower, the hourly treasures cannot be obtained.

Name: Phantoms (Touhou Project)
Summary: Phantoms are a kind of spirit in the Touhou Project series. They are the embodiment of the spirits of things, be it plants, humans or otherwise. They are not to be confused with ghosts.

Name: Pharynx
Summary: Pharynx a minion in the My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic series.

Name: Pichu (Super Smash Bros.)
Summary: Pichu is a playable character in Super Smash Bros. Melee and Super Smash Bros. Ultimate, as well as the pre-evolved form of Pikachu.

Name: Pikachu (Super Smash Bros.)
Summary: Pikachu (ピカチュウ, Pikachu) is a character from the Pokémon series, often serving as the mascot of the entire franchise. Being a member of the "perfect attendance crew," he has appeared in every Super Smash Bros. game to date.

Name: Pinkie Pie
Key: '''Base Form''' | '''Post-bonding with Chaosville''' | '''With Chaos Magic''' | '''Elements of Harmony/Magic of Friendship''' | '''Rainbow Power'''
Summary: Pinkie Pie is one of the main protagonists of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Pinkie Pie (Human World)
Summary: Pinkie Pie is one of the main characters of My Little Pony Equestria Girls, and represents the Element of Laughter.

Name: Piranha Plant (Smash Bros.)
Summary: Piranha Plant (パックンフラワー, Packun Flower) is a playable character in Super Smash Bros. Ultimate. Revealed alongside Ken and Incineroar on November 1st, 2018, it is the first DLC character in Ultimate, and was made available for purchase on February 1st, 2019. However, it was made available at no cost as early as January 29th, 2019 for players who purchased the digital version of Ultimate or registered their physical version with My Nintendo by January 31st, 2019. Piranha Plant is not part of either Fighters Pass, making it the only DLC character with this distinction. Piranha Plant is classified as Fighter #70.

Name: Plunderseeds
Summary: The Plunderseeds were a weapon used by Discord over 1000 years ago to try and capture Princess Celestia and Princess Luna before they could use the Elements of Harmony to defeat him. However, the Tree of Harmony had enough magic inside of it to keep the seeds from growing up, foiling Discord's plan.

Name: Pokémon Trainer (Super Smash Bros)
Summary: The Pokémon Trainer, alongside Pikachu itself, is the main Pokémon representative in Super Smash Bros. They also serve as the Super Smash Bros universe's Pokémon League Champion, retaining his title since Brawl.

Name: Popeye
Summary: First introduced Dice Island, a story arc in the comic strip Thimble Theater in 1928, Popeye the Sailor Man would later become the main focus of the strip, as well becoming as one of the most iconic comic and cartoon characters of all time. "Borned to the sea" near the bay of Santa Monica, Popeyes' childhood was hard. The ship he was born on was rocked by a massive typhoon just moments after his birth, though his family was ultimately unharmed by the event. Growing up, both his father, "Poopdeck Pappy" and his unnamed mother left his life at a young age. Eventually, Popeye decided to join the military. Despite his rough and gruff appearance, Popeye was a good guy who hated bullies and defended the weak.

Name: Power Rings (Archie Comics)
Summary: Power Rings, also called Magic Rings, are objects that appear in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: Princess Cadance
Summary: Princess Cadance is a secondary character in My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Princess Celestia
Summary: Princess Celestia is a major character in My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic and is one of the many Alicorns seen in the series, so far. She is Twilight Sparkle's mentor and the one responsible for raising the sun, every day. Celestia rules over all of Equestria and is portrayed as a wise, kind, and beloved leader.

Name: Princess Luna
Key: '''Princess Luna/Nightmare Moon''' | '''Vice Principal Luna (Equestria Girls counterpart)'''
Summary: Princess Luna is a former antagonist and recurring character in My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Prismo
Summary: Prismo is a major recurring character in Adventure Time. He is the cosmic wish granter and sole resident of the Time Room, a timeless realm at the center of the multiverse. Although considered to be an all-powerful deity capable of creating and destroying timelines with a mere command, Prismo is a remarkably laid back and generally jovial being whose always friendly to those who seek his wishes, even befriending them and throwing parties for them.

Name: Pure Hearts
Summary: Tier: 2-A

Name: Queen Chrysalis
Summary: Queen Chrysalis is the third main villain in My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: R.O.B. (Smash Bros.)
Summary: R.O.B. (Robotic Operating Buddy) is a playable character in the Super Smash Bros series.

Name: Rabanra
Summary: Rabanra (ラバンラ Rabanra) is a warrior from Dragon Ball's Universe 2, a member of Team Universe 2, and an attendant to the Kamikaze Fireballs.

Name: Raiko Horikawa
Summary: Raiko Horikawa is one of the Tsukumogami created by the Miracle Mallet incident. While enjoying her new power, she soon realized that her existence was temporary, due to the Mallet's power eventually fading away. Thus, she took a risky move and changed her own drums to obtain a new power source.

Name: Rainbow Dash
Key: '''Base Form''' | '''Elements of Harmony/Magic of Friendship''' | '''Rainbow Power'''
Summary: Rainbow Dash is one of the main protagonists of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Rainbow Dash (Human World)
Summary: Rainbow Dash is one of the main characters in My Little Pony Equestria Girls.

Name: Rainbow Power
Summary: Tier: 2-A, possibly Low 1-C

Name: Ramza Beoulve
Summary: Ramza Beoulve, also known as Ramza Lugria, is the main protagonist in Final Fantasy Tactics. Third son of House Beoulve, son of Barbaneth Beoulve and a commoner woman of the Lugria family, Ramza is the younger half-brother of Dycedarg and Zalbaag, and the full older sibling of Alma.

Name: Ran Yakumo
Summary: Ran Yakumo (八雲 藍, Yakumo Ran) is an unknown shikigami created by Yukari Yakumo that has possessed the body of a nine-tailed kitsune as long as she has been seen. None of the kitsune's original consciousness has ever been stated to be present. She obtained the powers and abilities of this unnamed kitsune by possessing her. Kitsune grow one extra tail per 100 years that they live. The possessed kitsune's nine tails showcases her great power and experience and her approaching divinity. It is not shown how she was created, or how she possessed the kitsune, but she is a very powerful youkai, even capable of owning a shikigami of her own.

Name: Rarity
Key: '''Unicorn Form''' | '''Possessed by a Spell Book''' | '''Elements of Harmony/Magic of Friendship''' | '''Rainbow Power'''
Summary: Rarity is one of the main protagonist of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Rarity (Human World)
Summary: Rarity is one of the main characters of My Little Pony Equestria Girls, and represents the Element of Generosity.

Name: Ravus Nox Fleuret
Summary: Ravus Nox Fleuret is a character in the Final Fantasy XV Universe, being a minor antagonist in the feature film Kingsglaive: Final Fantasy XV and the secondary antagonist in Final Fantasy XV. The older brother of Lunafreya Nox Fleuret, he is the former prince of Tenebrae and high commander of the Imperial Army of Niflheim.

Name: Regis Lucis Caelum
Summary: Regis Lucis Caelum is a major character in the Final Fantasy XV Universe, his most major appearance being in the feature film Kingsglaive: Final Fantasy XV. He is the main protagonist of A King's Tale: Final Fantasy XV, and also appears in Final Fantasy XV. He appears as a boss in Final Fantasy XV: Episode Ardyn.

Name: Reimu Hakurei
Summary: Reimu Hakurei is the Shrine Maiden of the Hakurei Shrine and the main protagonist of the Touhou series alongside her friend, Marisa Kirisame. She is exceptionally talented and gifted, but her laziness makes her hate training.

Name: Reisen Udongein Inaba
Summary: Reisen Udongein Inaba is a moon rabbit who deserted the Lunar Capital during the "Lunar War" that began in 1969, after the Apollo 11 "invasion". Arriving in Gensokyo, she stumbled upon the infamous fugitives Kaguya Houraisan and Eirin Yagokoro, and in exchange for asylum in Eientei, she swore loyalty to them.

Name: Remilia Scarlet
Summary: Remilia Scarlet is the head of the Scarlet Devil Mansion, the mistress of Sakuya and Meiling, a close friend of Patchouli's, and the older sister of Flandre Scarlet. While she often seems childish and non-threatening, she is incredibly strong and is known across Gensokyo as the "Scarlet Devil".

Name: Richard Watterson
Summary: Richard Watterson is one of the main characters in The Amazing World of Gumball. He serves the role of the father in the Watterson family. Unlike the traditional father, however, Richard is not wise, nor is he a good role model for his children in any way. Despite his misguided advice and uncouth mannerisms, Richard has good intentions and loves his family all the same.

Name: Rick (Kirby)
Summary: Rick is a friendly and energetic hamster that is a close friend with Kirby. He is one of the original three Animal Friends appearing Kirby's Dream Land 2, making major appearances in classic games of the series.

Name: Rika (Touhou Project)
Key: '''Rika by herself''' | '''Flower Tank/Shrine Tank''' | '''Evil Eye Sigma'''
Summary: Rika is a human engineer and first boss of Story in Eastern Wonderland. She is responsible for the creation of all the enemies in her stage, though she is unrelated to the incident.

Name: Rikako Asakura
Summary: Rikako Asakura is a scientist from Gensokyo. Being one of the few persons using science instead of magic, she firmly believes that the mysterious ruins were made using science.

Name: Riku
Summary: Riku is Sora's rival and best friend, as well as deuteragonist of Kingdom Hearts. A cool-headed and confident youth, he nevertheless is determined to leave the Destiny Islands and see the worlds outside of them. However, on the day he vowed to leave with Sora and Kairi, a freak storm hit that engulfed his world in darkness. Separated from his friends, Maleficent discovers his potential power and manipulates him into believing that Sora had forgotten and replaced him, stoking the inner darkness within Riku and turning him into an unwitting pawn despite his suspicions. Riku is later able to break free of the evil fairy's influence and decides to atone for his mistakes by sealing off the door to Kingdom Hearts along with King Mickey. His story did not end there, as he soon finds himself in Castle Oblivion's basement, having been guided there by Sora's heart. He takes this opportunity to continue assisting Sora from the shadows, but struggles with the darkness in his heart in spite of his attempts to embrace the light.

Name: Riku Replica
Summary: Riku Replica is a clone of Riku made by Vexen using his combat data. Having believed to be the true Riku, the truth has changed him, eventually just focusing on protecting Naminé.

Name: Rinnosuke Morichika
Summary: Rinnosuke Morichika (森近 霖之助, Morichika Rinnosuke), nicknamed Kourin (香霖), is a half-human half-youkai hybrid and using his ability to know the name and purpose of an object, he runs Kourindou, an antique shop specializing in items from the Outside World. He's one of the few male characters depicted in the Touhou Project and is the protagonist of Curiosities of Lotus Asia.

Name: Rita Repulsa
Summary: Rita Repulsa was initially the primary antagonist of Mighty Morphin' Power Rangers, though was eventually shoved to the side by her much more powerful and commanding husband, Lord Zedd.

Name: Robin (Super Smash Bros.)
Summary: Robin (ルフレ, Reflet) is a playable character in both Super Smash Bros for Nintendo 3DS/Wii U and Super Smash Bros Ultimate, where he served as one of the primary protagonists of Fire Emblem: Awakening and the customizable avatar character of the game.

Name: Rodimus (IDW)
Summary: We've seen off a phase sixer, cured an army of sparkeaters, survived a mutiny, travelled in time, gatecrashed a universe, saved half our race, we've liberated planets, defeated the D.J.D., found Luna-1 and the Necrobot, rescued TWO metrotitans, been erased from existence and stole a moon, and a few hours ago we died and broke heaven.

Name: Rouge the Bat (Archie Pre-Genesis Wave)
Summary: Rouge the Bat is a character that appears in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: Roukanken and Hakurouken
Summary: Tier: 2-C

Name: Roxas
Summary: Roxas is Sora's Nobody and the thirteenth member of Organization XIII, being titled "The Key of Destiny". Despite being Sora's Nobody, Roxas' appearance is heavily influenced by Ventus, whose heart had taken refuge in Sora's body to heal at the time of the Nobody's creation. Although kind and cheerful to his friends Axel and Xion, Roxas is prone to anger and recklessness, particularly in the face of deceit or when his individuality is questioned. Despite his best efforts to assert himself as his own person, he is ultimately coerced to merge with his original once more to revive him.

Name: Ryuji Sakamoto
Key: '''Beginning of the Game''' | '''Early Game''' | '''Mid Game''' | '''Late Game''' | '''End Game'''
Summary: Ryuji Sakamoto is one of the founding members of the Phantom Thieves of Hearts. A troublemaking delinquent at a glance, his colorful vernacular and rough appearance belie his kind and loyal heart. After awakening his Persona and obtaining the Metaverse Navigator, he and the other Thieves became determined to change the corrupted society they lived in by stealing the hearts of the wicked. With every heart he steals, he hopes to galvanize the weak and downtrodden and get them to stand up against those that would prey on their misery and suffering.

Name: Ryuji Yamazaki (The King of Fighters)
Key: '''Chapter of Orochi Saga (KOF '95 to KOF '97)''' | '''Chapter of Ash Saga (KOF 2003 to KOF XIII)'''
Summary: nan

Name: Sae Niijima
Summary: Sae Niijima is the fifth major boss of Persona 5, and the Ruler of the Casino of Envy.

Name: Sagume Kishin
Summary: Sagume Kishin (稀神サグメ Kishin Sagume) is a reclusive, high-ranking official on the Moon. Due to her power to reverse any situation by merely speaking of it, she is similar to an Amanojaku, but instead of acting contrarily, the world acts contrarily in response to her words. While she can be tentatively classified as a Divine Spirit, but her true nature is not that of a God.

Name: Sakuya Izayoi
Summary: Sakuya Izayoi is the chief maid of the Scarlet Devil Mansion. Although she is the leader of the fairy maids there, she usually has to do all of the work herself, as the fairy maids are completely useless. She also helps resolve incidents (usually those concerning the mansion), alongside Reimu Hakurei and Marisa Kirisame. Her origins are unknown; she is said to have been given her name by Remilia Scarlet, and Hieda no Akyuu theorizes that she was originally a vampire hunter.

Name: Sally Acorn (Archie Pre-Genesis Wave)
Summary: S: Fine then. I'm guilty. Hamlin: Well! In that case, I move that we... S: But understand this... I will not go through this again. I will not act, I will not give any order, until I have direct approval of the council. Even if we're in the middle of a fight. You can discount any help from the Chaotix, they are free agents, beyond my control. I will refuse to give them any orders. Or— You can trust me. I’ve been defending us all my life. I wouldn’t do anything to endanger my people.

Name: Sanae Kochiya
Summary: Sanae Kochiya is a human descendant of Suwako Moriya who was born in the Outside World. While she is a minor goddess due to her divine heritage, she works as the shrine maiden and wind priestess of the Moriya Shrine and moved into Gensokyo along with Suwako Moriya and Kanako Yasaka. As a result, she is one of the few people living in Gensokyo with a developed knowledge of the Outside World.

Name: Sara (Touhou Project)
Summary: Sara is the Stage 1 boss of Mystic Square and the gatekeeper of Makai, the realm created by Shinki.

Name: Sariel (Touhou Project)
Summary: Sariel is one of the final bosses of the original Touhou game, Highly Responsive to Prayers. She seems to be responsible for destroying Reimu's shrine and is eventually defeated by the Shrine Maiden.

Name: Saïx
Summary: Originally known as Isa, Saïx is the seventh member of Organization XIII and one of Xemnas' closest allies. Known as the "Luna Diviner", he is a cold, calculating, and manipulative Nobody who directs most of the Organization's day-to-day activities. But this facade of calm peels away once he enters battle, becoming a raging berserker who will not stop until his foe has been lost to the Darkness.

Name: Seiga Kaku
Summary: Seiga Kaku (霍青娥) is the wicked hermit responsible for resurrecting Yoshika Miyako and converting Toyosatomimi no Miko to Taoism.

Name: Sephiroth (Final Fantasy)
Key: '''Before Crisis & Crisis Core''' | '''Final Fantasy VII''' | '''Advent Children''' | '''Dissidia'''
Summary: nan

Name: Seven-Three
Summary: Seven-Three (セブンスリー Sebunsurī), whose proper designation is OG73-I, is a member of the Galactic Bandit Brigade.

Name: Shadow Futaba
Summary: I am the other you. How long will you continue blaming yourself and shutting yourself away from the world? For your mother's death. Don't you think it's time you grasped the truth of that moment? What happened before your eyes... What happened to your mother... Why did you choose to rely on the Phantom Thieves? Are you simply going to shut yourself in and do nothing? Are you going to avert your eyes from the true answer? If so... I will kill them in your world

Name: Shadow the Hedgehog (Archie Pre-Genesis Wave)
Summary: Shadow the Hedgehog is a protagonist in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: Shadow the Hedgehog (Light Mobius)
Summary: King Shadow the Hedgehog is a character that appears in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: Shard the Metal Sonic
Summary: Shard the Metal Sonic was the first ever version of Metal Sonic,[2] created by Mobius Prime's original Eggman to have his own Sonic the Hedgehog. He met his demise attempting to race Sonic on Stardust Speedway, his legs beginning to melt as he tried to keep up with his organic counterpart after he performed his Super Peel Out.

Name: Shingo Yabuki
Key: '''Chapter of Orochi Saga (KOF '97)''' | '''Chapter of NESTS Saga (KOF '99 to KOF 2001)''' | '''Chapter of Ash Saga (KOF 2003 to KOF XIII)'''
Summary: nan

Name: Shining Armor
Summary: Shining Armor is a Unicorn in My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Shinjiro Aragaki
Summary: Shinjiro Aragaki is a playable character in Persona 3. Shinjiro grew up alongside Akihiko Sanada in orphanage in their childhood. One day, Shinjiro encountered Mitsuru Kirijo and joined her original SEES group to fight the shadows. Tragically, later on Shinjiro's persona went berserk and killed an innocent woman: Ken Amada's mother. After the event, Shinjiro left SEES and began taking suppressants to control his persona and stopped attending school all together.

Name: Shinki
Summary: Shinki (神綺) is the goddess and creator of Makai, an alternate realm in the Touhou universe. However, she decided to start a vacation business to Gensokyo, sending demons there. Four people, Reimu, Marisa, Yuuka and Mima, went into her own Realm to beat her up and force her to abandon this project. To this day, she hasn't stopped yet.

Name: Shinmyoumaru Sukuna
Summary: Shinmyoumaru Sukuna (少名 針妙丸 Sukuna Shinmyoumaru) is an inchling living in the Shining Needle Castle. Her ancestor Issun-Boushi exterminated an oni, and obtained the oni's treasure, the "Miracle Mallet".

Name: Shion Yorigami
Summary: Shion Yorigami is Joon's elder twin sister and a goddess of poverty. As she brings misfortune and ruin everywhere she goes, she is universally despised, and she is incredibly unlucky herself. Due to the loathing she is subject to, Shion is generally depressed and lacks any motivation to do anything, preferring to let other people handle things for her while she wallows.

Name: Shiva (Final Fantasy XV)
Summary: Shiva, also known as the Glacian, is an Astral in Final Fantasy XV. Out of the Six she is the most friendly and compassionate toward mankind and acts as a Messenger of the gods to mortals. Prince Noctis forges a pact with her in Chapter 12.

Name: Shizuha Aki
Summary: Shizuha Aki is one of the two Aki goddesses of Autumn. Her job is to turn leaves red and make them fall from trees, although she does this by physically painting them red.

Name: Shockwave (IDW)
Summary: I shall remove the very concept of "change". All of space and of time shall exist as a single point, an ultimate singularity. An ultimate black hole. Here, on Cybertron.

Name: Shou Toramaru
