Summary: Shou Toramaru (寅丸 星, Toramaru Shou) is a disciple of the god Bishamonten (毘沙門天). Along with Minamitsu Murasa and the other youkai aboard the Palanquin Ship, she seeks to revive Byakuren Hijiri after she had been sealed away in Makai by humans.

Name: Silver Crystal (Sailor Moon)
Summary: The Silver Crystal (幻の銀水晶, Maboroshi no Ginzuishou; often translated as "the Illusionary Silver Crystal"), was a crystalline object of great and immeasurable power.it is the center of the plot of the Manga Sailor Moon, because of its power, All the Antagonist of the manga have tried to Get it in vain, It was used by Queen Serenity and Usagi. there are variant of the Silver Crystal like the Millennium Crystal which is a palace formed by the Silver Crystal when Usagi becomes queen in the future.

Name: SinGyoku
Summary: SinGyoku is a mysterious entity that appears at the Hakurei Shrine.

Name: Son Gohan (DBS Anime)
Key: '''Resurrection of F''' | '''Universe 6 Tournament''' | '''Tournament of Power''' | '''Super Hero Arc'''
Summary: Son Gohan (孫そん悟ご飯はん?) is the eldest son of Son Goku and Chi-Chi, and one of the primary heroes of the second half of Dragon Ball. Although originally introduced as a mild-mannered and easily scared child, Gohan harbors an immense, limitless potential that surpasses that of his father. However, unlike his father, Gohan dislikes fighting and harming others, and his true power only shows through during moments of intense rage. Following Goku's death, he was trained by Piccolo in anticipation of the upcoming Saiyan invasion, and grew much stronger and closer to his new mentor, ultimately redeeming him and setting him down the path of heroism due to their bond.

Name: Son Gohan (DBS Manga)
Summary: Son Gohan (孫そん悟ご飯はん?) is the eldest son of Son Goku and Chi-Chi, and one of the primary heroes of the second half of Dragon Ball. Although originally introduced as a mild-mannered and easily scared child, Gohan harbors an immense, limitless potential that surpasses that of his father. However, unlike his father, Gohan dislikes fighting and harming others, and his true power only shows through during moments of intense rage. Following Goku's death, he was trained by Piccolo in anticipation of the upcoming Saiyan invasion, and grew much stronger and closer to his new mentor, ultimately redeeming him and setting him down the path of heroism due to their bond.

Name: Son Goten (Manga)
Key: '''Majin Buu Arc''' | ''' DBS Super Hero Onwards '''
Summary: Son Goten (孫そん悟ご天てん, Son Goten?) is a protagonist in the Dragon Ball manga and the animes Dragon Ball Z, Dragon Ball GT and Dragon Ball Super. He is the younger son of the main protagonist of the Dragon Ball series Goku and his wife Chi-Chi, making him a Saiyan and Human hybrid. Goten is Gohan's younger brother and Trunks' best friend.

Name: Sora (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Sora is a cheerful, young boy hailing from the Destiny Islands and the main protagonist of the Kingdom Hearts series. Longing to see the worlds outside of his own, he and his friends Riku and Kairi pledged to build a raft and set out together. However, on their planned day of departure, a freak storm hit their home and their world was subsequently engulfed by the Darkness. It was at this time that Sora unlocked his ability to wield a Keyblade, a weapon of legend that is said to bring salvation or destruction but is thrown into a Corridor of Darkness despite his efforts to combat the shadows that were swarming his home. Awakening in Traverse Town, he soon sets out with Goofy and Donald Duck, attendants to King Mickey, to discover the mystery behind the darkness and reunite with his friends.

Name: Soul King
Summary: Adnyeus (アドナイェウス, Adonayeusu?), more commonly known as the Soul King (霊れい王おう, Reiō?), is the king of Soul Society, whose existence in Soul Society is as symbolic as it is absolute. The king resides in the Soul King Palace that exists in a separate, special realm in the very core of Soul Society, which is protected by the Royal Guard. The door to this realm is opened via the Ōken.

Name: Sous Roas (Anime)
Summary: Sous Roas (スー・ロース, Sū Rōsu) is a warrior from Universe 2 and a member of the Kamikaze Fireballs. In her Magical Girl form, she becomes Magical Girl Roasie (ロージィ, Rōjī).

Name: Staff of Sacanas
Summary: Staff of Sacanas is a powerful staff formerly used by The Storm King in the My Little Pony Movie.

Name: Star Swirl the Bearded
Summary: Star Swirl the Bearded is an important figure in Equestrian history.

Name: Starlight Glimmer
Key: '''From Season 5 to 8''' | '''Series Finale onward''' | '''Equestria Girls Human Self'''
Summary: Starlight Glimmer was the main antagonist of Season 5 of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic, and later one of the show's main protagonists.

Name: Stewie Griffin
Summary: Stewie Griffin is one of the main characters in the animated series, Family Guy.

Name: Storm the Albatross (Archie Comics)
Summary: Storm the Albatross is a hulking, grey albatross and the enforcer of the Babylon Rogues. Strong-armed and simple-minded, he serves as Jet the Hawk's right hand man and is usually at odds with his intellectually superior teammate, Wave the Swallow. Relying more on his brute strength, Storm is not the most skilled at riding Extreme Gear, but is still an adequate flyer while being able to match other physically fit opponents like Knuckles the Echidna.

Name: Stygian
Summary: Tier: Unknown, likely 8-A | 2-A, possibly Low 1-C

Name: Subspace Army
Summary: The Subspace Army is an organization hailing from Subspace led by Tabuu. It is the main antagonistic force of the Subspace Emissary, acting as the source behind most threats faced by the heroes. Its goal is the absorption of the World of Trophy into Subspace, done by the usage of Subspace Bombs. As Tabuu cannot leave Subspace, most of the forces are located in the World of Trophy while Tabuu manipulates them from Subspace. Those include the Isle of the Ancients, the Halberd (Piloted by Mr. Game & Watch) and the Koopa Troop. Most relations within the army are quite fragile, however, as a lot of them are done either through force or trickery. Notably, almost no one knows the existence of Tabuu, as the latter hides behind Master Hand to communicate his orders to his commanders.

Name: Suguru Kamoshida
Summary: Drop the attitude, you mediocre peasant! There's no wrong in using my gifts for my gain! I'm a cut above all other humans!

Name: Suika Ibuki
Summary: Suika Ibuki (伊吹 萃香, Ibuki Suika) is a typical oni who loves drinking and fighting. Before appearing in Gensokyo, she lived in the Underworld, and even before that, she lived on Youkai Mountain as one of the four "Devas of the Mountain", along with Yuugi Hoshiguma and two other unknown oni. Due to her immense strength, she is still remembered as someone to be respected.

Name: Suiki
Summary: Suiki is one of the Kishin Chiefs of Hell. It has been sent in Gensokyo to defeat Seiga Kaku, a hermit who lived past her intended lifespan.

Name: Sumireko Usami
Key: '''Base''' | '''Dream World''' | '''With the Occult Balls' true power'''
Summary: Sumireko Usami is the president of the Occult Club from the Outside world. She first reached Gensokyo through her dreams, but she planned to destroy the barrier separating the outside world from Gensokyo so she could access it fully.

Name: Sunset Shimmer
Key: '''Human''' | '''Unicorn Form''' | '''Element of Magic (Demon Form)''' | '''Pony-Up Form''' | '''Daydream Shimmer'''
Summary: Sunset Shimmer is a reformed villain from My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Suwako Moriya
Summary: Suwako Moriya (洩矢 諏訪子, Moriya Suwako) is the original goddess of the Moriya Shrine, prior to Kanako's take over. Officially the shrine belongs to Kanako, but Suwako handles the divine services. She is a native god born from and formed of faith, and Sanae Kochiya is her distant descendant and shrine maiden.

Name: Sword of Hisou
Summary: The Sword of Hisou is a relic that can only be wielded by Celestials and Tenshi's primary weapon.

Name: Tails (Archie Pre-Genesis Wave)
Summary: Miles Tails Prower is one of the main protagonists in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: Takaya Sakaki
Summary: Takaya Sakaki is a character from Persona 3. Takaya is the confident and charismatic young leader of Strega who was once experimented on by the Kirijo Group. He functions as the protagonist's foil, leading the rival group of Persona-users and setting himself up as a false messiah.

Name: Tempest Shadow
Summary: Tempest Shadow is a major antagonist in My Little Pony: The Movie.

Name: Tenryu (Touhou Project)
Summary: Tenryu, also known as the Celestial Dragon, is one of the Dragons in the world of Touhou Project. It is a living constellation in Heaven that is bound to eventually devour the Unmoving Star, also known as the North Star.

Name: Tenshi Hinanawi
Summary: Born Chiko Hinanawi, she ascended alongside her parents when they became Celestials, and chose to rename herself Tenshi. However, as she did not earn ascension herself, she is considerably less enlightened than her peers and quickly grew bored and frustrated with Bhavaagra. This is what prompted her to cause chaos in Gensokyo, having watched several of the incidents its inhabitants have caused and deciding that they must be lots of fun.

Name: Terminus Blade
Summary: The Terminus Blade is a legendary weapon that can bring Omega Terminus under heel, but also connect and even move worlds. It was created by Solus Prime for herself and her brethren to cross dimensions in their campaign against Unicron. As fate would have it, however, technological advancement rendered the Blade obsolete, and so it was carelessly cast aside, with none of the Thirteen considering what would happen if ordinary Cybertronians were to get ahold of it.

Name: Terra (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Terra is a Keyblade Wielder training under Eraqus in the Land of Departure. He aspires to be a Keyblade Master, but Eraqus refuses to give Terra the title of Master after noticing the Darkness in Terra's heart during his Mark of Mastery Exam. But after learning that the Seven Princesses of Heart were in danger of being attacked by the Unversed, Terra sets off on a quest to save them in order to protect the worlds and prove himself worthy of becoming a Keyblade Master.

Name: Terry Bogard (The King of Fighters)
Key: '''Prologue Chapter (KOF '94) ''' | '''Chapter of Orochi Saga (KOF '95 to KOF '97)''' | '''Chapter of NESTS Saga (KOF '99 to KOF 2001)''' | '''KOF Sky Stage''' | '''Chapter of Ash Saga (KOF 2003 to KOF XIII)'''
Summary: nan

Name: The Brotherhood of Guardians
Summary: To ensure history not repeat itself, they appointed a Guardian to stand and watch over the surviving Chaos Emerald. Edmund was the first to bear that mantle. A scared trust, passed generation unto generation, through all his children, to my father and finally, to me!

Name: The Cosmic Imagination
Summary: "Third Orb does not exist," said the Sage. "Why?" asked the Student. "Because the Multiverse," said the Sage, "within which Third Orb exists, does not exist. The Multiverse is a Consensus Reality shared by the Minds of all Sentient Beings. If they were to Die, the Multiverse, as such, would suddenly blink out of existence, vanish, be no more." "Why?" asked the Student. "Because," said the Sage, "there would be no one to perceive it."

Name: The Creator (VShojo Mythos)
Summary: As their title implies, The Creator is the higher power responsible for the existence of everything in the VShojo multiverse. Once everything had been created, they fell asleep almost immediately afterwards, locked behind a gate which was guarded by the higher angels. No one laid eyes on the Creator for eons, until one lower angel dared challenge the status quo.

Name: The Crystals (Final Fantasy)
Summary: The Crystals are objects of power that appear in the Final Fantasy series, serving as embodiments of wisdom and keepers of the four elements. In reality, they were made and sent out to various planets by The Creator for the ultimate goal of recording and furthering evolution. The crystals are a notable point of plot in the first five games in the series, and are confirmed to exist at least on the first six.

Name: The Dazzlings
Summary: The Dazzlings are the villains of the My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic movie Rainbow Rocks.

Name: The Enchiridion
Summary: The Enchiridion, also known as The-Book-That-Is-Not-A-Book is a mysterious and immensely powerful being in the appearance of a book. Created some time a million years ago by he who would become "The Reader", The Enchiridion is thought to be a "guide of heroism" but in actuality is a sentient entity capable of manipulating all of creation, as well as the object used to cast judgement upon The Multiverse at the end of time.

Name: The Lich (Adventure Time)
Summary: The Lich is the main antagonist of Adventure Time. Given life by GOLB's breath, the Lich first manifested as a Catalyst Comet that wiped out the dinosaurs. Then, during the Mushroom War, came into existence from the Mushroom Bomb's nuclear waste. Seeking the extinction of all life across the multiverse, he was first defeated by Billy, before freeing himself and menacing Ooo once more.

Name: The Maid
Summary: The Maid is a weapon which Finn and Jake used to try and remove The Lich in the episode "Crossover." It represents itself as a helper, hinted by its name "The Maid." When it is fired, a female voice can be heard saying "Housekeeping."

Name: The Mean Six
Summary: The Mean Six are the main antagonists of the MLP: FiM episode of the same name. They are clones of the Mane Six created by Queen Chrysalis before they end up turning against her.

Name: The Overlord (Ninjago)
Key: '''Spirit form''' | '''Possessing Lord Garmadon''' | '''Dragon Form''' | '''The Digital Overlord''' | '''The Golden Master''' | '''Crystal King'''
Summary: In the First Realm, only two races existed, the Oni, and the Dragons, beings who controlled creation and destruction, and who fought each other in an eternal stalemate. One day, however, a child who was born of both the Oni and the Dragon was born. This child, known as the First Spinjitzu Master, was sought by both races as a means to end the war. Seeing that the two races would never find peace and couldn't understand the balance that was necessary for existence, left the realm to create his own, which became known as Ninjago. However, as the balance dictates that a world must have both good and evil, the Overlord - the dark spirit that had always existed - emerged into the Realm. The First Spinjitzu Master and the Overlord fought tirelessly and endlessly until The Overlord created a stone army to finally kill him. Knowing that he would eventually lose, the First Spinjitzu Master split the land in two, the Overlord being sealed into The Dark Island. However, the Overlord saw the arrival of Lord Garmadon, and thus waited for the ultimate battle between good and evil. Eventually, his prediction came to pass, with Lord Garmadon being betrayed by the Serpentine and left to rot in the ocean, eventually landing on the island. Manipulating Lord Garmadon and starting the Celestial Clock's countdown, which would dictate the beginning of the battle, The Overlord tricked him into spreading darkness through the Garmatron into Ninjago, shifting the balance back to darkness and restoring his powers. Forcibly taking over Garmadon's body and regaining his true form, and proceeded to corrupt all of Ninjago. However, he was ultimately soundly defeated by Lloyd Garmadon, who had become the Ultimate Spinjitzu Master and was purged from Ninjago. Unfortunately for the Ninjas, the site of his defeat was still a foothold for him to remain and allowed him to take over Borg Industries, whose headquarters were built upon it. Taking over New Ninjago City’s infrastructure and the entirety of their computer system, he began a campaign to drain Lloyd’s power in order to become the Golden Master, a legendary being of Serpentine lore who held the powers of The First Spinjitzu Master at his peak, and would be fated to enslave the world. Eventually fulfilling this role with the power of the Golden Weapons, the Overlord was defeated by Zane, who sacrificed himself to turn the Overlord’s power against himself at the cost of his own life, purging his darkness from Ninjago once more.

Name: The Storm King
Summary: The Storm King is the main antagonist of the My Little Pony Movie.

Name: Tiamat (Final Fantasy I)
Summary: Tiamat is the Fiend of Wind final and most powerful member of the Four Fiends that the Warriors of Light face. She forged a contract with Garland to create an everlasting time loop that would revive the Fiends time and again until the Warriors of Light ventured into the past to end them once and for all.

Name: Tobias Wilson
Summary: Tobias Wilson is a supporting character in The Amazing World of Gumball. He is a student at Elmore Junior High. He claims to be popular with the ladies, but he is actually pretentious and is just good at projecting the persona of someone who is successful. Tobias frequently fails to impress his female classmates, yet continues to believe that he is the coolest person. He is overconfident in his social and physical capabilities, and enjoys boasting about his supposed status and accomplishments, much to the annoyance of others. Despite his shortcomings, Tobias does have plenty of friends anyway, and does actually come from a well-off family.

Name: Tommy Oliver
Key: '''Civilian''' | '''Mighty Morphin Power Rangers: Season 1''' | '''Mighty Morphin Power Rangers: Season 2''' | '''Mighty Morphin Power Rangers: Season 3''' | '''Red Zeo Form''' | '''Dino Thunder Black''' | '''Super Dino Mode'''
Summary: Tommy Oliver is the Green Mighty Morphin Ranger, White Mighty Morphin Ranger, Red Zeo Ranger, Red Turbo Ranger I & the Black Dino Ranger. He is often considered the greatest Power Ranger of all time both in and out of the actual show for his many accomplishments on several different teams. He is a fan favorite, the most reoccurring ranger, and second most reoccurring character in the entire show next to Bulk. He is also one of the strongest rangers.

Name: Tommy Oliver (Turbo)
Summary: Dimetria: That was cutting it very close, Rangers.

Name: Tonitrus Lucis Caelum
Summary: Tonitrus Lucis Caelum, more commonly known as The Fierce, is a past king of Lucis. He appears as a statue in Kingsglaive: Final Fantasy XV, and as a Lucii in Final Fantasy XV; he also appears as a boss in the Windows and Royal Editions.

Name: Toyosatomimi no Miko
Summary: Toyosatomimi no Miko is the true identity of Prince Shoutoku, an advocate of Buddhism from the 6th century. Renowned for her genius and skill, Miko gradually became dissatisfied with her life and turned against her fate as a human to eventually die. She was approached by Seiga Kaku, a Taoist hermit who taught her the ways of Taoism. Miko was delighted to find a religion that could help her realize true immortality, though she knew that it wasn't fit for ruling a country. So, she pretended to support Buddhism while advancing her own study of Taoism.

Name: Trent Fernandez-Mercer
Summary: Trent Fernandez-Mercer is the White Dino Thunder Ranger, who was initially corrupted by the White Dino Gem but then reformed when the evil was removed from him by his adopted father, Dr. Anton Mercer. When his biological parents were killed in an archaeological cave-in, Dr. Mercer took him in, though he still kept his original surname. He works at Hayley's Cyberspace as a waiter and draws in his spare time, though he keeps this secret because his father does not approve of his artistic endeavours.

Name: Tribe of the Ancients
Summary: The Tribe of Ancients or The Ancients are a group of powerful magicians from an advance civilization with an immense knowledge of different dimensions and the concepts in each of them. They created multiple worlds and the Pixls in order to build and cultivate said worlds. They also owned a book known as The Dark Prognosticus. Some time later, a group of individuals have separated themselves from the tribe with the Dark Prognosticus in their possession. This exiled tribe would be known as The Tribe of Darkness.

Name: Trini Kwan
Summary: Trini Kwan is the original Yellow Ranger of the Power Rangers series. She was the caring and optimistic member of the team during the war against Rita and served as the tactics expert on-board the Dino Megazord. She would go on to become a world peace ambassador following her retirement as a Ranger.

Name: Trunks (Manga)
Key: '''Majin Buu Arc''' | ''' DBS Super Hero Onwards '''
Summary: Trunks (トランクス) is a protagonist in the Dragon Ball manga, and the anime series Dragon Ball Z, and Dragon Ball Super. He is the Human and Saiyan hybrid son of Bulma and Vegeta.

Name: Truth (Fullmetal Alchemist)
Summary: Truth, or "God" is an intangible being who exists in the Fullmetal Alchemist series. Truth oversees everything in the universe, and regulates all Alchemic exchanges in the world. Truth reveals itself when alchemists attempt to "Play God" through attempting Human Transmutation. Seeing Human Transmutation as an unfair exchange according to the equivalent exchange laws of Alchemy, Truth will bring the alchemist into the Gate and forceably take their most valued attribute, or something of value that represents their anticipated relationship to the person they are trying to create, or resurrect. Truth will accept otherwise impossible exchanges when a Philosopher's Stone is used, as it or part of it will be used for the exchange instead.

Name: Tupper (Anime)
Summary: Tupper is a Pride Trooper from Universe 11 who fought in the Tournament of Power.

Name: Twilight Sparkle (Pony World)
Key: '''Unicorn Form''' | '''Alicorn Form''' | '''The Ending of the End Alicorn Form''' | '''Elements of Harmony/Magic of Friendship''' | '''All Alicorn Magic''' | '''Post-Timeskip Alicorn Form''' | '''Rainbow Power''' | '''Equestria Girls Human form'''
Summary: Twilight Sparkle is the main protagonist of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Twilight Sparkle (Sci-Twi)
Summary: Twilight Sparkle is one of the main protagonists in the My Little Pony: Equestria Girls series.

Name: Ultima, the High Seraph
Summary: nan

Name: Ultimate Annihilator
Summary: The Ultimate Annihilator was the ultimate weapon of the late, Prime Dr. Ivo Robotnik in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: Ultraman (Ultra Series)
Key: '''Showa Era''' | '''Heisei Era''' | '''Galaxy Crisis Era''' | '''New Generation Era (Before Crisis)''' | '''New Generation Era (After Crisis)''' | '''Reiwa Era'''
Summary: Mefilas: "What are you Ultraman? Are you an alien, or a human?" Ultraman: "I am both. I was born to fight those who break universal laws, like you"

Name: Unicron (IDW)
Summary: In the early days of Cybertron's history, Unicron was viewed as Cybertron's greatest enemy. It was told that he was arch nemesis of the mythical Primus, and would one day be destined to awakened once again to attack Cybertron, and was destined to be slain by the last of the Primes.

Name: Utsuho Reiuji
Summary: Utsuho Reiuji is one of Satori Komeiji's pets and the regulator of the flames of the former Hell of Blazing Fires. A Hell Raven, born from the darkness of Hell, Utsuho isn't the brightest, which made her a good subject for Kanako Yasaka's plan to gain the ultimate power of nuclear fusion. In her dreams, Utsuho was told to consume the remains of the sun god Yatagarasu, so she could fulfill the wishes of those above and below the surface of the world. However, she misinterpreted the message and decided that she would use her newfound, immense power to conquer all of Gensokyo and incinerate any who opposed her.

Name: Vanitas (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Vanitas is a Keyblade Wielder and Master Xehanort's mysterious new apprentice. He takes an unusual interest in Ventus (Kingdom Hearts) after their first meeting, mocking the young Keyblade Wielder and challenging him to go beyond the ken of the Land of Departure. His goals bring him into conflict with both Aqua and Terra, clashing with all three Keyblade Wielders throughout their travels.

Name: Vector the Crocodile (Archie Pre-Genesis Wave)
Summary: Vector the Crocodile is a Mobian crocodile and one of Knuckles the Echidna's oldest friends and the de-facto leader of the Chaotix. Having lived with the Guardian on Angel Island and made his acquaintance after what Knuckles thought was the death of his father Locke, Vector was the first mobian to join Knuckles as an ally in combat.

Name: Vegeta (DBS Manga)
Key: '''Battle of Gods Arc''' | '''Resurrection 'F' Arc''' | '''Universe 6 - Future Trunks Arc''' | '''Post-Training Future Trunks Saga''' | '''Universe Survival - Broly Arc''' | '''Galactic Patrol Prisoner Arc''' | '''Granolah the Survivor Arc'''
Summary: Vegeta (ベジータ, Bejīta?) is the disgraced prince of the Saiyan race, one of the few survivors of his species after Frieza destroyed Planet Vegeta. Left with no choice but to follow his orders, Vegeta travelled across the galaxy and eradicated planets for sale before he was brought to Earth by Raditz's report of the Dragon Balls, a magical set of balls that could grant him immortality. Upon arriving on Earth, he ultimately comes to encounter and fights Son Goku, the man who would go on to become his greatest rival.

Name: Vegito
Summary: nan

Name: Vegito (DBS Manga)
Summary: Vegito (ベジット, Bejitto?) is the Potara Fusion of Son Goku and Vegeta, originally formed to defeat Majin Buu after he had absorbed Gohan, and later reappearing to fight Fusion Zamasu. While all fusions have immense power, Vegito's power is abnormal even by Potara standards, as Vegeta and Goku's intense rivalry has brought out an exceptional power.

Name: Ventus (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Ventus is a rookie Keyblade wielder who trains alongside Terra and Aqua at the Land of Departure. He runs away from home to chase after Terra after receiving a warning of things to come. Despite not being as along in his training as they are, he's still a capable warrior and is eager to explore new worlds and make friends. He has some connection to Master Xehanort and his new apprentice Vanitas, but he cannot remember how or why.

Name: Vexen
Summary: Vexen, the Chilly Academic (いてつく学究 Itetsuku Gakkyū?, lit. Freezing Scholar), is the Nobody of Even and is Rank IV within Organization XIII. He controls ice and uses it to command storms and blizzards, freezing his opponents solid, while defending himself with his massive shield.

Name: Viara (Anime)
Summary: Viara is a warrior from Universe 3 who fought in the Tournament of Power.

Name: Vincent Valentine
Summary: nan

Name: Warrior of Light (Final Fantasy XIV)
Summary: The Warrior of Light, sometimes known as the Warrior of Darkness, Hydaelyn's Chosen, or the Hero of Eorzea, is a silent adventurer and the protagonist of the MMORPG Final Fantasy XIV. Though his gender, race, and appearance vary from player to player, he is represented in trailers and promotional materials as a male Midlander Hyur. As the chosen warrior of Hydaelyn, the Warrior uses his power to protect the realm of Eorzea from whatever threat would seek to destroy it.

Name: Watatsuki no Toyohime
Summary: Watatsuki no Toyohime is a Lunarian princess. Along with her younger sister, Yorihime, she is in charge of the Lunarian Defense Corps.

Name: Watatsuki no Yorihime
Summary: Watatsuki no Yorihime is a Lunarian princess. Along with her sister, Toyohime, she is the head of the Lunarian Defense Corps; she appears to be primarily responsible for training the moon rabbits.

Name: Wave the Swallow (Archie Comics)
Summary: Wave the Swallow is a purple Mobian swallow, and the resident technical genius for the Babylon Rogues. As a former member of the Battle Bird Armada, Wave worked with Dr. Fukurokov until she crossed him and went Rogue after escaping jail. She is quite knowledgable in mechanics and technological expertise, and is responsible for maintaining the Rogues' zeppelin and its supplies. Wave is a skilled rider of Extreme Gear and considers all of the Rogue's Gear her own; taking great pride in the work she puts into it while demeaning the skills of others like Tails with his own airboards, which makes her a bit of a trash-talker. She obsesses greatly over the effort put into keeping their Extreme Gear in the best condition possible that she gives them priority over anything else once they take enough damage. After a failed battle to steal a Sol Emerald, Wave found a clue to Babylon Garden that enabled the Rogues to discover the means to unlock it.

Name: Wii Fit Trainer (Smash Bros.)
Summary: Wii Fit Trainer is a fighter in the Super Smash Bros. series originating from the popular Wii game Wii Fit. Wii Fit Trainer's moveset takes heavy inspiration from Wii Fit, with his/her fighting style being based on various acrobatic moves and fitness equipment. Wii Fit Trainer is often portrayed as female, but can be swapped out for a male version

Name: Xemnas
Summary: Xemnas, the Superior of the In-Between (狭間の指導者 Hazama no Shidōsha), is the Nobody of Terra-Xehanort. He is the leader of the original Organization XIII, the former ruler of The World That Never Was, and a member of the True Organization XIII. He serves as the main antagonist of Kingdom Hearts II and as a supporting antagonist in Kingdom Hearts 358/2 Days and Kingdom Hearts 3D: Dream Drop Distance.

Name: Xion
Summary: Xion is the fourteenth member of Organization XIII, first appearing in the game Kingdom Hearts 358/2 Days, in which she could be viewed as both a main protagonist and antagonist. She is not a normal Nobody and is only a nominal member of the Organization. Because of this, she does not have a throne in Where Nothing Gathers, nor does she have a title or a breed of Nobody to control. Instead, she is an imperfect Replica of Sora created from his leaked memories as a fail-safe in case both Sora and Roxas proved to be useless to Organization XIII's plans. While this enables her to use the Keyblade, Xion's existence also halts Sora's progression of regaining his memories to fully awaken while in his pod, something which Naminé, DiZ, and Riku recognize.

Name: Yatagarasu
Summary: Yatagarasu was the avatar of Amaterasu and the Personification of the Sun. It used to be a giant crow living in the sun. However, seemingly after Houyi shot down the sun, it was found deceased. Following this, Kanako planned to make a certain underworld raven a living nuclear reactor by making her absorb the deceased Sun God into her being.

Name: Yatsuhashi Tsukumo
Summary: Yatsuhashi Tsukumo is one of the Tsukumogami sister. She was transformed into a Youkai from a simple tool due to the Miracle Mallet's magical powers.

Name: Yhwach
Summary: Yhwach (ユーハバッハ, Yūhabahha?) is the Father of the Quincy, the monarch of the Wandenreich, and the son of the Soul King, known by the designation "A" - The Almighty.

Name: Yin-Yang Orb
Summary: The Yin-Yang Orb is Reimu's main weapon and one of the main artifact of the Hakurei Shrine. Its exact nature hasn't been explained in detail, but it is recognized as an artifact from the Hakurei God that was created to fulfill the Shrine's function of exterminating youkai.

Name: Youkai Mountain
Summary: The Youkai Mountain is an important landmark in Gensokyo and home to several youkai, as per its name. The mountain covers several smaller locations such as the Giant Toad's Pond, the Moriya Shrine, the Genbu Ravine and the Untrodden Valley.

Name: Youmu Konpaku
Summary: Youmu Konpaku (魂魄 妖夢, Konpaku Youmu) is Yuyuko Saigyouji's gardener and attendant. A half-human, half-phantom, she was trained in the art of swordplay by the previous gardener, Youki Konpaku, and took over his position once he disappeared.

Name: Young Xehanort
Summary: Young Xehanort, referred to as the Unknown and the Mysterious Figure in the North American, PAL, and Final Mix versions of Kingdom Hearts Birth by Sleep, is a boss in Kingdom Hearts Birth by Sleep and one of the main antagonists in Kingdom Hearts 3D: Dream Drop Distance as well as Kingdom Hearts III.

Name: Yukari Takeba
Summary: Yukari Takeba is a playable character in Persona 3. She is the sole daughter of Eiichiro Takeba, a leading scientist that was made part of the experiment which would eventually give birth to the Dark Hour. She joins S.E.E.S. while seeking the truth about her father's death in order to achieve closure with his passing. She is a popular student and a member of the Archery Club.

Name: Yukari Yakumo
Summary: Yukari Yakumo is a legendary youkai with the power to manipulate boundaries, and one of the youkai sages who created Gensokyo. Often called the "gap youkai," she is a remarkably youkai-like youkai who spends most of her time sleeping and relaxing. However, she is quite brilliant and is aware of most things happening within Gensokyo.

Name: Yuki (Touhou Project)
Summary: Yuki is, along with Mai, a witch who resides in Makai and with Mai, serves as one of two bosses in Mystic Square's fourth stage.

Name: Yumeko
Summary: Yumeko is a resident of Makai, and one of Shinki's greatest creations. Initially polite towards her master, she regards the main heroines with disdain. Despite her display of power and being ranked as one of the most powerful beings, she is quickly defeated.

Name: Yumemi Okazaki
Summary: Yumemi Okazaki (岡崎 夢美, Okazaki Yumemi) is a college professor who has come to Gensokyo in her ship, the Probability Space Hypervessel, in search of magic, to bring it back to the scientific community.

Name: Yusuke Kitagawa
Summary: Yusuke Kitagawa is a playable character from Persona 5. Yusuke is an honor student in an art course at the Kosei High School, and because of that, his entire life’s passion is comprised of and surrounded by art. He searches for the aesthetic everywhere in his surroundings, from people to places. He sees every opportunity or challenge presented to him as a way to broaden his horizons and primarily considers how it will benefit him as an artist, all while fighting alongside the Phantom thieves of Hearts in an effort of changing the corrupted society that they live in.

Name: YuugenMagan
Summary: YuugenMagan is a boss from the first installment of the Touhou Project series: Highly Responsive to Prayers. Nothing is known about this enemy, except the fact that it's found in Makai.

Name: Yuugi Hoshiguma
Summary: Yuugi Hoshiguma is an oni of the Underworld and one of the former Big Four of the Mountain, alongside Suika Ibuki. Content to spend her life partying and drinking, she lives alongside the many other oni that were forced below ground.

Name: Yuuka Kazami
Summary: Yuuka Kazami (風見 幽香, Kazami Yuuka) is a mysterious, long-lived youkai most often found in the Garden of the Sun. With a threat level described as "very high" and a human friendship level described as "worst", she is a fearsome and immensely strong youkai despite her polite mannerisms.

Name: Yuuma Toutetsu
Summary: Yuuma Toutetsu (饕餮 尤魔 Toutetsu Yuuma) is the leader of the Gouyoku Alliance under which the eagle spirits serve. She was originally mentioned by Saki Kurokoma in the extra stage of Wily Beast and Weakest Creature, before appearing as the primary antagonist of Gouyoku Ibun.

Name: Yuyuko Saigyouji
Summary: Yuyuko Saigyouji is the ghost princess of Hakugyokurou, the shrine of the Netherworld. In life, before she became a ghost, she was the head of the Saigyouji clan. Possessing the powerful ability to manipulate departed souls, after this power developed into the ability to kill anything, Yuyuko was overwhelmed by the power of her ability and, terrified, she committed suicide. She was buried under the Saigyou Ayakashi, sealing away its blossoms, and she returned as a ghost, incapable of vanishing or reincarnating as long as the seal still stands.

Name: Zeekeeper
Summary: The Zeekeeper is the guardian figure of the Pi'illo Kingdom, who helped them take down Antasma many thousands of years before the events of the game.

Name: Zelda (Super Smash Bros.)
Summary: Zelda (ゼルダ, Zelda), is a playable character in the Super Smash Bros. series. For each generation of Hyrule, there has been a distinct incarnation of Zelda serving as its crown princess, as seen throughout The Legend of Zelda timeline. Similarly, her Super Smash Bros. counterpart has also cycled through different incarnations across the series, resembling her canon self in Ocarina of Time, Twilight Princess and A Link to the Past.

Name: Zetton
Key: '''Ultraman (Generation I)''' | '''Return of Ultraman (Generation II)''' | '''Ultraman: The Ultimate Hero (Powered)''' | '''Ultraman Max''' | '''Ultraman Mebius''' | '''Ultraman Mebius Gaiden: Ghost Rebirth (EX)''' | '''Ultraman X''' | '''Ultraman Orb (Maga)''' | '''Ultraman Taiga''' | '''Ultra Galaxy Fight: The Absolute Conspiracy'''
Summary: Zetton, is a giant, horned, humanoid, beetle-like Kaiju that served as the final and strongest monster of the original Ultraman series.

Name: Zexion
Summary: Zexion, the Cloaked Schemer (影歩む策士 Kageayumu Sakushi, lit. Shadow-Walking Schemer), is the Nobody of Ienzo and is Rank VI in Organization XIII and an antagonist in Riku's storyline in Kingdom Hearts: Chain of Memories. He weaves illusions to fight for him. Unlike the other Organization members, Zexion's weapon was originally unknown, and his talents were used only outside of normal combat. In Kingdom Hearts Re:Chain of Memories, Zexion's weapon was revealed to be a book called a Lexicon.

Name: Zoffy
Key: '''Showa Era''' | '''Heisei Era''' | '''Galaxy Crisis Era''' | '''New Generation Era (Pre-Crisis)''' | '''New Generation Era (Post-Crisis)''' | '''Reiwa Era'''
Summary: Human, you've come this far under your own power. Before long, the time will come that you'll stand side by side with us, and soar across the gulf of the stars. Until then, we will be the shield for your world. I look forward to our next meeting

Name: Zone Cops
Summary: We're Ready for this, every Single Zone Cop is prepared to give it all they've got.

Name: 160-Ton Thermonuclear Bomb
Summary: The 160-Ton Thermonuclear Bomb is a Doomsday weapon created by Captain Underpants's arch nemesis, Tippy Tinkletrousers. After suffering a humiliating defeat from the hero, Tippy planned to get his final revenge by detonating the bomb. Which would destroy Captain Underpants, and the entire world along with him.

Name: Agrias Oaks
Summary: Lady Agrias Oaks is a secondary character appearing in Final Fantasy Tactics, initially as a guest character working together with Ramza Beoulve through the story, finally joining him during the events of Chapter 2.

Name: Aigis
Summary: Aigis is a 7th Generation Anti-Shadow Suppression Weapon constructed by the Kirijo Group as part of their experiments. Created to wield a Persona and do battle against Shadows, she is one of the last of her kind. She fights alongside the members of SEES during the events of Persona 3, becoming especially attached to its field leader.

Name: Akihiko Sanada
Summary: Akihiko Sanada is a playable character in Persona 3. Growing up in an orphanage alongside his best friend Shinjiro and younger sister Mikki. Mikki one day died in an orphanage fire and by that grief and powerlessness, Akihiko vowed to become stronger eventually encountering Mitsuru Kirijo and joining S.E.E.S.

Name: Amaterasu Oomikami (Touhou Project)
Summary: Amaterasu Oomikami is a goddess in the Touhou Project universe. She is the sister of Lord Tsukuyomi, the leader, and ruler of the Lunar Capital.

Name: Ann Takamaki
Key: '''Beginning of the Game''' | '''Early Game''' | '''Mid Game''' | '''Late Game''' | '''End Game'''
Summary: Ann Takamaki is one of the founding members of the Phantom Thieves of Hearts. The classmate of Ren Amamiya and Ryuji Sakamoto, she is one of the first playable characters in Persona 5. Ann was shunned because of her looks and didn't have many friends before meeting the protagonist. Along with the other Phantom Thieves of Hearts, Ann hopes to reform society by stealing the hearts of the corrupt.

Name: Antasma
Summary: Antasma (Japanese: アックーム, Akkumu) is one of the main antagonists in Mario & Luigi: Dream Team.

Name: Anubis Cruger
Summary: Anubis "Doggie" Cruger is the leading commander of Earth Branch's Space Patrol Delta, a dog-like alien race called Sirian, and the S.P.D Shadow Ranger. Before residing on Earth, he lives on a planet named Sirius, which was was attacked by Emperor Grumm and his forces. Despite fighting against the army and even cutting off one of Grumm's horns, the battle was lost with the Sirian race being killed and Sirius being destroyed. While he tends to act stubborn and serious, he is actually courageous, considerate, and indulgent. He was eventually promoted to Supreme Commander of Space Patrol Delta.

Name: Aunn Komano
Summary: Aunn Komano is a Komainu living near the Hakurei Shrine. Without its owner's knowledge, she guards the Shrine against intruders.

Name: Benben Tsukumo
Summary: Benben Tsukumo is one of the Tsukumogami sister. She was transformed into a Youkai from a simple tool due to the Miracle Mallet's magical powers.

Name: Blue Senturion
Summary: After the United Alliance of Evil took over the universe, the Blue Senturion was built and sent into the past to inform the Rangers about the future. Eventually he becomes part of the present time and aids the Rangers on their mission to protect the world and save Zordon

Name: Captain Falcon (Smash Bros)
Summary: Captain Falcon is a character that first appeared in the F-Zero series and eventually became famous thanks to his appearance in the very first Super Smash Bros game.

Name: Casey Rhodes
Key: '''Casey Rhodes''' | '''Dai-Shi awakening Arc (1-10)''' | '''Overlords Arc (11-21)''' | '''Phantom Beast Arc (22-32)'''
Summary: Casey Rhodes is the Jungle Fury Red Ranger. He was a fairly new member to the Pai Zhua Academy and hence known as a cub and possessed the spirit of the tiger. He has the power to stand up for what he believes in and for others. He doesn't like other people to get picked on. When Casey stood up one day for a fellow cub who was being verbally abused by Jarrod, Master Mao (the leader of the Pai Zhua Academy) dismissed Jarrod. Master Mao saw the potential that Casey had in him and chose him instead of Jarrod, to guard Dai Shi's imprisonment box.

Name: Chang'e (Touhou Project)
Summary: Chang'e is a background character in the Touhou Project series. Although she didn't make any proper appearance, she has been mentioned numerous times, notably in Legacy of Lunatic Kingdom.

Name: Chizuru Kagura
Key: '''Chapter of Orochi Saga (KOF '96 to KOF '97)''' | '''Chapter of Ash Saga (KOF 2003 to KOF XIII)'''
Summary: nan

Name: Cole Evans
Summary: Cole Evans is the Red Ranger Wild Force and the main character of Power Rangers Wild Force, leading his team of rangers against Master Org and other Orgs.

Name: Conner McKnight
Key: '''Civilian Form''' | '''Red Ranger''' | '''Super Dino Mode''' | '''Triassic Ranger, w/ Battlizers'''
Summary: Conner McKnight is the Dino Thunder Red Ranger and leader of the group. He is given the special power of super speed by his Red Dino Gem and fights alongside the other DT rangers in order to defeat Mesagog. Conner's enjoys soccer, playing at Reefside High School and on a namesake club, and he aspires to be a famous soccer star. At first, he appears to fit the stereotype of being a high school jock as he comes off as hot-headed, arrogant and being a bit of a flirt with woman but he is actually a very well-meaning and honest person who always does the right thing in the end.

Name: Darren the Ancient Sleeper
Summary: Darren the Ancient Sleeper is a mysterious being in Adventure Time, summoned by Maja The Sky Witch and was the secondary antagonist of the episode Something Big. Darren is a simple monster, wanting only battle and destruction. He was summoned by Maja the Sky Witch to destroy the Candy Kingdom for its sentimental value.

Name: Darwin Watterson
Summary: Darwin Raglan Caspian Ahab Poseidon Nicodemius Watterson Ⅲ is the deuteragonist of The Amazing World of Gumball, and is Gumball and Anais' adoptive sibling.

Name: Dino Megazord
Summary: The Dino Megazord is the original Megazord granted to the Mighty Morphin Power Rangers by Zordon, and is a combination of the Zords from each Power Ranger. It is often called upon when Rita Repulsa grows one of her monsters to destroy Earth and the Power Rangers.

Name: Donkey Kong (Super Smash Bros.)
Summary: Donkey Kong (ドンキーコング, Donkey Kong), oftentimes shortened to DK, is the eponymous protagonist of the Donkey Kong series. First premiering in the video game of the same name alongside Mario, he has since starred in a plethora of his own adventures while persisting in his rivalry against the plumber. As a member of the "perfect-attendance crew", Donkey Kong has been featured as a playable character in every installment of the Super Smash Bros. series.

Name: Dragon God (Touhou Project)
Summary: The Dragon (龍, Ryū), also called Dragon God (龍神, Ryūjin) is, according to Perfect Memento in Strict Sense, the highest god of Gensokyo. All living things, whether human or youkai, worship the dragon god. The dragon lives in sea or sky or rain, and regardless of the Great Hakurei Border, the Dragon can move freely through heaven, hell, netherworld, and the outside world. Its voice divides the sky and causes thunderstorms. When it winds its body it causes mountains to crumble and earthquakes to occur. While destroying at the same time being the creator of Gensokyo, and the rain, the rivers, abundant greens are all due to the dragon's help.

Name: Duck Hunt Dog (Super Smash Bros)
Summary: Duck Hunt Dog, also known as Duck Hunt Duo, which comprises of the classic dog, a duck, and the hunter, is a playable character in the Super Smash Bros. series. Originating in Super Smash Bros. for 3DS and Wii U, the dog throws various projectiles, the duck carries it around and assists the dog by extending its melee range, and the hunter fires at their opponents from far away.

Name: Eight Million Gods
Summary: The Eight Million Gods, also known as the Yaoyorozu no Kami, are the gods of the Touhou Project world. They always existed in the world, even before the world became the organized whole we know today. They first gave a "name" to everything, defining each object's boundary and place in the world.

Name: Eika Ebisu
Summary: Eika Ebisu is the spirit of a stillborn child, and a god of fortune, inhabiting the riverbank of the Sanzu River. Here, she acts as the leader of other stillborn children, where she often organize stone stacking contests.

Name: Eiki Shiki, Yamaxanadu
Summary: Eiki Shiki, Yamaxanadu (四季映姫・ヤマザナドゥ) is one of the Yama who judge the dead and decide whether they go to Heaven, Hell, the Netherworld, or get reincarnated. She currently resides in Hell. Whether it's because she simply has a habit of lecturing or because she genuinely wants others to change for the better, she's become well known in Gensokyo for lecturing anyone and everyone about their faults.

Name: Eirin Yagokoro
Summary: Eirin Yagokoro (八意 永琳, Yagokoro Eirin) is a medical genius from the Moon, able to create even the Hourai Elixir with the help of Kaguya's power, the manipulation of eternity. She is living in exile in Gensokyo after choosing to stay with and devote herself to Kaguya Houraisan on Earth rather than take her back to the Moon. She was a very well-known figure on the Moon, having not only been instrumental in the founding of Lunar society with Lord Tsukuyomi, but also being its leading medical mind and the person in charge of the Moon's emissaries to the Earth.

Name: Evil Dragon (Touhou Project)
Summary: The Evil Dragon was a dragon that was sealed long ago into the local Inari Shrine. It recently tricked Marisa into unsealing it.

Name: Futaba Sakura
Summary: Futaba Sakura is a member of the Phantom Thieves of Hearts. She serves as the navigator for the team after they save her by helping her to overcome her intense guilt and depression stemming from the death of her mother. She is a genius hacker who uses her skills to support the Phantom Thieves both inside and outside of the Metaverse.

Name: Gomora
Key: '''Ultraman (Generation I)''' | '''Ultraman 80 (Generation II)''' | '''Ultraman: The Ultimate Hero (Powered)''' | '''Ultraman Max (Generation III)''' | '''Ultraman Mebius (Generation IV)''' | '''Ultraman Ginga S''' | '''Ultraman R/B''' | '''Ultraman Z'''
Summary: Gomora is an ancient kaiju species from Earth. Gomora is supposedly portrayed as a hostile Kaiju, starting with the emergence of Rei's Gomora, most later incarnations of them are portrayed as comrades to respective protagonists of the series.

Name: Greninja (Super Smash Bros)
Summary: Greninja is a Water/Dark type Pokemon and the final evolution of Froakie. They are hailed as being as dangerous as any other known ninja. This specific Greninja witnessed the intense battles the Smash Bros fighters undertook, and entered it himself as a surprise entrance. He has stayed with his newfound fighting partners ever since.

Name: Gumball Watterson
Summary: My brain is amazing; when I find something boring, it actually prevents me from hearing it.

Name: Haru Okumura
Summary: Haru Okumura is a playable character from Persona 5.

Name: Hata no Kokoro
Summary: Hata no Kokoro (秦 こころ) is a menreiki youkai. As she relies on her masks to show her emotions to others, her facial expressions are emotionless and can be likened to a poker face.

Name: Hecatia Lapislazuli
Summary: Hecatia Lapislazuli (ヘカーティア・ラピスラズリ) is a mysterious Goddess of Hell who governs the Hells of the moon, the Earth, and Otherworlds. She has a separate body in each of the three worlds and can act independently with each of them. Once, she was the main leader of the Ministry of Right and Wrong, but due to unknown reasons, deserted of the organization, living now as an outlaw, controlling the Hells from the shadows.

Name: Hina Kagiyama
Summary: Hina Kagiyama (鍵山 雛, Kagiyama Hina) is a misfortune goddess that resides in the Great Youkai Forest, at the base of Youkai Mountain. It is her job to amass misfortune and scare off any humans that get too close.

Name: Houyi (Touhou Project)
Summary: Houyi is a god from Chinese Mythology. In Touhou, he is responsible for shooting down multiple suns, including one in Hell. Due to this action killing Junko's son, he was later murdered by her.

Name: Ice Climbers (Smash Bros.)
Summary: The Ice Climbers are fighters from the iconic NES game Ice Climbers. First originating in Super Smash Bros. Melee, the Climbers, comprised of Popo and Nana, fight as a team together and use various ice-based moves based off their games. They appeared in it's sequel, Super Smash Bros. Brawl, but did not appear in Super Smash Bros. 4. They returned in 2018 in Super Smash Bros. Ultimate

Name: Ichiryusai Madarame
Summary: Ichiryusai Madarame is the second major boss of Persona 5, and the Ruler of the Museum of Vanity.

Name: Incineroar (Super Smash Bros)
Summary: Incineroar is a fiery hotshot newcomer to the Super Smash Bros roster, being the only new Pokemon in its latest game. But he can more than back it up with his strength in the ring, his battle prowess earning him a spot as one of the toughest combatants to ever come out of the Pokemon series, his abilities allowing him to already fight blow for blow with the veterans. Like any cat however, he has a softer side, making friends with many of the younger, smaller Pokemon outside the ring.

Name: Isabelle (Smash Bros.)
Summary: Isabelle (しずえ, Shizue) is a playable character in Super Smash Bros. Ultimate. She is the 68th fighter overall. While she shares many moves with Villager, Isabelle is not an Echo Fighter and is instead a semi-clone.

Name: Iwanagahime
Summary: Iwanagahime was a goddess from Mt. Fuji. She used to live with her sister, Konohana-Sakuyahime, until the latter partially destroyed a mountain out of spite. This caused Iwanagahime to move to what will eventually become the Youkai Mountain.

Name: Jason Lee Scott
Summary: Jason Lee Scott is the original Red Ranger of the Power Rangers series, and in a sense was the first true main character. He led the team during the struggles against Rita and even a bit into the Zedd times, but eventually left to attend a Peace Conference. He has later come back as the Gold Ranger in Zeo and as a Red Ranger in the special Forever Red.

Name: Jigglypuff (Super Smash Bros.)
Summary: Jigglypuff (プリン, Purin), is a creature from the Pokémon series. It debuted in the series' first generation, and is considered part of the "perfect-attendance crew" throughout the entire Super Smash Bros. series.

Name: Joon Yorigami
Summary: Joon Yorigami is Shion's younger twin sister and a goddess of pestilence. While she inevitably leads those around her to financial ruin, she is better liked than her sister and is much more driven. Using her abilities and her skill in conning others, she gets them to use up all their money for her before abandoning them once they're completely drained of fortune and money.

Name: Junpei Iori
Summary: Junpei Iori is a playable character in Persona 3/FES. He is best friends with the protagonist, meeting them at the start of the game and becoming a member of SEES due to being able to percieve the Dark Hour, and as such, able to summon a Persona, a fact discovered by one of the members of SEES itself.

Name: Junya Kaneshiro
Summary: I went through shit until I crawled my way out of the dregs! Now it's my turn to profit on everyone else! It doesn't matter whether you're clean or dirty! Only the clever come out on top! The strong and the smart devour the weak. That is the natural order of things. You damn brats who think you know the world through the shit you read online will make the perfect prey

Name: Justin Stewart
Summary: Justin Stewart is the blue ranger of the Turbo team. Justin a child prodigy who lost his mother at a young age. After Rocky damaged his leg, Justin went to see him in the hospital where he found the secret identities of the Power Rangers. After the Rangers received the Turbo Powers, they were missing a Blue Ranger. The Blue Turbo Power went to Justin as Rocky was in a bad shape, making him the new Blue Power Ranger. Justin would fight against Divatox and her armies for the entire season without being replaced as the first Turbo Rangers did. After the Command Center explodes, Justin doesn't join the Rangers on their way to follow Divatox to space and decides to stay on Earth but ready to help if they ever need him again.

Name: Kanako Yasaka
Summary: Kanako Yasaka (八坂 神奈子) is the current goddess of the Moriya Shrine, following her victory over Suwako during the Great Suwa War, thousands of years in the past. Due to her dependence on faith, which was scarce in the Outside World, she moved her shrine to Gensokyo so she could collect it more easily.

Name: Keiki Haniyasushin
Summary: Keiki Haniyasushin (埴安神 袿姫 Haniyasushin Keiki) is a god summoned by human spirits and acts as the main antagonist of Wily Beast and Weakest Creature.

Name: Ken (Super Smash Bros.)
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:KenIsReadyForYaSoBringItOn.ogg

Name: Ken Amada
Summary: Ken Amada is a Playable Character in Persona 3. Growing up only with his mother, one night his mother died in an accident where Shinjiro Aragaki's Persona went out of control, killing her. Swearing revenge and unable to get anyone to believe him due to the nature of the Dark Hour, Ken joins SEES 2 years later to kill Shinjiro. During a Full Moon Operation, Shinjiro gave his life to save Ken from a bullet from Takaya Sakaki; causing Ken to feel remorse over his plot to take his life. By Persona 4 Arena Ultimax, Ken had further matured into a responsible young man, choosing to live for both his Mother and Shinjiro's sake, becoming an auxiliary member for Mitsuru's Shadow Operatives.

Name: Kim Kaphwan (The King of Fighters)
Key: '''Prologue Chapter (KOF '94) ''' | '''Chapter of Orochi Saga (KOF '95 to KOF '97)''' | '''Chapter of NESTS Saga (KOF '99 to KOF 2001)''' | '''Chapter of Ash Saga (KOF 2003 to KOF XIII)'''
Summary: nan

Name: King K. Rool (Smash Bros.)
Summary: King K. Rool is the 67th fighter to be added to Super Smash Bros. Ultimate. In Adventure mode, he, along with everyone else besides Kirby, was incapacitated. When Galeem was defeated, he was captured by Dharkon.

Name: Kirby (Smash Bros.)
Summary: Tier: High 6-A, higher with Final Smash | Low 2-C, higher with Final Smash

Name: Kogasa Tatara
Summary: Kogasa Tatara (多々良 小傘 Tatara Kogasa) is a subspecies of the Tsukumogami, a Karakasa obake. Originally coming from the Outside World, she ended up in Gensokyo where she became a Youkai that feeds on fear. Although with time passing, humans became less scared and she was left desperately trying to scare humans.

Name: Komachi Onozuka
Summary: Komachi Onozuka (小野塚 小町) is a lazy shinigami who ferries souls across the Sanzu River and works for Eiki Shiki, Yamaxanadu. While she is a slacker and a slow worker, she tends to copy her boss' habit of lecturing others and has little else to talk about besides suicide and other death-related horrors.

Name: Konohana-Sakuyahime
Summary: Konohana-Sakuyahime is the Goddess of Volcanoes in Gensokyo. She resides on Mt. Fuji. Years ago, a group of humans came to her mountain to drop a jar into the volcano. Unfortunately, the jar contained the Hourai Elixir, which would trigger the volcano's eruption hard enough that not even Sakuyahime could stop it. As such, she convinced the humans to not drop it in the volcano. As a precaution, she also murdered most of them in their sleep. The two survivors had to carry away the Elixir, although one of them killed the other and took the Elixir for themselves. Said person will go on to become Fujiwara no Mokou.

Name: Koromaru
Summary: Koromaru is a playable character in Persona 3/FES. Koromaru is an albino Shiba Inu. When he joined SEES, he was given a special Evoker for dogs, a metallic collar around his neck. He has a red armband on his left arm, a miniature white t-shirt and very small angel-esque wings on his back.

Name: Kunikazu Okumura
Summary: Kunikazu Okumura is the fourth major boss of Persona 5, and the Ruler of the Space Station of Greed.

Name: Kutaka Niwatari
Summary: Kutaka Niwatari (庭渡 久侘歌 Niwatari Kutaka) is a god of chickens and a guard of Hell. She lives in a spring atop the Youkai Mountain but goes to Higan for her job of overseeing the gateway to otherworlds such as Hell under the yama's oversight. Kutaka first appeared as the stage 3 midboss and boss in Wily Beast and Weakest Creature, attempting to dissuade the protagonist from entering Hell. She speaks in a polite, somewhat refined manner, and despite already being authorized to let the protagonist through, she takes extra care to test the protagonist's strength out of concern for their well-being.

Name: Kyo Kusanagi
Key: '''Prologue Chapter (KOF '94)''' | '''Chapter of Orochi Saga (KOF '95 to KOF '97)''' | '''Chapter of NESTS Saga (KOF '99 to KOF 2001)''' | '''KOF Sky Stage''' | '''Chapter of Ash Saga (KOF 2003 to KOF XIII)'''
Summary: nan

Name: Leanbow
Summary: Leanbow is Udonna's husband, Bowen's father (AKA Nick Russel), and the mentor of Daggeron and Calindor. He was known for his honor and valor which Calindor resented. As a Mystic, he can assume "Ancient Mystic Mode", resembling a red/purple fiery demon wielding a sword and shield. Twenty years prior to the series, Leanbow led the other Mystics in the Great Battle against the Supreme Master of the Underworld, and his Forces of Darkness led by Morticon in order to prevent them entering the human realm. The forces of good magic eventually forced the Forces of Darkness through the Gate of the Underworld, with Leanbow personally taking on Morticon at one point. In order to keep the Forces of Darkness from escaping the Underworld, he held back the Darkness hordes from the Gate while Niella the Gatekeeper sealed both it and Leanbow into the Underworld.

Name: Lord Tsukuyomi
Summary: Lord Tsukuyomi is the leader and ruler of the Lunar Capital. Very little is known about him.

Name: Lucina (Super Smash Bros.)
Summary: Lucina (ルキナ, Lucina) is one of the primary protagonists of Fire Emblem: Awakening, being the daughter of Chrom who traveled into the past in order to save her future from disaster. She was first introduced in Super Smash Bros. for Nintendo 3DS/Wii U, and has since appeared in Super Smash Bros. Ultimate as well.

Name: Luigi
Summary: Luigi is Mario's younger, taller, and thinner twin brother. He is a major protagonist of the Mario series. Luigi has helped and fought alongside his brother on many occasions.

Name: Makoto Niijima
Summary: There are too many incidents in this country that are never brought to light. That host was one. Villains who prey on the hearts of the weak with cowardly, legally questionable methods... My father risked his life trying to catch a group of those people. I will never forgive them. But I won't be able to eradicate them all on my own... Instead, I want to head an organization that will destroy the lawless and help rescue victims. (The Player chooses) Your father would be proud. I hope so... That is the justice I aim for. I also believe it will be a continuation of my father's legacy

Name: Makoto Yuki
Summary: Makoto Yuki is the protagonist of Persona 3/FES/Portable. He is a transfer student enrolling in Gekkoukan High School in Iwatodai City. He is an orphan whose parents died on the Moonlight Bridge in their car during a fatal incident a decade before the events of the game. He has dark blue hair unkempt at the front, blue eyes, and a light build, being shorter than average. His bangs cover his right eye. He is often shown with his hands in his pockets. He is very stoic, reserved, and calm, gathered by the fact that he remains unmoved even when guns are pointed at him. He appears very introverted, distant, and aloof since he only observes the conversations of his party members and only speaks when someone is directed at him for his opinion on the matter.

Name: Mario (Super Smash Bros.)
Summary: Mario (マリオ, Mario) is the eponymous protagonist of the Mario series. Unanimously viewed as the mascot of Nintendo, Mario is said to be the most well-known and most popular video game character in the world, having appeared in over 200 video games. As a member of the "perfect-attendance crew", Mario has been featured as a playable character in every installment of the Super Smash Bros. series.

Name: Marth (Super Smash Bros.)
Summary: Marth (マルス, Marth; formerly translated as Mars prior to Super Smash Bros. Melee) is the main protagonist of the first game in the long-running Fire Emblem franchise, Fire Emblem: Shadow Dragon and the Blade of Light, and has been an extremely important presence throughout the entire series. He has made an appearance in every entry of Super Smash Bros. franchise ever since his premiere appearance in Super Smash Bros. Melee)

Name: Martin Mertens
Summary: Martin Mertens, also formerly known as Mr. M, is Finn's biological father. Billy calls him "Dad the Human", similar to Finn's title "Finn the Human". He was first revealed in the episode "Billy's Bucket List".

Name: Megabug
Summary: Megabug is a dragon-like creature of pure energy. It happens to be aberration of time and space from the dimensional vortex that altered the fabric of Mario's world, created from the Rabbids' Time Washing Machine after a blast of the SuperMerge visor. Initially, appearing as a blue dimensional rift, it slowly grows larger and changes colors from the energy it absorbs from the all the Rabbids-fused enemies Mario and his allies defeated, which happened to be created by Spawny under Bowser Jr.'s command. It eventually gains form and absorbs Spawny and later Bowser to form MegaDragonBowser. After Mario, his friends, and their Rabbid counterparts teamed up and defeated it, the monstrosity disappeared and the rift along with it, making the world safe once more.

Name: Mewtwo (Super Smash Bros)
Summary: Mewtwo is one of the oldest Pokémon representatives in Super Smash Bros, debuting in Super Smash Bros: Melee. He was absent for the next game, Brawl, replaced by a functionally identical character, as well as the next game before he was finally added back into the series in the form of free DLC by popular demand, and remains in the series to this day.

Name: Mii Fighter
Summary: The Mii Fighters are warriors based on the customizable Mii avatars.

Name: Minoriko Aki
Summary: Minoriko Aki is one of the two goddesses of autumn. Her job is to make harvest fruitful by helping farmers with their plantations.

Name: Mitsuru Kirijo
Summary: Mitsuru Kirijo is the only child of the current head of the Kirijo Group, Takeharu Kirijo. She is also the Gekkoukan High School’s valedictorian and student council president as well as the leader of the Specialized Extracurricular Execution Squad (S.E.E.S.), an organization composed of Persona users to battle Shadows during the Dark Hour.

Name: Mizue no Uranoshimako
Summary: Mizue no Uranoshimako was a human fisherman from Earth, who accidentally found himself on the Moon. Believing it to be the Dragon Palace, he stayed there for three years before being sent to his world, but three hundred years into the future. When he arrived, everyone he knew had disappeared, and no one believed his stories about the Dragon Palace. In despair, he opened up the box that was gifted to him, which made him age all of his 300 skipped years. Despite his old age, rumors about the old man's visit to the Dragon Palace spread around the land, eventually reaching the Emperor's ear. However, Uranoshimako had already died by the time the Emperor got to him. A shrine was built in his name, and he eventually became a god.

Name: Morgana (Persona)
Key: '''Beginning of the game''' | '''Early Game''' | '''Mid Game''' | '''Late Game''' | '''End Game'''
Summary: Morgana is a playable character in Persona 5.

Name: Mr. Game & Watch
Summary: Mr. Game & Watch is an inhabitant of a completely flat world called Flat Zone. He does various chores there, varying from cooking to fighting a giant octopus and even saving a princess. However, the 2D composition of his body made him a prime target for Tabuu's evil plan. He was captured by Tabuu and convinced to produce the Subspace Army for him. He also was the one controlling the Halberd. He was later stopped by Peach and co. and brought back on their side by giving him an umbrella.

Name: Ness (Super Smash Bros.)
Summary: Ness is a character that first appeared in EarthBound (or Mother 2 in Japan) and eventually became famous thanks to his appearance in the very first Super Smash Bros game (mostly in the U.S).

Name: Nicole Watterson
Summary: Nicole Watterson is one of the main characters in The Amazing World of Gumball. Nicole is the mother of the Watterson family. She is the only truly responsible member of the family. She is very dedicated to her family, and would do anything in her power to keep them comfortable and safe.

Name: Okina Matara
Summary: Okina Matara (摩多羅 隠岐奈, Matara Okina) is a secret god who lurks behind all things, hiding in plain sight behind a number of public faces and disguises, such as an Earth Mother Goddess, a god of Noh, a god of the stars, a god of silkworm breeding, a god of impediments, and a god of burakumin. No one knows her true identity, but she was one of the sages who helped create Gensokyo in the past. Now, living in the Outside World, she protects Gensokyo and maintains its balance.

Name: Pichu (Super Smash Bros.)
Summary: Pichu is a playable character in Super Smash Bros. Melee and Super Smash Bros. Ultimate, as well as the pre-evolved form of Pikachu.

Name: Pikachu (Super Smash Bros.)
Summary: Pikachu (ピカチュウ, Pikachu) is a character from the Pokémon series, often serving as the mascot of the entire franchise. Being a member of the "perfect attendance crew," he has appeared in every Super Smash Bros. game to date.

Name: Piranha Plant (Smash Bros.)
Summary: Piranha Plant (パックンフラワー, Packun Flower) is a playable character in Super Smash Bros. Ultimate. Revealed alongside Ken and Incineroar on November 1st, 2018, it is the first DLC character in Ultimate, and was made available for purchase on February 1st, 2019. However, it was made available at no cost as early as January 29th, 2019 for players who purchased the digital version of Ultimate or registered their physical version with My Nintendo by January 31st, 2019. Piranha Plant is not part of either Fighters Pass, making it the only DLC character with this distinction. Piranha Plant is classified as Fighter #70.

Name: Pokémon Trainer (Super Smash Bros)
Summary: The Pokémon Trainer, alongside Pikachu itself, is the main Pokémon representative in Super Smash Bros. They also serve as the Super Smash Bros universe's Pokémon League Champion, retaining his title since Brawl.

Name: Popeye
Summary: First introduced Dice Island, a story arc in the comic strip Thimble Theater in 1928, Popeye the Sailor Man would later become the main focus of the strip, as well becoming as one of the most iconic comic and cartoon characters of all time. "Borned to the sea" near the bay of Santa Monica, Popeyes' childhood was hard. The ship he was born on was rocked by a massive typhoon just moments after his birth, though his family was ultimately unharmed by the event. Growing up, both his father, "Poopdeck Pappy" and his unnamed mother left his life at a young age. Eventually, Popeye decided to join the military. Despite his rough and gruff appearance, Popeye was a good guy who hated bullies and defended the weak.

Name: R.O.B. (Smash Bros.)
Summary: R.O.B. (Robotic Operating Buddy) is a playable character in the Super Smash Bros series.

Name: Raiko Horikawa
Summary: Raiko Horikawa is one of the Tsukumogami created by the Miracle Mallet incident. While enjoying her new power, she soon realized that her existence was temporary, due to the Mallet's power eventually fading away. Thus, she took a risky move and changed her own drums to obtain a new power source.

Name: Ramza Beoulve
Summary: Ramza Beoulve, also known as Ramza Lugria, is the main protagonist in Final Fantasy Tactics. Third son of House Beoulve, son of Barbaneth Beoulve and a commoner woman of the Lugria family, Ramza is the younger half-brother of Dycedarg and Zalbaag, and the full older sibling of Alma.

Name: Richard Watterson
Summary: Richard Watterson is one of the main characters in The Amazing World of Gumball. He serves the role of the father in the Watterson family. Unlike the traditional father, however, Richard is not wise, nor is he a good role model for his children in any way. Despite his misguided advice and uncouth mannerisms, Richard has good intentions and loves his family all the same.

Name: Rinnosuke Morichika
Summary: Rinnosuke Morichika (森近 霖之助, Morichika Rinnosuke), nicknamed Kourin (香霖), is a half-human half-youkai hybrid and using his ability to know the name and purpose of an object, he runs Kourindou, an antique shop specializing in items from the Outside World. He's one of the few male characters depicted in the Touhou Project and is the protagonist of Curiosities of Lotus Asia.

Name: Rita Repulsa
Summary: Rita Repulsa was initially the primary antagonist of Mighty Morphin' Power Rangers, though was eventually shoved to the side by her much more powerful and commanding husband, Lord Zedd.

Name: Robin (Super Smash Bros.)
Summary: Robin (ルフレ, Reflet) is a playable character in both Super Smash Bros for Nintendo 3DS/Wii U and Super Smash Bros Ultimate, where he served as one of the primary protagonists of Fire Emblem: Awakening and the customizable avatar character of the game.

Name: Ryuji Sakamoto
Key: '''Beginning of the Game''' | '''Early Game''' | '''Mid Game''' | '''Late Game''' | '''End Game'''
Summary: Ryuji Sakamoto is one of the founding members of the Phantom Thieves of Hearts. A troublemaking delinquent at a glance, his colorful vernacular and rough appearance belie his kind and loyal heart. After awakening his Persona and obtaining the Metaverse Navigator, he and the other Thieves became determined to change the corrupted society they lived in by stealing the hearts of the wicked. With every heart he steals, he hopes to galvanize the weak and downtrodden and get them to stand up against those that would prey on their misery and suffering.

Name: Ryuji Yamazaki (The King of Fighters)
Key: '''Chapter of Orochi Saga (KOF '95 to KOF '97)''' | '''Chapter of Ash Saga (KOF 2003 to KOF XIII)'''
Summary: nan

Name: Sae Niijima
Summary: Sae Niijima is the fifth major boss of Persona 5, and the Ruler of the Casino of Envy.

Name: Sagume Kishin
Summary: Sagume Kishin (稀神サグメ Kishin Sagume) is a reclusive, high-ranking official on the Moon. Due to her power to reverse any situation by merely speaking of it, she is similar to an Amanojaku, but instead of acting contrarily, the world acts contrarily in response to her words. While she can be tentatively classified as a Divine Spirit, but her true nature is not that of a God.

Name: Shadow Futaba
Summary: I am the other you. How long will you continue blaming yourself and shutting yourself away from the world? For your mother's death. Don't you think it's time you grasped the truth of that moment? What happened before your eyes... What happened to your mother... Why did you choose to rely on the Phantom Thieves? Are you simply going to shut yourself in and do nothing? Are you going to avert your eyes from the true answer? If so... I will kill them in your world

Name: Shingo Yabuki
Key: '''Chapter of Orochi Saga (KOF '97)''' | '''Chapter of NESTS Saga (KOF '99 to KOF 2001)''' | '''Chapter of Ash Saga (KOF 2003 to KOF XIII)'''
Summary: nan

Name: Shinjiro Aragaki
Summary: Shinjiro Aragaki is a playable character in Persona 3. Shinjiro grew up alongside Akihiko Sanada in orphanage in their childhood. One day, Shinjiro encountered Mitsuru Kirijo and joined her original SEES group to fight the shadows. Tragically, later on Shinjiro's persona went berserk and killed an innocent woman: Ken Amada's mother. After the event, Shinjiro left SEES and began taking suppressants to control his persona and stopped attending school all together.

Name: Shion Yorigami
Summary: Shion Yorigami is Joon's elder twin sister and a goddess of poverty. As she brings misfortune and ruin everywhere she goes, she is universally despised, and she is incredibly unlucky herself. Due to the loathing she is subject to, Shion is generally depressed and lacks any motivation to do anything, preferring to let other people handle things for her while she wallows.

Name: Shizuha Aki
Summary: Shizuha Aki is one of the two Aki goddesses of Autumn. Her job is to turn leaves red and make them fall from trees, although she does this by physically painting them red.

Name: Shockwave (IDW)
Summary: I shall remove the very concept of "change". All of space and of time shall exist as a single point, an ultimate singularity. An ultimate black hole. Here, on Cybertron.

Name: Soul King
Summary: Adnyeus (アドナイェウス, Adonayeusu?), more commonly known as the Soul King (霊れい王おう, Reiō?), is the king of Soul Society, whose existence in Soul Society is as symbolic as it is absolute. The king resides in the Soul King Palace that exists in a separate, special realm in the very core of Soul Society, which is protected by the Royal Guard. The door to this realm is opened via the Ōken.

Name: Stewie Griffin
Summary: Stewie Griffin is one of the main characters in the animated series, Family Guy.

Name: Subspace Army
Summary: The Subspace Army is an organization hailing from Subspace led by Tabuu. It is the main antagonistic force of the Subspace Emissary, acting as the source behind most threats faced by the heroes. Its goal is the absorption of the World of Trophy into Subspace, done by the usage of Subspace Bombs. As Tabuu cannot leave Subspace, most of the forces are located in the World of Trophy while Tabuu manipulates them from Subspace. Those include the Isle of the Ancients, the Halberd (Piloted by Mr. Game & Watch) and the Koopa Troop. Most relations within the army are quite fragile, however, as a lot of them are done either through force or trickery. Notably, almost no one knows the existence of Tabuu, as the latter hides behind Master Hand to communicate his orders to his commanders.

Name: Suguru Kamoshida
Summary: Drop the attitude, you mediocre peasant! There's no wrong in using my gifts for my gain! I'm a cut above all other humans!

Name: Suwako Moriya
Summary: Suwako Moriya (洩矢 諏訪子, Moriya Suwako) is the original goddess of the Moriya Shrine, prior to Kanako's take over. Officially the shrine belongs to Kanako, but Suwako handles the divine services. She is a native god born from and formed of faith, and Sanae Kochiya is her distant descendant and shrine maiden.

Name: Takaya Sakaki
Summary: Takaya Sakaki is a character from Persona 3. Takaya is the confident and charismatic young leader of Strega who was once experimented on by the Kirijo Group. He functions as the protagonist's foil, leading the rival group of Persona-users and setting himself up as a false messiah.

Name: Tenryu (Touhou Project)
Summary: Tenryu, also known as the Celestial Dragon, is one of the Dragons in the world of Touhou Project. It is a living constellation in Heaven that is bound to eventually devour the Unmoving Star, also known as the North Star.

Name: Terry Bogard (The King of Fighters)
Key: '''Prologue Chapter (KOF '94) ''' | '''Chapter of Orochi Saga (KOF '95 to KOF '97)''' | '''Chapter of NESTS Saga (KOF '99 to KOF 2001)''' | '''KOF Sky Stage''' | '''Chapter of Ash Saga (KOF 2003 to KOF XIII)'''
Summary: nan

Name: The Overlord (Ninjago)
Key: '''Spirit form''' | '''Possessing Lord Garmadon''' | '''Dragon Form''' | '''The Digital Overlord''' | '''The Golden Master''' | '''Crystal King'''
Summary: In the First Realm, only two races existed, the Oni, and the Dragons, beings who controlled creation and destruction, and who fought each other in an eternal stalemate. One day, however, a child who was born of both the Oni and the Dragon was born. This child, known as the First Spinjitzu Master, was sought by both races as a means to end the war. Seeing that the two races would never find peace and couldn't understand the balance that was necessary for existence, left the realm to create his own, which became known as Ninjago. However, as the balance dictates that a world must have both good and evil, the Overlord - the dark spirit that had always existed - emerged into the Realm. The First Spinjitzu Master and the Overlord fought tirelessly and endlessly until The Overlord created a stone army to finally kill him. Knowing that he would eventually lose, the First Spinjitzu Master split the land in two, the Overlord being sealed into The Dark Island. However, the Overlord saw the arrival of Lord Garmadon, and thus waited for the ultimate battle between good and evil. Eventually, his prediction came to pass, with Lord Garmadon being betrayed by the Serpentine and left to rot in the ocean, eventually landing on the island. Manipulating Lord Garmadon and starting the Celestial Clock's countdown, which would dictate the beginning of the battle, The Overlord tricked him into spreading darkness through the Garmatron into Ninjago, shifting the balance back to darkness and restoring his powers.
